title: curried rice salad
directions: Make Rice-A-Roni as directed on package.
Chop the green pepper and green onion and add to rice.
Mix all the rest together and chill.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix the onion, garlic, lime juice and picante sauce together in a large mixing bowl.
Cut avocados in half lengthwise.
Twist the halves to separate.
Scoop out the halves with a spoon and mash with a fork.
Add in remaining ingredients.
Top with the cheese.
Serve with warm tortilla chips.
Serves 8 as a dip.

title: christmas tea
directions: Mix and put in closed container.
Let stand a few days before using.
Mix 3 teaspoons with a cup of hot water.

title: five can casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except bread crumbs in 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Yields 4 servings.

title: sour cream raisin bars
directions: Mix well in double boiler. Cook until thick, 15 to 20 minutes.

title: snicker cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Grease and flour 9 x 12-inch pan.
Pour half of batter in pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Put caramels, milk and butter in a saucepan and heat until melted, then pour over cake.
Sprinkle on chocolate chips and nuts on top of caramel mixture.
Pour on rest of cake batter.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°, then turn down oven to 250° and bake 20 minutes more.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Put caramels, butter and milk in a double boiler and melt.
Put half of cake batter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Pour caramel mixture on top and pour other half of cake batter over caramel mixture.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts on top.
Bake for another 25 minutes.

title: cabriolet of beef
directions: Trim fat off meat and cut in bite size pieces.
Preheat with enough soy and teriyaki sauce to cover bottom of skillet.
Add meat; brown and stir.
Reduce heat to low.
Add 50/50 mixture of soy and teriyaki sauce to cover approximately 3/4 depth of meat. Add generous dash of Worcestershire sauce.
(Optional:
Add small dash of Tabasco sauce.)
If needed, add water to just cover meat; simmer 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Place vegetables in boiling water and boil for 3 minutes; drain.
Cover vegetables with lite salad dressing for 4 to 6 hours.
Top mixture with a sprinkling of parsley flakes and serve on toothpicks.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll into balls.
Bake for 15 minutes. Cool and freeze, or bake for 20 minutes and serve.
These can be heated in toaster or oven.

title: crab melts
directions: Split muffins apart.
Melt butter with onion.
Add cheese and crab meat.
Spread mixture on muffins.
Place muffins on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cut in quarters and serve.

title: sock-it-to-me cake
directions: Blend first 6 ingredients together with mixer.
In a separate bowl, mix 3 tablespoons brown sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon. Grease and flour a tube or Bundt pan (even if it is Teflon).
Place 1/3 of the batter in pan and sprinkle 1/2 of sugar mixture evenly over this.
Add 1/3 more of batter, then sugar mixture.
Repeat. Bake at 325° for approximately 60 minutes or until done.
Let cool for 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: pearl meat ball
directions: Put sweet rice in a bowl of water for 4 hours.
Put pork, scallions, egg, mushroom, salt, cornstarch and salt in bowl and mix thoroughly.
Rinse rice and place in another bowl.
Make meatball round in hand and dip into sweet rice so that it sticks around the meatball.
Steam meatballs for 20 minutes.
When rice is transparent-like, it is done.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 cake pan with cooking spray.
Sprinkle desired amount of brown sugar in pan.
Spread drained pineapple over the brown sugar and put desired amount of cherries wherever you want them placed.
Put aside.

title: no bake orange balls
directions: Mix crushed wafers, powdered sugar, orange juice and 1 cup crushed walnuts in a large bowl.
Use enough Karo to hold the mixture together.
Chill.

title: bell chiffon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in 1 cup hot water; add 1 cup cold water. Add pineapple, cottage cheese, milk, mayonnaise and nuts.
Mix together well; pour into desired mold.
Chill until set.
Yield: About 20 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add peanut butter. Mix well; add vanilla and eggs. Add flour last. Roll into balls. Press with fork. Bake at 300°.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Keep in sealed jar.
Use 2 teaspoons to 1 cup boiling water.

title: beer cheese soup
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Add chicken broth; stir until lumps are gone.
Add half and half.
Add cheese, Cheez Whiz, and Worcestershire sauce.
Let it simmer; stir occasionally until all cheese is melted.
Pour in beer 15 to 20 minutes before serving. Sprinkle with chives or popcorn if desired.

title: frosted ambrosia
directions: Roll scoops of vanilla ice cream in flaked coconut.
Put in sherbet glasses.
Pour a little defrosted, but not diluted, orange juice concentrate around the ice cream scoop.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Boil and drain noodles; mix noodles with all other ingredients.
Put into greased 11 x 13-inch casserole.
Top with crushed cornflakes.
Dot with lots of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: jiffy corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except the butter.
Melt butter or margarine in a pan and pour the corn bread mixture over butter. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together flour, salt and baking powder.
Add corn meal. Combine milk, well beaten egg, syrup and oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix just enough to moisten flour mixture.
Pour into a greased square pan.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.

title: banana loaf
directions: Mix together and pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 325° to 350° for about 1 hour.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, sugar, buttermilk and eggs.
Pour into an 11 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Mix brown sugar and cinnamon together and swirl in cake.
Mix the powdered sugar, milk and vanilla.
Pour over cake.
Cook at 350° until done, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: christmas tree soup
directions: Boil skinned chicken in water.
Cool chicken and shred into pieces.
In the broth combine onion and spices.
Simmer 15 minutes with chicken pieces.
Add noodles and cook per directions.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add egg, sour milk, soda, baking powder, vanilla, salt and flour.
Add nuts and raisins if desired.
Drop cookies by teaspoon and smash with cup or roll and cut.
Bake on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.

title: pizza hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper.
Add soup.
Cook noodles but not until well done.
Mix noodles with hamburger and soup.
Add pizza sauce and mushrooms.
Mix together.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Put in cake pan.
Bake at 350° until cheese browns.

title: pork chop meal
directions: Brown pork chops and onion lightly in oil.
Add potato, cut in chunks, cabbage, cut in chunks, apple juice, vinegar, pepper and dried mixed fruit.
Simmer on low for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 2 generously for one-dish meal.
Serve with salad and Italian bread or rolls.

title: wassail
directions: Put brown sugar, whole cloves and cinnamon in top of coffee pot.
Perk with other ingredients in a 30-cup pot.

title: cinnamon apples
directions: In saucepan, place 1 cup water and 1/2 cup cinnamon candies (red hots).
Cook together until candies are completely dissolved. Peel and cut 5 or 6 apples into 8 wedges.
Put apples into the syrup and gently simmer for 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and let the apples cool in syrup.
Refrigerate, leaving apples in syrup until serving.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: another good icing (karol's)
directions: In saucepan melt butter, cocoa and Eagle Brand.
Heat and remove from stove.
Sift in confectioners sugar.
Beat for 1 minute.
(I've never tried this but Karol says it's good.)

title: tiger butter
directions: Mix white chocolate and peanut butter together well.
Pour mixture on wax paper, spoon melted milk chocolate over peanut butter mixture.
With a spatula marbleize.
Put in freezer to set up.
Cut into squares.

title: homemade butter
directions: Lay margarine out at room temperature and let soften.
Mix all ingredients.
Beat until fluffy.
Place in fridge to cool.

title: scotch teas
directions: Melt butter; stir in brown sugar.
Add baking powder and oats. Spread in 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Be sure to remove from pan before completely cooled (very important).

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Add sugar.
Mix and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Mix jello and water.
When jello begins to thicken, add cranberry mixture.
Add pineapple, apples, bananas and nuts to this mixture.
Pour into mold and place in refrigerator to set. Makes a large amount.

title: peach pudding
directions: Put all ingredients into the blender and process at liquefy until smooth.
Cook over low heat until thickened.

title: pickled onions
directions: Combine water and canning salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Take 2 cups of salted water and 1 cup vinegar and boil; then pour onions in this mixture and pack into jars.
Add dill or garlic, if desired. Seal while hot.
Repeat process for additional onions.

title: *pork chops supreme
directions: Salt, pepper and flour each chop.
Brown in skillet and place in a buttered, shallow baking dish.
Add potatoes, onion and carrots.
Cover with soup and milk.
Salt and pepper vegetables. Cover and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until meat is tender. Makes 4 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Beat shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add bananas and beat.
Add flour and baking soda.
Add nuts.
If you would like, you can add 1/2 cup chopped dates.
Bake in loaf pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: diet barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until thick, about 30 minutes.

title: copper carrot pennies
directions: Pour over carrots, etc. Better if refrigerated 10 to 12 hours. Will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: vanilla wafer candy
directions: Mash vanilla wafers and chopped nuts.
Mix milk, mashed wafers and chopped nuts together.
Use powdered sugar on your fingers. Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
No baking.
Place on wax paper.

title: lime cucumber salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Strain cucumber and onion.
Mix with cottage cheese, mayonnaise and almonds.
Fold into jello. Chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cheese stand at room temperature for an hour or so. Place in mixing bowl with onion and Worcestershire.
Mix well with
fork until
smooth
and
well blended.
Stir in milk, a little at a time.
Cover and chill until firm.
Set 4 hours or overnight. Shape
the
cheese
into
a ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill until
ready
to
serve.
Serve
on platter with crackers.

title: pumpkin pie(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar replacement and spices until blended. Stir in eggs and mix well.
Slowly add milk and blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake in 400° oven for about 40 minutes or until firm.
Makes 1 pie.
Makes 8 pieces or 8 servings.
One serving equals 1/2 milk, 1 bread and 1 fat.

title: goblin granola
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Great for Halloween parties.

title: beef yorkshire pie
directions: Cook beef and onion in hot skillet.
Remove and drain.
Mix in next 5 ingredients.
Heat well-greased 10-inch skillet (cast-iron is best) in 400° oven.

title: michigan chilies rellenos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray casserole with Pam.
Combine yogurt, egg and flour until smooth; set aside.
Combine cheeses in other bowl.
In casserole sprinkle 2 ounces of cheese in bottom of casserole; top with chili peppers, then cheese mixture.
Pour yogurt mixture on top, then tomato sauce, then rest of cheese. Bake until puffed and edges are slightly browned, about 40 minutes. Per serving:
458 calories, 28 grams protein, 30 grams fat, 19 grams carbohydrates, 1087 mg sodium.
Serves 2.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls out on a large ungreased cookie sheet like you are making a pizza crust. Make sure to get as many of the air bubbles out as you can.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown (do not overbake).
Let cool completely.

title: raw veggie dip
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill at least 1 hour.
Contains 40 calories per tablespoon.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add the eggs and flour to sugar. Fold the buttermilk and nutmeg into mixture.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies or 1 deep dish pie.

title: fresh peach polka dot pie
directions: Arrange peaches, cut side down, in pastry lined pan.
Mix sugar, flour, mace and salt.
Stir in cream gradually.
Pour over peaches.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Bake at 400° about 45 minutes until filling is set.
Serve warm or cold.

title: cherry delight
directions: Work together with pastry blender.
Place in 9 x 13-inch dish and press half-way up the sides of dish and on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, until lightly brown.

title: hamburger macaroni casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat, chopped onion and chopped green pepper in skillet.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix corn meal, onion, flour, baking powder and salt together. Add milk and mix.
Blend in beaten egg.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Butter casserole dish.
Sprinkle rice over bottom of dish. Add soups and milk and stir.
Lay chicken parts on top.
Sprinkle onion soup over all.
Cover dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Don't peek.

title: tasty fish
directions: Fork fish slightly and place in a large, Ziploc bag.
Put Italian dressing in with fish (enough to cover fish).
Marinate for 6 hours.
Grill outside for 8 minutes on each side.
Serve with vegetables.

title: spinach pie
directions: Cook spinach, squeeze all water out and let stand.
Mix eggs, milk, cottage cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Add spinach and mix. Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top and serve.

title: oyster stew
directions: Empty oysters and juice into saucepan; bring to medium boil. Add milk and simmer slowly until oysters float on top.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line bottom of three 9-inch round cake pans with wax paper. Microwave chocolate and water in large microwave on High 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until chocolate is almost melted, stirring halfway through heating time. Stir until chocolate is completely melted.

title: toll house mud bars
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
Set aside.
In bowl, beat brown sugar, oleo and vanilla until creamy.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour mixture.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread in a 9-inch square baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
Immediately sprinkle 2/3 cup chocolate chips over top.
When morsels are shiny, spread evenly.

title: savory corn bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 2-quart casserole.
In a large bowl, combine milk and egg yolks; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into a measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, cornmeal, baking powder and pepper; beat until smooth.
Stir in green pepper, corn and bacon.
In a small bowl beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into corn mixture.
Pour into dish.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 70 minutes or until center is firm.
Serves 8.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, layer the bean dip and piquant sauce. Combine avocados, lemon juice, salt and pepper; layer next. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning; layer next. Top with onions, tomatoes, olives and cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Serve with chips.

title: a whale of a good meal:  corn flake fish
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Grease 12 x 8-inch baking pan.
Beat together egg and milk in bowl.
Place corn flakes in sealable plastic bag.
Seal and beat into crumbs.
Open and add flour. Seal and shake bag.
Pour contents of bag onto a plate.
Dip fish fillets into egg mixture, coating both sides, then drag through corn flake mixture, again coating both sides.
Place in pan; dot with margarine.
Bake for 15 minutes.
You know it's good when your kids demand more!

title: chicken with broccoli
directions: Combine chicken fricassee, cheese, cream and curry powder and cook in a chafing dish for 10 minutes, stirring frequently. Serve on hot platter surrounded with broccoli. Serves 6.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Melt butter in a 6-quart saucepan.
Add onions, salt and pepper. Saute until golden. Add flour, stirring and blending for 2 minutes. Add broth and milk, stirring constantly, until mixture starts to boil. Remove from heat.
Add broccoli and cheese. Return to heat until cheese is melted.
May be made ahead and reheated.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: venison
directions: Slice meat into thick pieces (about 1/2 inch thick).
Dip meat in flour until completely covered.
Heat oil.
Place meat in hot oil, salt and pepper, cook until golden brown.
Turn and fry other side.

title: momo's 7-up cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream together sugar, oleo and crisco.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Add lemon extract to eggs.
Add egg mixture to sugar and shortening mixture and mix together.
Blend in 3 cups of presifted flour - one cup at a time.
Finally, fold in one cup of 7up.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake for 1 hr 15 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes then turn onto plate.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Put first three ingredients in blender.
Cover and quickly turn blender on and off.
Heat butter until melted or almost boiling.
Turn blender on high speed; slowly pour in butter, blending until thick and fluffy, about 30 seconds.

title: grapefruit salad
directions: Add tablespoon water in large bowl to gelatin, then dissolve sugar into boiling water and add to gelatin mixture.

title: pineapple ham casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In a large skillet, saut celery in 1 tablespoon butter until tender. Stir in cream cheese and milk; cook until cheese is melted.
Add the noodles, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Transfer to an ungreased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Melt remaining butter; toss with bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, Ranch dressing and Miracle Whip.
Spread over top of crescent roll crust.
Top with assorted vegetables (i.e., broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, green peppers, etc.).
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Arrange apple slices in bottom of a buttered casserole.
Top with cinnamon, salt, lemon juice and water.
Blend sugar, flour and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and yellow rice casserole
directions: Cook rice following directions on package.
Mix all ingredients except paprika and pour into 9 x 13 inch casserole dish.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: oatmeal crispies(cookies)
directions: Cream sugars and butter until frothy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla until blended.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Sift flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats.
Chill.
Drop by spoonfuls on lightly greased sheets.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: cream cheese roll
directions: Mix cream cheese, green onions and all but one package of dried beef together. Shape into ball.
Roll ball in remaining package of dried beef.
Chill.
Serve with snack crackers.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Serve on your favorite sandwich bread, roll, croissant or lettuce leaf for a salad.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown bacon; drain.
Brown hamburger and onion.
Add rest of ingredients, mix and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy pasta and veggies
directions: Heat milk, bouillon and cheese until cheese melts.
Nuke mac and cheese.
Nuke broccoli.
Combine milk and cheese with mac and broccoli.

title: homemade light bread
directions: Scald milk.
Add oleo and sugar.
Set aside to cool.
Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Set aside.

title: poppy seed breadnederland, texas
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and bake in 7 loaf pans at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: patty cake
directions: Bake at 350°
for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in shortening until consistency of small peas.
Beat egg; mix with water and vinegar. Add at once to flour mixture; mix together with fork.
Divide into 4 balls of equal size.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour while making filling.
Yields 2 double crust pies.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle coconut and pecans evenly on bottom of pan. Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Spread over nuts and coconut. In microwave-safe container, melt cream cheese and butter in microwave oven. Stir confectioners sugar into cream cheese mixture, mixing well. Spread over cake batter. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until center is set and lightly browned.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion.
Drain.
Add soup, vegetables and water.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Put in Pyrex dish; top with biscuits.
Bake at 400° until biscuits are brown (8 to 10 minutes).

title: deer jerky
directions: Stir this mixture well with a spoon to dissolve all of the soluble ingredients.
Place the strips of meat in the marinade. Be sure they are completely submerged.
Marinate overnight, turning if necessary.
Lay marinated meat strips on oven rack. Cook for 6 to 8 hours at 150°.
They get crisper the longer they bake.
Store finished jerky in Ziploc bags or other airtight containers to seal in freshness.

title: chocolate chip muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add eggs, milk, orange juice, orange rind and oil and blend lightly.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Fill greased muffin tins or paper liners 2/3 full and bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Mix chicken soup with 2 ounces water.
Crumble croutons.
Dip chicken into soup mixture, then into croutons.
Place on greased baking pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In 6-quart pot, brown roast on all sides in 2 tablespoons oil. Spoon off fat.
Stir in soup and onion soup mix.
Add 1 cup water.
Reduce to low heat.
Cover and cook 2 hours.
Add vegetables and cook 45 minutes or until tender.
Remove roast and vegetables.
Stir in flour and 1/4 cup water until smooth.
Bring to boil and thicken.
Stir constantly.
Place roast on dish and cover with mix.
Garnish and season to taste.

title: vinegar pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients, then mix with margarine.
Mix together vinegar, vanilla and beaten eggs; add to first mixture and pour in 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in 300° oven for 45 minutes or until pie is set.
(An extra tablespoon of vinegar may be used if a more tart pie is desired.)

title: divinity
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and water until it spins a hair (hard ball). Pour into beaten egg whites, beating all the time.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: manicotti
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Add eggs, bread, milk and approximately 1 cup cheese (more if you like).
Stuff shells with mixture.
Pour some of the spaghetti sauce in the bottom of a cake pan, then place stuffed shells in pan.
Pour remainder of spaghetti sauce over the shells and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 325° until thoroughly heated and cheese is melted.

title: apple goody
directions: Sprinkle over apples and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken.
Layer a 13 x 9-inch pan with broccoli, then chicken.
Mix soup, mayo, spices and lemon juice; pour over broccoli and chicken.
Put bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Last 10 to 15 minutes, add cheese.
Very good!

title: pink cloud
directions: Heat pineapple and sugar.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Remove from stove and add dry Jell-O.
Cool.
Add cream cheese and blend well. Add Cool Whip and spread in 9 x 13-inch container.
Chill in refrigerator for several hours.

title: deviled tomatoes
directions: Melt
butter
or
margarine
in top of a double boiler. Remove from
heat
and stir in eggs, vinegar, sugar, mustard, salt
and cayenne
pepper.
Beat
the eggs until frothy, stir into the seasoned mixture and cook over hot water until water in bottom of double boiler comes to a boil.
Turn off heat and let
mixture stand
over
the
water
about 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Bake
tomatoes at 350° about 7 to 10 minutes or until
tender, but
still
keeping their shape.
Arrange on a warm serving platter
and pour the hot deviled egg sauce over tops.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: grandma glover's peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in a pan; pour over batter and then put fruit on top.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Best to use your hands. Form into a ball or whatever shape you wish. Serve with an assortment of your favorite crackers. Best if you make day ahead and chill overnight.

title: date and nut cake
directions: Pour hot water over dates; cool.
Combine shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add alternately with date mixture on low speed.
Blend only until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: asparagus cheese soup(servings:  4)
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour and seasonings.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Return to heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add asparagus and cooking water; heat to simmering. Remove from heat and stir in cheese until melted.
Garnish with paprika, if desired.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix.
Add 2 cups flour saving some out to coat fruit.
Mix and add fruit and mix well.
Bake for 2 1/2 hours at 275° with a pan of water under cake as it bakes.
Grease and line pans with wax paper.
Makes 4 (1 pound) loaves or 1 tube pan.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add cooked rice.
Combine other ingredients with above.
Stir until cheese melts.
Spray baking dish with Pam.
Pour mixture in dish and bake 20 to 30 minutes in 350 degree oven.

title: eggs benedict arnold
directions: To save final preparation time while entertaining hungry guests for brunch, the eggs can be poached ahead of time.
Poach slightly underdone.
Place in ice water until you begin making the sauce.
Replace ice water with warm water to bring the eggs up to room temperature.
As the sauce nears completion, replace the warm water with boiling water to heat the eggs prior to serving.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix together and set overnight in refrigerator.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter, vanilla and mace.
Mix in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Mix 1/4 cup flour in cherries and 1/4 cup flour in pineapple and 3/8 cup of flour in pecans.
Mix all together and put in tube pan.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: 1-2-3 pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cut loaves in half.
Toast bread lightly.
Spoon sauce over bread.
Add toppings.
Put Mozzarella cheese on top.
Bake 10 minutes or until cheese melts.

title: harvest salad
directions: Tear lettuce and spinach into 1 to 2-inch pieces.
Slice radishes, carrots and red cabbage finely.
Lightly toss together and add ham, turkey and cheese.
Top with croutons and tomato wedges.
Add your favorite dressing.

title: hungarian goulash
directions: In a large skillet, heat cooking oil.
Saute onion until soft and transparent, but not browned.
Add beef cubes and brown; add stock, paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and reduce heat. Simmer 1 hour; add potatoes, carrot and tomato juice.
Simmer 30 minutes longer (until beef is tender and vegetables cooked).

title: egg casserole
directions: Beat eggs, milk and cornstarch.
Mix with rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into a greased dish.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oatmeal and soda; add flour and baking powder.
In another bowl, mix vinegar and milk and let stand for 5 minutes. Mix remaining ingredients; stir wet ingredients with dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: apricot whip
directions: Combine ingredients; chill.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Return to refrigerator to set.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Add scalded milk last.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes or until knife comes out of center clean.

title: quick pepper steaks
directions: Cut steak and
green peppers into 1/2 inch strips; cook and stir in oil
in
large skillet until meat loses red color. Stir in water, gravy
mix
and soy sauce.
Cover; simmer 10 to 15 minutes until
tender,
stirring
occasionally.
Onion may also be used.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir together flour, salt and soda.
In a separate bowl, mix Crisco, sugars, egg, water and vanilla.
Mix the dry ingredients with sugar mixture.
Stir in old fashioned Quaker oats, using a spoon.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown the ground beef and onions; drain. Add ketchup, mustard, salt and pepper to the meat mixture; heat until bubbly. Line the bottom of a 9 x 13 baking dish with biscuits. Spoon the meat mixture over the biscuits. Top with the cheese slices. Cut the remaining biscuits into quarters and place them point side down around the edge of the pan. Bake in a 400° oven for 15 to 17 minutes.

title: onion pie
directions: Combine crushed crackers and 1/2 cup melted oleo and press into a casserole dish.
In skillet, mix onions and 1/4 cup oleo. Saute until onions are clear.
Put into cracker crust.
Sprinkle cheese over onions.
Mix milk, eggs and salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add vinegar and water and bring to boil.
Cool.
Add milk and mayonnaise.
Pour mixture over cooked macaroni, celery, onions and chopped hard cooked eggs. Refrigerate overnight.

title: lo-cal dip
directions: Make "fake" sour cream by creaming 1/2 of the cottage cheese with 1 teaspoon of vinegar.
Gradually add remaining cottage cheese and vinegar; blend in mayonnaise.
If too thick, add milk until desired consistency.
When "fake" sour cream is complete, add package of salad dressing mix; blend well.

title: golden fried chicken
directions: Heat oil in skillet until hot.
Roll chicken in pancake mix; place in skillet.
Sprinkle salt and pepper over chicken.
Brown chicken lightly, then lower heat and cook until tender.
Turn chicken over when needed.

title: squash pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes, then 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: walnut frosties
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
Gradually add sugar to butter in mixing bowl, creaming until light and fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla, beating well.
Gradually add the dry ingredients, mixing well after each addition.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Make a depression in center of each cookie; place 1 teaspoon topping in depression. Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes or until delicately browned. Makes about 48 cookies.

title: burrito bake
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper together.
Drain well. Add taco seasoning and 1 cup water.
Simmer 20 minutes.

title: stir and drop oatmeal cookies(serves 18)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease baking sheet.
Stir into bowl, flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and ginger;
add sugar, oats, oil, 2 to 3 tablespoons milk, egg and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon about 2 inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Cook sausage and drain; set aside.
Scramble eggs in bowl.
Add one or two tablespoons of chopped nacho slices into scrambled eggs. Drain juice of Ro-Tel and add contents to bowl.
Put pan of sausage on medium heat.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix all ingredients
together thoroughly as listed, one at a time.
Pour in
a
tube
pan
that
has
been greased and sprinkled with flour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Remove from oven and
pour the following sauce over cake while in pan.

title: hanky panky hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cook beef and sausage together until done. Add cheese, garlic, Worcestershire sauce and oregano.
Let cool.
Lay slices of party rye on cookie sheet. Top each slice with meat mixture. These can now be put in the freezer for 20 minutes or until frozen.
Put in Baggies.
When ready to bake, take them out of the freezer, put on cookie sheet and broil for 5 to 10 minutes.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in greased 12 x 18-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Combine soup with milk and stir well.
Spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with stuffing mix.
Drizzle oleo over the stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Recipe can be cut down.

title: chili
directions: Saute onions and green peppers with the cooking oil.
Mix in ground beef, tomato sauce, molasses, pepper and salt, then add kidney beans.
Simmer 1 hour and add chili powder.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in margarine.
Mix in corn and rice.
Top with slices of Velveeta cheese.
Bake in a casserole at 350° for 45 minutes or cook in a crock pot at low setting 2-3 hours.
Stir often.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: *Mixed vegetables, asparagus or mushrooms may be substituted for broccoli.

title: squash casserole
directions: Steam squash in microwave until tender, about 9 minutes. Saute carrots and onion in margarine
until tender.
Mix remaining ingredients together, including package of herbs from dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: weight control chicken salad
directions: Mince zucchini and mushrooms.
Stir in chicken, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Fill pita pockets.
Serves 2.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Add vegetables and saute until tender. Add uncooked rice and soups.
Mix well.
Pour into casserole dish. Cook 1 hour in oven at 350°.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add egg and milk.
Roll dough 1/2-inch thick.
Cut into 3-inch rounds.
Place 1-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Split when cool. Fill with sweetened strawberries and top with whipped topping.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well; pour into an unbaked pie shell (9-inches) and bake in a 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and top with whip cream or ice cream, if desired.
Even served nothing tops this.

title: stuffed pepper cups
directions: Cook beef and onion until meat is lightly browned; drain. Season with salt and pepper.
Add tomatoes, water, rice and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer the mixture until rice is tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add 4 ounces of cheese; stir well.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Mix well most of the ingredients together, folding in zucchini and pineapple last. Pour into 2 greased loaf pans and bake in a 350 degree oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit bars
directions: Cover bottom of a greased and floured 8 x 13-inch pan with the nuts.
Mix together the margarine, brown sugar, eggs and flour. Add the red cherries, green cherries and pineapple, all cut up. Spread mixture over nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: tuna and cheese macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni per package instructions and drain and rinse. Add tuna, drained mushrooms and soup to macaroni.
Cook over medium heat until warm through.
Add cheese.
Mix until melted. Serves 6.

title: white salad
directions: Crumble Ritz crackers
in
bowl.
Add
walnuts.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff, add sugar and fold in cracker mixture. Bake at 350° for 5 to
minutes	in greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool completely.

title: crazy kristy cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and baking soda.
Don't sift!
Make 3 holes for cocoa, oil and white vinegar.
Add water and vanilla. Mix well by hand.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in 8-inch pan.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix pudding according to directions.
Add Cool Whip.
Put a layer of graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add 1/2 of above mixture, another layer of crackers, rest of mixture and cover with crackers.
Let sit while making the topping.

title: diabetic pumpkin pie filling
directions: Place pie filling in prepared crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife tested and comes out clean.

title: banana split cake
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix graham crackers, 1 stick melted margarine and 1/2 cup pecans.
Pat into 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan.

title: reba's rolls
directions: Mix yeast with warm
milk.
Add
salt,
sugar,
oil and eggs; mix well, then add
flour
(more
if
needed).
Place in bowl about 1/3 larger than dough.
Let
rise
to
top of bowl. Work down with large spoon.
Place
on floured waxed paper and shape into rolls.
Place in greased pan and let rise.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix together egg whites and 2 tablespoons of water.
Mix rest of ingredients except pecans and add to egg mixture.
Mix pecans in egg whites and spices until coated.
Place on cookie sheet, covered, with foil.
Butter the foil.
Spread pecans on foil.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Spread on waxed paper and cool.

title: sylvia's rolls(very good)
directions: Add shortening to flour, salt and sugar.
Mix yeast with warm water and add to flour mixture.
Add milk and mix.
Let stand 1 hour.
Then roll out and cut in biscuits.
Fold these in half and place in pan and let set one hour.
Bake in a 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Spread a little butter on rolls before baking.

title: chicken baked in rice
directions: Mix rice, water and soup mix in baking dish. Place chicken on top and dot with margarine. Salt and pepper. Cover and bake 1 and 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: cherry almond muffins
directions: Beat egg, stir in milk, oil, cherry syrup and almond extract. Mix in flour, 1/4 cup sugar, cherries, baking powder and salt, just until flour is moistened.
Fill 12 muffin cups 2/3 full.
Mix 2 Tbsp. sugar and 2 Tbsp. chopped almonds.
Sprinkle over batter in muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: creamy baked cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Cook beef and onions in a saucepan on medium heat, until done. Drain fat and add the remaining ingredients to the saucepan.
Cook together on medium heat about 15 - 30 minutes until it starts to thicken a little, stirring always to keep it from sticking.
Eat with tortilla chips or flour tortillas (cut up).

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, basil, salt and pepper.
Thinly slice mushrooms and onion; add to first mixture.
Refrigerate for at least 1/2 hour.
Wash and tear spinach in pieces; drain well and put into salad bowl.
When ready to serve, add mushrooms and oil mixture to spinach and toss.

title: shirley's easy pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add
eggs,
one
at a time. Beat well after each addition.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and beat well.
Bake in greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours or until
cake
tests done.
Cool in pan on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: In a saucepan add cornstarch, sugar, lemon juice, pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook until thick.
Cool, then add Cool Whip, pineapple, fruit cocktail, oranges and cherries.

title: fudge pie
directions: Melt margarine; stir in sugar, cocoa, flour and salt.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla.
Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Place chicken in casserole dish. Mix chicken soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Melt margarine; add crushed crackers and poppy seed.
Pour over soup. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: southern style pound cake
directions: Beat softened butter about 2 minutes.
Gradually add sugar. Beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add one cup at a time to the butter and sugar mixture.
Separate eggs.
Add yolks to batter.
Beat egg whites until stiff and add to batter.
Pour in a tube pan and bake at 300° for 2 hours or until done when tested. This recipe came out of Southern Living.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, butter, peanut butter, sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Blend in sugar and salt.
Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Shape dough into balls.
Flatten with fork in crisscross pattern to 2 inches.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until set.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Place milk, salt, sugar and butter in mixing bowl.
Gradually add yeast and flour.
Place dough in a greased bowl and brush top with butter.
Let rise to double its size, 2 to 3 hours.

title: guacamole
directions: Mash avocados.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill or enjoy ASAP, as we do.
Serve with tacos or chips or by the spoonful.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Crush chips while in bag (real fine).

title: caramel nut pie
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk and brown sugar in a double boiler; cook until thick.
Add the pecans and pour into prepared crust.
Top with whipped topping and coconut.

title: potato casserole
directions: Spread potatoes (thawed) into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cut up butter and spread on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Mix sour cream, soup and cheese.
Spread on top of potatoes.
Top with cracker crumbs and butter.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Can be prepared a day ahead.

title: mexicorn casserole
directions: Mix all together and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: lois' apple cake
directions: Cream eggs, oil and sugar.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased and floured tube pan.

title: lemon crunch pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into a large greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° until center springs back when touched.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Simmer	onion, celery, sugar, salt, bay leaves, cloves, Lea & Perrins
and Tabasco, uncovered, for 5 minutes in 1 cup tomato juice.
Soften the unflavored gelatin in 1 cup of cold tomato juice.
Dissolve this in the hot juice mixture.
Add 1 cup cold tomato juice and lemon juice.
Chill until firm.
May add carrots or olives.	Serves 8 to 10.

title: chicken and artichokes
directions: Season chicken parts with salt, pepper and paprika.
Brown 12-15 minutes in 4 tablespoons butter.
Remove chicken from pan and place in casserole.
Add 2 tablespoons butter to skillet and saute mushrooms about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, bouillon and Sherry.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Arrange artichokes over chicken.
Pour sauce over top.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 375°.

title: double crust pear pie(9-inch pie)
directions: Roll half of pastry to 1/8 inch thickness on lightly floured surface; fit into a deep-dish 9-inch pie plate.
Combine 1/4 c. brown sugar, 1 tablespoonful all-purpose flour in a large mixing bowl; stir well.
Add pears, tossing lightly to coat; spoon into pastry shell.
Combine 1/2 cup flour, lemon juice, butter and sprinkle over pears.
Roll out remaining pastry to 1/8 inch thickness and place over filling.
Trim edges;
then seal and flute.
Cut slits to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yield: one 9-inch pie.

title: black and white cookies
directions: Beat butter (softened) and sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla and egg.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add chocolate chunks and nuts, if desired.
Drop onto foil-covered cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes, until almost cooked in center.
Cool completely so center sets.

title: oven crispies
directions: Boil butter, sugar and half and half for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; dip bread squares into hot mixture.
Place on buttered cookie sheet; bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Put baked bread on rack to cool.
They will get crispy as they cool. Dip in chocolate if desired.

title: dill weed dip
directions: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Makes two cups. Delicious with chips and raw vegetables.

title: lemon coconut dessert
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press firmly into bottom of 9-inch pan.
Beat egg yolks in large bowl until thick.
Stir in milk, lemon juice and rind and blend.
Fold in 1 2/3 cups of coconut and Cool Whip.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold into the lemon mixture.
Spoon over crust.
Sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Freeze until firm, about 5 hours.
Makes 9 servings.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Lightly brown sausage and chopped onion.
Beat egg with water; add soup and mix together.
Add the Rice Krispies and rice, sausage and onion and half of the cheese.
Stir together.
Cover with shredded cheese and bake for 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: cinnamon balls
directions: Combine butter, sugar and vanilla.
Cream until light and fluffy. Sift together the flour and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in corn flakes and pecans.

title: corn chowder
directions: Saute onion in pan sprayed with Pam until transparent, not brown.
Mix onion, bacon bits, cooked potato and creamed corn.
Mix flour with enough water to make a thin paste and stir into milk. Cook until slightly thickened and add to corn mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: maine corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels.
Set aside. Saute onions in bacon drippings until soft.
Add potatoes, water, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer about 15 minutes until potatoes are done.
Add corn and milk.
Heat thoroughly. When serving, garnish with crumbled bacon.

title: apple bars
directions: Mix flour, 1 tablespoon sugar, salt, margarine, shortening, egg yolk and milk.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out onto 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Spread Rice Krispies on top of unbaked crust.
Add apples, 1 1/2 cups sugar and cinnamon; cover with top crust.
Beat egg white until stiff and spread over top crust.

title: meatball surprise
directions: Prepare Stove Top per package directions; cool.
Form the dressing into balls and wrap them with ground beef.
In a saucepan, combine the milk, mushroom soup, Worcestershire sauce and catsup; heat.
Pour over meatballs and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: party cheese cakes
directions: Bring cheese to room temperature.
Add sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Spoon into cup cake papers already in the pan.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.
Let set 5 minutes.
Spoon topping into depression left from cooling cakes.
Bake another 5 minutes.

title: cream crab soup
directions: Heat soup in pan.
Whisk in half and half.
Reheat - do not boil.
Add crab (shrimp also if desired).
Heat! Eat! Enjoy!

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: To the mashed potatoes, add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
This recipe can be assembled the night before and baked the day of.
If the dish has been refrigerated, remove about 1 hour before baking.
Serves 10 to 14.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Combine and shake well; store cool.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix Veg-All, corn, celery, onion, mayonnaise and cheese. Place in an 8 x 8-inch casserole.
Top with Ritz cracker crumbs which have been mixed with the butter.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: skillet chicken (or beef) teriyaki
directions: Mix soy sauce, water, sugar, garlic and ginger together. Saute chicken/beef in oil, about 10 minutes.
Remove meat; drain oil.
Return meat to pan; pour sauce over the pieces.
Bring to a boil, then cover.
Simmer for 20 minutes, turning occasionally. Serve with sauce over rice.

title: chicken with artichokes and red peppers
directions: Sprinkle chicken with Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
In a large, nonstick skillet, heat oil (enough to cover thinly the bottom of skillet).
Add chicken.
Saute 1 1/2 minutes per side until lightly browned.
Remove and reserve.
Add onion to skillet and saute briefly.
Stir in artichokes with marinade and pepper strips.
Add chicken broth.
Cook over high heat 6 to 8 minutes until liquid is reduced to a thin sauce.
Reduce heat to low. Return chicken to skillet.
Cook until heated through.

title: 24-hour salad
directions: Tear lettuce into small pieces.
Chop cauliflower into little flowerets.
Dice onion into tiny pieces.
Fry bacon crisp and break into crumbs.
Thaw out package of frozen peas.
Put in Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle sugar lightly over the top.
Spread mayonnaise over top.
Cover and refrigerate.
Mix well.

title: palmer's granma jean's biscotti from lee lee
directions: Mix eggs and sugar.
Add oil, anise and vanilla.
Mix flour with baking powder.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture slowly, beating well after each addition.
Let dough rest 1 to 3 hours or overnight (makes it easier to handle).
Form into loaves approximately 1/2-inch thick and 2 to 3 inches wide.
Don't let loaves touch.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Let cool. Slice diagonally into 1/2 to 3/4-inch slices.
Sprinkle with sugar and toast slices in pan in oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until slightly brown.
Store in sealed container.
You can add 12 ounces chocolate chips to the recipe with the eggs and sugar.
Great.

title: salmon bake with pecan crunch coating
directions: Sprinkle salmon with salt and pepper; place skin side down, in lightly greased 11 x 7 x 1 inch or 9 inch square baking pan.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Season chicken.
Mix rice with soup mix in ungreased pan. Lay chicken on top of rice.
Add water and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Check after 20 minutes.
Add water if needed.

title: lemon barbecue chicken salad
directions: Sprinkle chicken with lemon juice and salt.
Add rice, celery and stuffed olives, toss until well mixed.
Mix mayonnaise, liquid smoke and barbecue sauce.
Stir into rice-chicken mixture and chill.
Serves six.

title: vanilla horns
directions: Mix flour, butter and sugar with fingers until mixed well.
Add nuts and shape with fingers in horn figures.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
While hot, dip in powdered sugar.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch or larger ungreased baking pan or casserole dish.
Optional:
Sprinkle 1 cup or more crushed potato chips on top.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour uncovered.
Let sit 5 minutes before serving.

title: mock pecan pie
directions: Bake in unbaked pie shell 10 minutes at 450° and 30 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix beans, peas, onions, pepper and pimento together.
In a separate bowl, mix well vinegar, oil and sugar.
Pour over bean mixture, stirring well.
Let marinate overnight or for several hours.
It is optional to drain before serving.

title: sukuma wiki("push the week")
directions: Wash greens several times.
Remove stems and ridges.
Using only the leaves, cut the greens into thin strips about 1/8-inch wide.
Saute onions and tomatoes in margarine.
Stir-fry sukuma (greens) with onions and tomatoes until bright green.
Add water and salt.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.

"Sukuma Wiki" or "Push the Week" is so called in Kenya because toward the end of the week, when food supplies are low and the next pay day is a few days off, they cook this to "Push the Week" and stretch the groceries until they can buy more.
Therefore, no Kenyan family would serve "Sukuma Wiki" to guests.
It would be an insult.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream, mustard, onion, salt and pepper. Set aside.
Layer in glass bowl the lettuce, eggs, peas, macaroni, ham strips and cheese.
Top with mayonnaise mixture and chopped parsley.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: pizza (two 12 inch pies)
directions: Dissolve
the
yeast
in
cup warm water.	Add the flour, olive oil, salt and 1 cup of warm water.
Knead together
for
10 minutes.
Place in an oiled bowl to rise, covered with
plastic wrap.
When the dough has doubled in bulk (about 2	hours) punch it down and divide in two.	Let the dough rest a few minutes.

title: savory pepper steak
directions: Coat steak with mixture of flour, salt and pepper.
In large skillet, brown strips in shortening.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add reserved liquid, water, onion, garlic and gravy base to meat.
Cover; simmer 1 1/4 hours or until meat is tender. Uncover; stir in Worcestershire and add green peppers.
Cover; simmer meat and peppers for 5 minutes.
If gravy is too thin, combine 1 to 2 tablespoons all-purpose flour with an equal amount of cold water; stir into sauce.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add drained tomatoes, cut up; cook 5 minutes more. Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mexican wedding cookies(yields 100 portions)
directions: Cream the butter and 1 pound of confectioners sugar.
Add vanilla and blend.
Gradually blend in flour and oats or nuts.
Portion with a No. 40 scoop.
Place cookies 6 x 8 on ungreased sheet pans.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes. Bake until set but not brown.
Cool slightly and sprinkle each pan of cookies with confectioners sugar.

title: the vicar's irish soda bread
directions: Blend together all dry ingredients.
Make a well in the middle and add milk and sour cream.
Blend until it holds together.
Knead in the bowl about 4 minutes.
Shape dough into a ball and then flatten it until it is about 3 inches high and slightly rounded on top.
Place loaf on greased cookie sheet.
Score a cross about 1/2-inch deep on top.
Lightly rub top of loaf with milk.
Bake for 45 minutes in preheated 400° oven.
Flip loaf over onto its top and bake another 5 minutes.
Wrap in a damp dish towel and stand loaf on its side to cool.

title: sonora chicken
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Debone chicken and tear into bite size pieces.
Mix all other ingredients except chicken, cheese and tortillas.
Tear tortillas into pieces.

In 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole pan, layer 1/2 of the tortillas, 1/2 of the chicken, 1/2 of the sauce and 1/2 of the shredded cheese; then repeat layers. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°, or until completely heated.

title: gingerbread muffins
directions: Using low speed of electric mixer, blend molasses, brown sugar, oil, cinnamon, ground cloves, nutmeg and ginger. Add boiling water; blend.
Gradually add flour, beat 2 minutes or until smooth.
Dissolve baking soda in 2 tablespoons hot water. Add to batter.
Blend.
Pour into 8-inch square Teflon baking pan or into paper-lined muffin tins.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: president's chicken
directions: In a pan, mix together all ingredients except chicken breasts and heat over low flame until butter or margarine has melted. Place chicken breasts in a shallow baking dish and pour sauce over the breasts.
Broil 30 to 35 minutes, turning chicken occasionally, to coat well with sauce.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Drizzle pan drippings over the rice or noodles for a delicious flavor boost.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and salt.
Bring to a full boil, stirring occasionally.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat, stir in vanilla.
Beat until thick and creamy.
Spread on cake.

title: cream puffs
directions: Bring shortening and water to a boil.
Add dry ingredients quickly.
Beat until the batter leaves the side of the pan. Remove and cool.
Add eggs one at a time, beating each one until smooth.
Drop by tablespoons onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Fill with vanilla pudding.
A little cream added to instant vanilla pudding makes a light filling.

title: turkey
directions: Stuff inside of turkey with bell pepper, apple, celery, onion, 1 stick margarine, salt and pepper.
Baste outside of turkey with 1 stick melted margarine; salt and pepper.
Wrap in foil or put in browning bag.
Bake in 300° oven until done (approximately 15 minutes per pound).

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix spaghetti and dressings; set in refrigerator overnight. Then add remaining ingredients.
Let stand one hour before putting in refrigerator.
Vegetables should be dry and added a short time before eating to be crunchy.
I usually make half of the recipe.

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Set oven at 375°.

title: purlough
directions: Boil chicken with bay leaves and celery stalks until completely cooked.
Debone chicken and retain stock for later use. Discard celery and bay leaf.
Cut bacon strips in half.
Fry in medium Dutch oven or heavy pot with a tight fitting lid until done but not crispy.
Remove bacon from pan.
Saute onion in bacon grease until transparent.
Do not discard grease.
Add sausage to onion and cool until sausage is warmed up.
Add chicken and bacon; heat until all are warm.
Add chicken stock (chicken bouillon may be substituted), 2 cups of stock to each cup of rice.
(To serve 4 people use 4 cups stock and 2 cups rice.)
Bring mixture back to a low boil.
Cover tightly and cook until rice is done, stirring often to prevent sticking (approximately 20 minutes).

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, then applesauce.
Add flour and spices; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add nuts, raisins and dates.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours in a 325° oven.

title: cinnamon christmas cookies
directions: In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and cinnamon. Set aside.
In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla extract.
On low speed, gradually beat in flour mixture until combined.
Divide dough in half.
Shape each half into a ball.
Wrap and refrigerate until firm, approximately 1 to 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
On a lightly floured board or between 2 pieces of waxed paper, roll dough to 1/3-inch thickness.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Bake until golden brown, approximately 10 minutes.
Cool before decorating or frosting.
Let decorated cookies set overnight, loosely covered, to set frosting before putting into gift tins or cookie jars.
If a "sugar cookie" is preferred, add colored sugars prior to baking and omit frosting.

title: homemade lye soap
directions: Note:
Always make soap before the new moon.

title: old fashioned raisin pie
directions: In a bowl, beat eggs.
Add sour cream.
Stir in remaining ingredients; pour into pie crust.
Top with lattice crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350°; bake for about 25 more minutes, or until filling is set.
If desired, sprinkle with nutmeg.
Makes 8 servings.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Mix flour, baking powder and salt in bowl.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beating well after each addition. Mix in food coloring and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan for several minutes.
Invert onto serving plate.
Spread frosting over cake.
Garnish with chopped pecans.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: venison and rice
directions: Salt and pepper a 5 to 6 pound rib roast.
Pierce roast on all sides with knife.
Preheat oven at 375°.
Put roast in baking pan.
Bake for 1 hour; turn off oven.
Do not open door!
When ready to serve, turn oven back on and heat to 375°.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes.
Roast will be crisp on the outside and rare in the middle.

title: fresh peach cooler
directions: Place peaches, honey and a small amount of milk in a blender, puree until smooth.
Add remaining milk and ice cream, blend until smooth and frothy.
Serve with peach slices.

title: spinach sesame salad
directions: Mix soy sauce, oil, vinegar, garlic and seasonings.
Pour over spinach.
Sprinkle with sesame seed; toss lightly.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage in frypan.
In bowl, mix milk, eggs, mustard, salt and pepper.
In casserole dish, layer the bread crumbs, sausage, cheese and 1/2 egg mixture.
Repeat with layer of bread crumbs, sausage, cheese and other 1/2 egg mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: instant cocoa mix
directions: Mix and store in a covered container.
Stir 1/3 cup into 1 cup hot water.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a bowl.
Add oleo or shortening and cut into the flour.
Beat the eggs and the milk. Pour in flour mixture and mix until it looks like cake.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in baking dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and place marshmallows on top.
Return to oven and slightly melt and brown marshmallows.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes in boiling salted water.
Drain well.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, eggs, cheese, pepper and onion. Mix well.
Add broccoli and turn into greased 2-quart baking dish. Sprinkle with crushed Ritz crackers and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until it bubbles and browns.
Serves 8.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: To half of toasted bread cubes, add chicken, celery, cheese, almonds, onion and pepper; toss well.
Add lemon juice and mayonnaise, mix well.
Place in casserole, top with remaining bread cubes.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Can be prepared ahead and frozen.

title: creme de menthe brownies
directions: Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage well and drain.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch casserole baking dish.
Tear bread in small pieces and sprinkle over margarine.
Sprinkle drained sausage over bread crumbs. Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs and other ingredients; pour over mixture.
Chill for 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° 45-50 minutes.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add nutmeg, eggs and flour. Roll thin.
Cut out desired shapes, and bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes, or until lightly brown around edges.

title: barbecue chicken
directions: Mix ingredients and pour sauce over chicken; boil until done. Use sauce used in boiling to serve over rice with chicken.
For a whole chicken, triple recipe.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream together butter, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool and roll again in powdered sugar.

title: chocolate pudding delight
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Put in a greased 11 x 16 x 2-inch cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cook pudding according to directions.
Let cool.
Spread over cake. Refrigerate until pudding is completely cooled.
Put Cool Whip on top of pudding.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Keep refrigerated.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to pkg. directions, drain.
Transfer to a large bowl;
then add the next ten ingredients and mix well. Spoon into greased 13 x 9 cake pan.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese if desired.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 40-45 minutes or until heated through.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream well.
Add flour, salt, water and vanilla.
Stir in chopped pecans; blend.
Shape dough into date-like pieces.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm. Yields 90 cookies.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Grate cheese and Spam.
Melt butter.
Mix all ingredients. Chill a few hours.
Spread on buttered hot dog buns and broil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease casserole. Combine soup, sour cream and milk. Mix until smooth. Combine the soup mixture with the chicken and vegetables and put in casserole. Prepare dressing according to directions on the package and crumble over mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chile con queso
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add diced tomatoes and jalapenos.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Slowly add Cheddar cheese.
Serve immediately over tortilla chips.

title: chi chi punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together in punch bowl and serve.

title: kenneth's done it again cream cheese surprise
directions: Slice the cream cheese lengthwise while it is cold.
Put a slice of smoked salmon and onion.
Continue to layer the cheese, salmon and onion until it all is stacked.
Put the caviar and lemon juice on top.

title: fish batter
directions: Mix ingredients.
Dip fish fillets and fry in hot fat (375°) for 5 minutes.

title: herb potatoes(4 pates)
directions: Heat sour cream, thyme, butter and savory on potatoes and mash.
Put in shells and sprinkle with paprika and cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: frozen fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients well and freeze.
Thaw approximately 3 hours before serving or only freeze until slushy.
This should be served as a slushy drink.
Makes approximately 1 gallon or enough for 20 servings.

title: peanut patties
directions: Mix and cook for 8 minutes.
Add oleo, vanilla and red food coloring.
Beat until creamy.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Mix jello and boiling water.
Add other ingredients and stir until candies are dissolved and mixture is well blended. Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: special angel food cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on cake mix box.
When batter is foamy, add the unbeaten egg whites.
Finish mixing according to box directions.
Bake according to the directions on the box also. When done baking, the cake will stand real high.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Brown chicken.
Saute onion and pepper.
Brown rice in same oil.
Place all ingredients in baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: aunt sharon's yogurt chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in baking pan.
Mix mayonnaise and yogurt together.
Spread mixture over chicken; cover pan with foil.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Grind first 4 ingredients together.
Sprinkle with salt; let stand overnight.
Next day, drain and rinse.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over mixture, heat to a boil.
Boil 5 to 10 minutes.
Pack into clean, sterilized jars and seal while hot.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate. This is better if it is allowed to stand a couple of days before using.

title: rice salmon loaf
directions: Select standing aged prime rib roast (any size).
Stand meat at room temperature 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Rub meat with salt, sprinkle with pepper.
Place fat side up in shallow roast pan.
Do not cover.
Do not add water.
Put roast in oven and cook one hour.
Turn off heat, but do not open oven door at any time until ready to serve.
Regardless of length of time meat is in oven, 30 or 40 minutes before serving, turn oven on again; reset temperature to 375°.
Cook meat for those remaining 30 or 40 minutes.
Now open oven door, remove roast to serving platter.
The meat will be very brown and crisp on the outside.
Carve thin slices; it will be pink and juicy and medium rare.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix in baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: hamburger cabbage casserole
directions: Heat meat through.
Do not brown with onion.
Spread cabbage (half) in a 2-quart casserole with mixture, then with remaining cabbage.
Pour soup over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix ingredients and press in bottom of 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Let cool completely.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pineapple and marshmallows and let stand 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Mix Knox gelatine with 1/2 cup of water to dissolve and let stand 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add bananas, cherries and coconut with pineapple and gelatin.
Fold in whipping cream.

title: mazeta
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and pepper in skillet.
Drain off grease.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Add to beef.
Add soups and cheese.
Simmer until cheese melts, about 20 minutes.

title: dole honey-mustard chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper to taste.
Rub with garlic powder; brown in hot oil. Combine 2 tablespoons pineapple juice with cornstarch.
Combine honey and mustard.
Stir in skillet with remaining sauce.
Spoon sauce over chicken; cover and simmer 15 minutes. Add pineapple and serve over rice.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix well the graham cracker crumbs and 1 cube melted margarine.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan to form crust.

title: sausage bean bake
directions: Cook meat in skillet, breaking it up with a fork as it cooks. Saute onion with it.
In a pan mix beans, catsup, prepared mustard and poultry seasoning.
Add sausage and onion; drain grease.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package.
With spoon make hollow groove around edge of casserole. Spoon corn muffin batter into grooves.
Bake 35 or 40 minutes at 400° and 10 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Prepare cake.
Let cool and cut layers in half.
Mix Cool Whip, cream cheese, sugar and powdered sugar.
Cover layers with blueberries and Cool Whip mixture.

title: pork chop-potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Place potatoes in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased baking dish.
Season with spices to taste.
Separate onions and place over potatoes.
Pour chicken bouillon into corner of dish so that it covers the bottom thoroughly.
Place seasoned to taste pork chops over the top.
Cover and bake 30 minutes. Uncover; turn pork chops and bake additional 30 minutes or until chops are done and potatoes are tender.
(Pork chops may be rolled in flour prior to placing over potatoes.)

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Refrigerate for a few hours or freeze a short time.

title: sausage roll
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add milk and mix well.
Knead on lightly floured board until dough can be handled easily.
Divide dough in half and roll one-half inch thick. Divide sausage in half and spread dough.
Roll in jelly fashion. Chill.
Slice and bake at 350° until brown and meat is done.

title: sweet potato salad
directions: Cook sweet potatoes with the peeling on, then peel, cool and cut in 3/4-inch chunks, about 5 1/2 cups.
Place mayonnaise, yogurt, curry powder and salt in a large bowl and whisk to blend. Add potatoes and remaining ingredients.
Toss gently to mix and coat.
Cover and chill at least 1 hour or up to 3 days for flavors to develop.

title: blanc mange
directions: Boil milk.
Moisten the cornstarch with a little cold milk, then add to the boiling milk and stir until it thickens.
Add the sugar and salt.
Remove from heat and pour into custard cups. Refrigerate to harden.
Serve with cream sauce.
Serves 5.

title: hershey pie
directions: Melt bars in microwave or double boiler. Let cool. Add room temperature cool whip and mix. Put in cooled baked pie shell.

title: crusty coconut pie
directions: Pour
milk
over
coconut; set aside.
Cream butter and sugar. Add
eggs;
beat well.
Add milk, coconut and vanilla. Blend well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set and golden brown.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Stir vinegar into milk and set aside. Stir all dry ingredients into flour.
Cut in shortening with fork or pastry cutter until quite fine or looks like cornmeal.
Make a hole in center and pour milk into flour.
Fold flour into it gently.
If too dry,
add small amount of milk; gently stir and fold until all flour is moistened.
Scrape from sides of bowl and form into a rounded mass that can turn out onto a thickly floured board.
Very gently, turn and coat with flour; gently push and knead 6 to 8 times.
Gently pat into 1-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Place 1/2-inch apart on cookie sheet.
Re-roll scraps and pat out again to finish cutting.
Bake 10 minutes on rack in middle of oven or 1 notch above.

title: mock red raspberry jam
directions: Grind or
blend
tomatoes.
Mix
with sugar and boil 15 minutes. Remove from heat and add jello.
Mix well;
put in containers.
Seal or freeze.

title: old fashion tea cakes(cookies)
directions: Mix Crisco, sugar and eggs together well.
Add flour and baking powder.
Roll dough on lightly floured cutting board to about 1/4-inch thick.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Sprinkle with sugar before baking.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 8 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: baked corn casserole
directions: Cook rice according to instructions.
Melt butter in a large bowl.
Mix all ingredients together except for cheese.

title: best coconut cake i ever ate
directions: Cook until mixture thickens, then add coconut. Cool and spread between layers.

title: roast chicken
directions: Fry onions in a little oil to a pale golden color and drain and cool.
Crush with back of spoon and set aside.
Soak breadcrumbs in tomato juice.
Fry potatoes a golden color.

title: potatoes
directions: Thaw potatoes overnight and go through to check for bad pieces.
Once potatoes are defrosted, mix them with all ingredients in a big pan or bowl.
Place in a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt 1/4 cup butter; mix with bread crumbs and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Excellent for buffet or to serve at a cookout.
Serves 16.

title: cabbage pineapple slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, pineapple tidbits, apple, celery and raisins.
Toss with low calorie mayonnaise until well coated. Serve on lettuce lined bowl.
Garnish with apple.

title: duke bran muffins(with fruit of your choice)
directions: These muffins are best if done by hand (sans electric beaters).

title: ike and mamie fudge
directions: Place the chocolate ingredients (broken into small pieces) and the Marshmallow Creme into a large mixing bowl and set aside. Cook the sugar, Pet milk and margarine for 6 minutes after it comes to a boil (stirring constantly).
Remove from heat and pour over chocolate.
Beat until ingredients are melted and add nuts. Beat until stiff enough to pour in large buttered dish.

title: dora's brownies
directions: Grease pan.
Sift flour 3 times.
Combine melted butter and cocoa; add sugar.
Gradually add eggs, beating thoroughly.
Add cocoa and butter.
Add flour and mix well.
Add nuts and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan.

title: mama's lasagna
directions: Brown meat adding spices (garlic powder and Italian seasoning).
Drain and cool.
Boil noodles until tender.
Drain and cool.
In bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, empty can of tomato sauce.
Layer a row of noodles, cover lightly with spaghetti sauce.
Add layer of meat.
In small bowl, mix cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese (save 1 cup of Mozzarella cheese for top). Layer cheese mixture on top of meat, then add layer of noodles, sauce, meat, cheese, etc.
Alternate layers until finished with layer of noodles.
(Should be 4 layers approximately.)
Top with what's left of sauce (if needed, add tomato sauce).
Top with layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until heated through.

title: spinach broccoli casserole
directions: Cook
spinach and broccoli until just tender-crisp;
do not overcook.
Drain
well
by
squeezing out water.
Combine sour cream
and
soup
mix and stir into spinach and broccoli. Place in casserole dish.
Bake, covered, in preheated oven at 350° for
30 minutes
or
until
bubbly.
Top with cheese and bread
crumbs; drizzle
butter over top.
Place under broiler until bubbly and browned.
Can be made a day ahead and kept in refrigerator.

title: zucchini nibblers
directions: Lightly mix all ingredients together and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in 350° oven for about 25 minutes or until top is golden.
Cut in squares and eat hot or cold.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into small balls.
Press flat with fork and bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes, until golden color.
Cookies will be crunchy.

title: crock-pot spaghetti and meat balls(servings:  6)
directions: Cook onion and garlic in hot oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered for 30 minutes.
Remove bay leaf. Make meat balls fairly large and drop into sauce.

title: premier white brownies by nestle
directions: Melt Nestle Premier white baking bars.
Microwave Full power for 2 minutes, stirring twice.
Be careful, it's easy to burn! Stir until smooth; set aside.
In small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt; set aside.
In large bowl, combine sugar, eggs and almond extract; mix well.
Blend in melted butter and baking bars.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan.
Sprinkle almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: "dom econ" cake
directions: Pour water over chocolate and butter; stir until melted.
Add sugar, flour and soda which has been sifted.
Add milk.
Mix well.
Break whole egg in and beat well.
Bake at 350° in 2 layers and ice with any white frosting (boiled frosting is best).

title: breakfast granola
directions: Spread rolled oats on a 15 x 10-inch baking pan.
Toast at 350° for 5 minutes.
Stir; toast 5 more minutes.
Meanwhile, combine honey or molasses and oil in saucepan.
Heat, but do not boil.
Stir in vanilla.
Remove oats from oven; toss with nuts, bran and coconut.
Pour hot honey mixture over oat mixture.
Toss well.
Return to oven and bake 20 to 25 minutes, stirring 3 times while baking.
Remove from oven.
Add raisins and dates; stir well.
Cool.
Store in airtight container.
Yield:
8 cups.

title: long john silver's batter
directions: Mix and let stand 5 minutes.
Dip and fry fish, okra, squash.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt the butter and chocolate together over low heat.
Stir in the sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Add the vanilla and the nuts.
In another bowl, sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir this into the chocolate mixture. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: oven-orange chicken
directions: Place chicken in 2 -quart baking dish.	Sprinkle green pepper and onion on top.
Combine remaining ingredients except oranges and mix until smooth.
Cover chicken with mixture and bake covered for 1 hour at 350 degrees.	Place orange slices on last.
Serves 4.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Saute onions, pepper, celery, garlic and green onions until tender.
Add crawfish and seasonings and cook for 15 minutes. Stir in the soup and tomato sauce and cook 15 minutes more.
Serve with rice.

title: buttery biscuit rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in large saucepan.
Add sour cream and flour; mix.
Drop batter into miniature ungreased muffin tins.
