Fill to top.
Bake 25 minutes.
Makes 24 small biscuits rolls.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Add 1-quart boiling water to Kool-Aid and sugar.
Dissolve. Add other quart of water to juice and strawberries. Mix well and freeze.

title: vanilla pudding and cherry parfait
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package.
Cool and then fold in oranges.
Combine pie filling and orange rind and layer with pudding in individual dessert dishes, beginning and ending with pudding.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: beef and cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage coarsely; cut out tough ribs.
Cook in oil in 5-quart Dutch oven until tender; stir occasionally.
Brown meat and onion in large frypan.
Add spaghetti sauce, water and raw rice; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 20 minutes. In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, spoon in 1/2 cup of meat sauce.
Top with half of cabbage, half of meat sauce and half of cheese. Repeat with remaining cabbage, meat sauce and cheese.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Makes 8 servings.

title: grandma esther's and sue's hash brown casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place frozen potatoes in single layer.
Mix together soup, Cheddar cheese, onion and sour cream. Pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle parsley and Parmesan cheese. Microwave on Medium-high 22 minutes, turn 3 times.

title: chicken pie
directions: Make white sauce using broth according to directions on cornstarch box.
Separate biscuit layers.
Put a layer of biscuits, layer of chicken and layer of white sauce.
Repeat until all is gone.
Bake at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: one hour yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine milk, sugar, oil and salt. Sift flour and soda into large bowl.
Mix yeast and milk; add to flour.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Roll out, cut and place in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Turn over to butter top.
Let rise 30 minutes. Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: microwave mini pizza
directions: Spread pizza sauce on english muffin halves.
Add cheese and toppings.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 minutes or bake at 350 degrees for 3 to 5 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well. Saute onion in margarine until tender. Add soup, milk and cheese. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until cheese melts. Stir in rice and broccoli. Pour into a 2-quart greased casserole; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a mixing bowl, beat the cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream and butter on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour half into greased 8-inch square baking dish. Top with apples.

title: farmer brown's special
directions: Equal amounts of the ingredients.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all together; chill 8 hours before using.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In bowl, combine oil, sugar and brown sugar.
Beat until sugar dissolves or is smooth. Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Bake in a 350° oven.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend cream cheese, vanilla, sugar, pudding and Cool Whip into a medium-size bowl.
Blend until smooth.
Pour mixture over 1/2 package crushed Oreo cookies in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Crush remaining cookies and spread on top of other ingredients. Place in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: pretzel wands
directions: Melt chocolate chips in microwave or on stove in double boiler. Dip pretzel rods one by one, half into chocolate chip mixture and then roll in sugars or cereal mixture.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine spinach, onions and eggs.
Add desired amount of bacon bits and dressing 15 minutes before serving.

title: dressing
directions: Blend all together and chill before serving.

title: mexican pasta salad
directions: Sprinkle chicken with cumin and chili powder.
Heat oil in a medium skillet; add chicken and cook over medium heat 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Add water and bouillon granules; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken from broth, reserving broth in skillet.
Cover and chill chicken.

title: cherry tomato salsa
directions: In food processor, chop
parsley, onion and hot pepper. Add tomatoes, olive oil,
vinegar and lemon pepper; chop until tomatoes are finely
chopped.
Add seasonings and refrigerate. Serve with corn chips.

title: summer tea
directions: Remove tea bags; pour tea into gallon container.
Add juice, lemonade, sugar and water to 1 gallon; stir well.
Serve over ice for refreshing thirst quencher.

title: mushroom chicken
directions: Bake chicken breasts at 350° for 15 minutes on each side. After chicken is cooked, add soup in pan with chicken.
Add 2 cans water in pan with chicken and soup, depending on how thick you want gravy.
Stir.
Put pan back in oven long enough to heat gravy, about 10 minutes.
Best served with rice.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken wings
directions: Brown chicken in shortening.
Remove chicken and drain drippings from pan.
Add all ingredients for sauce and bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Put chicken back into pan with sauce; simmer 15 minutes covered and 15 minutes uncovered.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla and beat until thick and lemon colored.
Stir in zucchini, flour, cinnamon, baking powder, soda and salt.
Fold in nuts, raisins and pineapple.
Pour into two greased and floured pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chipped beef ball
directions: Mix together all ingredients, including half of the chipped beef.
Form into a ball.
Roll ball in remaining chipped beef and refrigerate until ready to use.

title: butterflake rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Cream sugar and shortening. Add 1 cup water, eggs and yeast.
Stir in flour and salt.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: mild peppers and wieners
directions: Cut peppers and wieners in about 1-inch pieces.
Combine tomato juice, water, vinegar, sugar and salt.
Let come to a boil. Add peppers and wieners.
Let come to boil.
Pack while hot into sterilized jars and seal.

title: mom's bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Put bread crumbs in 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.
Blend with all the other ingredients.
Place the baking dish in a pan or another larger baking dish containing 1 inch of hot water.
Carefully place in pre-heated oven and bake for 40-45 minutes, until a silver knife inserted 1 inch from edge comes out clean.
Serve warm or cold, with or without vanilla sauce. Serves:

title: pretzel salad
directions: *Strawberry jello can be used with frozen strawberries.
May substitute with canned fruit, well drained.

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine cake mix, 8 ounces of evaporated milk and softened butter.
Spread half of mixture in greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
(Mixture will be thick; will be easier to spread with a wet spatula.)
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small mixing bowl, combine 3/4 cup butter, flour, oatmeal, brown sugar and baking soda.
Mix well.

title: german meat balls
directions: Combine ground chuck, salt, pepper, poultry seasoning, bread crumbs, milk, chopped parsley and egg.
Mix lightly and shape into 24 meat balls.
Brown slowly in hot fat and turn frequently to keep them round.
Drain fat.

title: mom's onion pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine onions, 4 cups cheese, flour, baking powder, salt, pepper and butter.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole.
Top with remaining 1 cup cheese and crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes.
Especially good with grilled meats.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: boiled stone crab
directions: In a large kettle, bring water to a boil. Add mustard and salt; blend. Drop in claws; cover and boil 20 minutes.
Remove claws; break them open and serve with butter to which a few drops of Key Lime juice has been added.

title: mango rum french toast
directions: Ingredient amounts according to serving portions desired. With a fork, mix and beat eggs as for regular French toast, adding desired amount of Mango Rum.
Add rum to Maple syrup and warm. Slice and soak bananas in Mango Rum.
Spray a nonstick skillet with cooking spray.
Dip bread slices in egg mixture and cook over medium heat long enough to brown evenly on both sides of bread. Arrange sliced bananas over slices of bread and serve with warm rum syrup.

title: brenda's easy lasagna
directions: Brown the meat with 1/2 cup chopped onion.
Drain and stir in mushrooms.
After cooking them a bit, stir in the spaghetti sauce. While this simmers, cook the lasagna noodles.

title: barbecued little doggies by inez
directions: Place barbecue sauce and jelly in a crock-pot, stir until well mixed.
Add mustard, soy sauce and Worcestershire sauce, if desired.
Cut wieners into small pieces and place in sauce mixture.
Simmer until little doggies have barbecue taste.

title: microwave hamburger stroganoff
directions: Place ground beef and onion in a 2-quart glass baking.
Cover with waxed paper.
Cook in microwave oven 5 minutes at High or until meat is no longer pink.
Stir occasionally.
Drain off excess fat.
Add salt, pepper and soup.
Mix well.
Cook covered in microwave oven 6 to 8 minutes at High or until thoroughly heated. Stir occasionally.
Stir in sour cream.
Cover and allow to stand 2 minutes.
Yields about 4 servings.
Serve on noodles, potatoes or rice.

title: hot cider punch(in honor of roy amos)
directions: Mix and simmer all day in a crock-pot.
Tastes great and gives great aroma to the house.
Besides serving hot, one may want to try it cooled at room temperature and then poured over ice cubes, in one's glass.
If served hot, serve from mugs or punch cups.

title: cajun corn bake
directions: Drain whole kernel corn; save juice.
Add liquid to cornbread mix.
Add egg, sour cream and margarine; mix well.
Add corn and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Grease a 9 x 11-inch pan. Pour ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
You may add Tabasco sauce to mixture before baking if you like it spicy.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook water, sugar, and corn starch until clear, then add box of jello.
Fill pie shell with fresh strawberries.
Pour cooked mixture over top.
Place in refrigerator for approximately two hours.
Top with Cool Whip and ENJOY!

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine cake mix and pudding mix.
Add Wesson oil, then eggs, one at a time.
Add 7-Up and mix well.
Bake in three pans for 40 minutes at 325° or until done.

title: chocolate vanilla parfait
directions: Pour milk into a 4-cup measuring bowl.
Empty package of vanilla pudding into milk.
Beat with eggbeater until it begins to thicken.
Stop; scrape sides of bowl with spatula.
Beat a few seconds more.
Spoon small amount of pudding into each parfait glass.
Slowly add a thin layer of chocolate syrup.
Add more pudding and more syrup until almost full, ending with syrup.
Makes 4 servings.

title: easy egg custard(makes its own crust)
directions: Mix all together.
Flavor with 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour in 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: candied carrots
directions: Peel and cut carrots into sticks.
Cook until tender-crisp; drain.
Melt margarine in frying pan.
Add orange peel, brown sugar and carrots.
Cook and toss until sugar is melted and carrots are glazed.

title: chicken rotel casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Save broth.
Cook spaghetti in broth; drain.
Saute onion and bell pepper; add all ingredients and pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Prepare potatoes.
Melt butter in saucepan and blend in flour. Cook just until bubbly.
Stir in milk, salt and pepper to taste. Continue cooking.
Add cheese.
Cook and stir until cheese melts. Layer potatoes and cheese sauce, ending with cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: pineapple fruit dip
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg together.
Add juice drained from 1 can of chunk pineapple.
Bring to a boil and cook until it thickens.
Cool and use for dipping pineapple chunks, bananas, pears and other fresh fruit.

title: chocolate cream pie
directions: In a saucepan, mix together sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Blend milk and egg yolks.
Gradually stir into sugar mixture.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Let boil and stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; blend in chocolate and vanilla mixture.
Pour in baked 9-inch pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown slightly.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In sheet cake pan (11 1/2 x 17 1/2-inch), fit crescent rolls on bottom and sides of pan.
Cook sausage and drain.
Layer cooked sausage and hash brown potatoes over sausage.
Put cheese over potatoes.
Pour egg mixture over all.
Bake 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat in oil with onion, garlic and salt.
Add tomatoes and spices.
Cook about 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Run hot water over vegetables; drain.
Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish.
More cheese can be put on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable cheese dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and coffee.
Mix until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Blend well and chill.
Serve with raw vegetables, if desired.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: ground beef with potatoes
directions: Spray a heavy pan and cook meat first.
Drain.
Add potatoes, margarine, celery and onions.
Salt and pepper.
Cover and cook on low heat until vegetables are soft.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients until moistened.
Stir vigorously one minute.
Pour batter into 9 x 13-inch or Bundt cake pan.
Bake about 40 to 45 minutes until top springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cool.
Very moist; does not need frosting, but it can be dusted with powdered sugar or drizzled with chocolate syrup. Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Sprinkle topping on top.

title: salami wedges
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread on 9 slices salami.
Stack spread slices and top with a plain slice of salami.
Cover and chill.

title: chocolate spritz cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add or delete flour for desired consistency.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
May be used as roll out cookies or use in cookie press.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain well.
(Not necessary if it's "diet lean" hamburger.)
Combine all ingredients in a large pot. Simmer, covered, at least 2 hours, or all day.
Serves 10.

title: grandpa ward's cake mix cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Mix ingredients well.
Spoon and roll into 1-inch circles.
Roll circles in powdered sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until tops are slightly brown.
Remove and place onto cooling rack.
Cookies will be very tender.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix; pour into unbaked shell.
Bake until firm at 350° or cook and then pour into baked shell.

title: fruit and nut morning buns
directions: In large bowl, combine hot roll mix, yeast packet, oats, flour, brown sugar, fruit and nuts.
Mix well.
Add cream cheese, 2 tablespoons margarine, orange peel and egg.
Mix well, until dough pulls away from sides of bowl.
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and knead 5 minutes.
Add additional flour if dough is sticky.
Shape dough into ball.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Let rise in warm place for 20 minutes.

title: mrs. lillie thompson's steamed fig pudding
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar slowly, beating well.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add figs or dates.
Pour into greased pan and steam 2 hours.
Serve with sauce.

title: apple celery salad with banana dressing
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Grind walnuts and then add bananas, honey and lemon juice.
Combine and serve immediately.

title: baked eggs
directions: Place cheese in 9 x 9-inch greased pan or baking dish.
Pour melted oleo on top.
Mix next 4 ingredients.
Pour 1/2 of mixture on cheese and oleo.
Pour on eggs.
Pour on rest of liquid. Optional:
Chopped sausage links, pepper, onion, etc.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Cook until boils and forms a small ball in a cup of cold water.
Add 2 cups of oats and 1/2 cup peanut butter to mixture.
Stir well and spoon into mixture on wax paper.

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: In a 2 quart casserole dish combine macaroni, flour, onion, salt, and Tabasco Sauce.
Stir in milk and water; dot with margarine.
Cook covered on HIGH for 10 to 12 minutes or until macaroni is just about tender.
Stir every 4 minutes.
Remove from microwave; stir in cheese.
LET STAND 3 to 5 MINUTES to finish cooking.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mash cream cheese on glass platter.
Pour cocktail sauce over cream cheese. Sprinkle shrimp over sauce. Sprinkle cheese over shrimp.
Mix veggies together and spread over top of cheese. Decorate with paprika.
Spread on crackers.

title: upside-down pineapple cake
directions: Use a 10-inch skillet or a 2-quart, 11 x 7 x 1-inch pan.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Combine the chocolate morsels, condensed milk and butter in a double boiler. Cook over boiling water until blended, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Stir in pecans and marshmallows into the chocolate mixture. Put
in a 9x13- inch dish lined with waxed paper. Chill, covered, for 2 hours or until set. Cut into 36 squares. Store, at room temperature.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Put small amount of flour, salt and pepper into plastic bag. Add beef and shake well to coat on all surfaces.
Brown in hot oil in frying pan.
Stir to sear all sides.
Remove from oil.
(Can put onto paper towel and pat gently to remove oil.)
Put into large ovenproof casserole. Put into preheated 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Stir once or twice.
Add carrots and potatoes.
Combine soup mix, water, tomato paste and brown sugar.
Pour liquid over all.
Reduce heat to 350°.
Cover; cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Add green beans for last 15 minutes if desired.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except egg whites and mix well. Stiffly beat and then fold in egg whites.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cake cool.
Makes 3 (8-inch) layers.

title: old south pralines
directions: Butter sides of heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Place sugars, cream and salt in saucepan.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved.
Turn heat to medium and cook until mixture boils.
Reduce heat and continue cooking to 234° on a candy thermometer.
Remove from heat.
Add butter and vanilla; do not stir.
Cool 5 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Beat until candy loses gloss and becomes thick (about 300 strokes or 2 minutes).
Quickly spoon candy mixture, by teaspoonfuls, onto buttered cookie sheets. If mixture gets too thick to drop from spoon, add hot water, a teaspoonful at a time.
Yield:
36 pieces.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Drain liquid from corn and peas (about 1 1/2 cups).
Add milk to make 1 quart liquid.
In a large casserole, alternate layers of vegetables and crackers.
Add seasonings and liquid.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Cook and drain sauerkraut.
Layer all ingredients in order in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: poor man's lobster(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except butter and lemon juice in a 2-quart microproof bowl.
Cook on High (max power), 12 to 14 minutes, or until fish flakes easily and is opaque, stirring once during cooking time.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Combine butter and lemon juice in a 2 cup glass measure.
Cook on High 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes.
Remove cod from cooking broth with slotted spoon; place on a serving platter.
Serve with lemon butter for dipping. Serves 4.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: In a shallow bowl mix together the cornmeal, flour and sugar. Dredge both sides of the tomatoes in the mixture.
Press the slices firmly into the meal so it will make a good coating. Put enough oil or shortening in an iron skillet to come to a depth of about 1/4 inch, and heat over medium high heat.

title: sausage beef stew
directions: Cook sausage (in bite-size pieces) and beef chuck in 1-inch pieces in 2 tablespoons melted shortening.
Place in a casserole. Cook onion in fat until transparent.
Add peppers and cook 1 minute longer.
Add remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until beef and potatoes are tender.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake for 30 minutes at 300°.

title: nut drops
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together. Set aside. Cream sugar and shortening. Stir in eggs. Blend in flour mixture and add nuts. Drop on lightly greased sheet and bake in oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add nuts.
Chill dough.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 1/2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until set.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll in sugar again.
Bake at 375°.
Do not brown.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Scald milk.
Add sugar, butter and salt to milk and cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, vanilla, almond extract and 3 cups flour.
Beat until a smooth soft dough forms.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Remove to a floured countertop and knead until dough is smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl and lightly grease top of dough.
Cover with plastic wrap and let rise until doubled in bulk.

title: crescent chicken squares
directions: Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons butter until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk and onion.
Separate crescent roll dough into four rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Spread 1/2 cup of chicken mixture onto each piece of dough.
Pull dough over chicken to form a roll.
Seal ends and edges.
Brush tops with reserved butter.
Dip rolls in bread crumbs.

title: pina colada punch
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Whir 2 cups pineapple juice with cream of coconut in blender.
Combine pureed mixture with remaining pineapple juice, soda, juice of 1 lime, rum (if desired) and ice. Garnish with 1 sliced lime and mint.
Makes 15 servings.

title: sombrero chocolate cake
directions: Beat all ingredients for 4 minutes.
Pour batter into well-greased Bundt or tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Turn out on rack to cool. Dust with powdered sugar or glaze.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and mix with rice, soup, cheese and onion.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pickled green beans
directions: In 8-quart pot, heat 5 quarts salted water to boiling over high heat.
Add beans and cook 5 to 7 minutes.
Beans should still be crisp.
Drain beans in larger colander; rinse under cold running water.
In 2-quart pot, heat sugar, garlic, dill, mustard, 1/2 cup vinegar, 2 teaspoons salt and 1/2 cup water to boiling. Cook for 1 minute, stirring.
Remove from heat; add remaining vinegar and 1 1/2 cup cold water.
Stir.
Place beans in 2-gallon Ziploc or large bowl with lid.
Pour vinegar mixture over beans. Put in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Can keep for up to 5 days.
In a Ziploc, turn occasionally.
If in bowl, stir occasionally. Great snack.
Good as pickles!

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix well with cornmeal to the consistency of mush.
Boil slowly for 15 or 20 minutes, then bake in oven for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into an oblong pan, greased and floured.
Batter will be thin.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: green bean parmesan salad
directions: Steam or boil the string beans until cooked.
Mix with remaining ingredients and serve.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: hermits
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat margarine or butter with an electric mixer on medium to high speed for 30 seconds.
Add about half of the flour, the brown sugar, egg, milk, vanilla, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Beat until thoroughly combined.
Beat in remaining flour.
Stir in raisins and nuts.

title: korean salad and dressing
directions: Combine spinach, bean sprouts, water chestnuts, eggs and bacon bits in salad bowl.
Add dressing (recipe follows); toss to mix well.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 servings.

title: nutty oatmeal cookies
directions: Set oven at 350°.
Sift together first four ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Arrange by teaspoonfuls on buttered cookie sheets.
Bake until the edges are brown (about 12 minutes). Makes 75.
Increase oatmeal to 2 cups and flour to 1 3/4 cups for thicker cookies.

title: lemon - lime cake
directions: Mix jello with 3/4 c hot water and 1/2 c cold water. Bake cake as directed on box.
Poke holes in cake while warm - pour jello over cake.

title: apple waffle
directions: Sift dry ingredients; add egg yolks and milk and beat.
Stir in shortening; beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold apples and egg whites in batter.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together. Place in glass baking dish. Melt butter and mix with crackers. Pour over mixture. Bake 45 minutes at 350°. Great with Fritos or chips or crackers.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
With small spoon (such as a baby spoon) scrape out insides of mushrooms and place them and stems in mixing bowl.
Chop onion finely and saute in butter.
Add mushroom stems and scrapings.
Continue cooking and add garlic powder to taste.

Add stuffing, finely crushed and Parmesan cheese. If Pepperidge Farm stuffing is used, no extra spices are required. If other bread crumbs/stuffing is used, oregano and other Italian spices must be used according to taste.
Fill mushrooms with mixture and bake in 350° oven about 8 minutes.
Add grated Cheddar or Swiss or Monterey Jack cheese to tops of mushrooms and heat again to melt.
Mushrooms may be reheated several times.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Remove skin from sausage and mix with ground beef. Add onions, grated Parmesan cheese, egg, spices and garlic. Soak bread in milk. Squeeze dry and grate. Add to meat mixture. Roll into 2 ounce balls. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 12 meatballs.

title: fresh green bean casserole(german)
directions: Clean and cut fresh green beans in 1-inch lengths.
Scrub new potatoes (do not peel).
Put beans and potatoes in large pan; add water and cook until tender.
Do not drain.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble over beans.
Saute onion in bacon drippings, then add to beans and potatoes.
Add 1/2 cup milk.
Mix and heat up all ingredients.
Thicken to gravy consistency and serve.
Season to taste.

title: hot rum cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Mix cake mix, oil, pudding, rum and water.
Add eggs and nuts and mix well.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: next morning pull apart coffee cake
directions: Mix last three ingredients and melt together in microwave. Generously grease Bundt pan.
Place frozen rolls on bottom. Sprinkle with pecans.
Add more rolls.
Sprinkle with more pecans. Pour box of pudding over top.
Add microwave mixture over top. Cover with plastic wrap and set on counter overnight.
Next morning, bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugars thoroughly.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Yields 3 dozen.

title: angel food bars
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, onion and butter and cook until tender.
Drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup of cheese to sprinkle over the top.

title: egg rolls
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, oil and yeast together.
Add warm water. Combine mixture with flour and put in 1/2 teaspoon of oil and let rise.

title: cocktail sauce
directions: Mix chili sauce, juice salt, Tabasco sauce and horseradish. Chill before serving.

title: glazed peanuts
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients; stir over medium heat until all liquid evaporates.
Pour onto cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir and sprinkle with salt.
Return to oven for 15 minutes.
Stir again, then bake 10 minutes longer.
Let cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add milk and egg.
Mix well.
Drop into boiling broth and cook, covered.
Do not remove lid for 5 minutes.

title: strawberry balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form into balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: salt rising bread(alabama tech extension service)
directions: Scald milk and stir in enough cornmeal to make a batter.
Add salt.
(Do this about 3 p.m. in winter and 8 p.m. in summer.)
At 5 or 6 a.m., add 1/2 cup tepid water and enough flour to make a stiff batter.
Set in a vessel of warm water and keep at an even temperature.
Watch carefully and if water forms on top, as it sometimes does, add 1 tablespoon flour.
Let rise and add 4 cups flour, 2 tablespoons lard, 1/2 teaspoon salt and 1 tablespoon sugar.
A little warm water may be added, if necessary, to make a soft dough.
Knead well and put in greased pans to rise.
This makes 2 small loaves.
Grease the top when it rises well and bake in a moderate oven at 375°.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Boil water and sugar for 2 minutes.
Dissolve jello in syrup; add lemon and orange juice and milk and freeze.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for five minutes.
Add white sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice.
Combine all dry ingredients and add to this mixture. Mix well and spread batter into greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Turn onto towels and sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Roll up, then combine cream cheese, powdered sugar, butter and vanilla (nuts optional) and spread on roll. Roll back up and refrigerate.
Slice.

title: toll house pie
directions: Mix flour with sugar.
Add beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Add butter, melted and cooled.
Fold in pecans and chips.
Pour into uncooked crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato loaf cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and water; beat at medium speed just until blended.
Combine the next 5 ingredients; add to egg mixture, mixing just until moistened.
Stir in sweet potatoes, pecans and raisins.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple wood julep
directions: Mix juices together and chill. Serves 6.

title: shayh's stuffed shrimp
directions: "Put the noodles in the pot.
Put the meat sauce on to cook. Then you put it on the plate and let it cool for an hour and one-half and then you eat it."

title: toffee bars
directions: Separate graham crackers into individual pieces on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over graham crackers.
In saucepan combine sugar, margarine and butter.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Pour over graham crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 48 bars.

title: pork tenderloin in white wine sauce
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper; coat tenderloin with flour mixture. Melt butter; cook tenderloin 4 minutes on each side on medium heat. Add onions; cook 2 to 4 minutes.
Add rosemary; cook 1 minute.
Add mushrooms; cook 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth and wine; cook about 10 minutes longer.
Serves 8. Total cooking time approximately 22 minutes.

title: frozen oreo cookie sundae(bill meyer's favorite!)
directions: Crumble most of the Oreos into a layer on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Save a few to sprinkle on top.)
Layer softened ice cream on top of crushed Oreos.
Put in freezer for a while to let ice cream get hard.
Heat hot fudge sauce in jar in microwave (be sure to take lid off) for a minute or so until it pours easily. Pour over ice cream layer.
Spread Cool Whip over hot fudge. Sprinkle remaining Oreos on top.
Freeze.
Take out of freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: caramelized brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package. Pour batter into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan. Melt butter in small pan. Add pecans and sugar and cook over medium heat, stirring frequently or until sugar dissolves. Drizzle caramel mixture over brownie batter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Mix hot, drained noodles with margarine and put in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Layer with sauerkraut, then corned beef. Mix ketchup and salad dressing together and spread over beef.
Top with tomatoes and then shredded cheese.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar.
Beat eggs well and gradually add to butter mixture.
Sift spices and flour together.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk and add to flour mixture.
Gradually add flour mixture to butter and sugar mixture and mix well.
Mix in raisins, nuts and jam.
Bake at 350° until fork comes clean.

title: roast beef
directions: Place roast on large sheet of heavy-duty aluminum foil in pan. Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over roast.
Spread mushroom soup over all.
Bake at 300° for 4 hours.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Line pie pan with pastry.
Put in pecans in a layer.
Add mixture. Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes.
Nuts will rise to the top to form a crusted pie.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: In 4-quart saucepan or Dutch oven, brown ground beef with onions, carrots and celery.
Drain well.
Add remaining ingredients; stir to combine.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 25 to 35 minutes or until vegetables and rice are tender.
Remove bay leaf.

title: kay's rice pilaf dish
directions: Follow directions on box.
Use 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Bake in medium heat oven.

title: dinner in a dish
directions: Put Crisco in skillet and lightly fry peppers and onion for 3 minutes.
Add meat and blend very well. Add seasonings. Remove from fire. Stir in eggs and mix well.
Put 1 cup corn in baking dish, then half the meat mixture,
a layer of tomatoes, then another layer of corn, meat and tomatoes. Cover with bread crumbs. Cover with bits of butter.
Bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: b~b~q sauce
directions: Mix and boil for 5 minutes.
Store in a glass jar.
Sauce will keep for 3 months.
Makes 4 cups.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
These cookies may be iced.

title: paella
directions: Have ready a deep, 3-quart microwave-safe casserole.
Put onion, oil and garlic in casserole.
Cover with lid or vented plastic wrap.
Microwave on High 3 to 5 minutes, until onion is crisp and tender.
Stir in broth, turmeric, thyme, then rice. Cover and microwave on High 14 to 16 minutes, stirring twice, until rice is almost tender.
Stir in ham, peas, pimiento and shrimp.

Cover and microwave 2 to 4 minutes longer, until rice is tender and shrimp are almost opaque but still look slightly raw. Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes, until shrimp are completely opaque and cooked through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pizza salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients and set aside.
In another bowl, combine the rest of the ingredients, beginning with the oil and mix well.
Pour over the macaroni mixture.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Top with croutons just before serving.

title: ann's yellow tail "matacumbe"
directions: Saute garlic and shallot in olive oil.
Add wine, lemon juice, capers and fresh basil, stirring constantly, 5 minutes. Add yellow tail and diced tomatoes.
Cook until fish flakes easily with fork.

title: quick and easy ice cream caramel rolls
directions: Cut biscuits in 4 pieces; roll in sugar and cinnamon.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix ice cream, brown sugar, white sugar and margarine together.
Melt mixture and pour over biscuits.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pop corn
directions: Pop 2 quarts of popcorn.
Bring sugar and corn syrup to a rolling boil.
Remove
from heat and add peanut butter and vanilla. Pour over popcorn, stirring to coat.

title: irish brown soda bread
directions: Sift the flours, salt and baking soda together into a large bowl.
Stir in the oats.
Make a well in the center; pour in the buttermilk and stir with a wooden spoon until the mixture comes together to form a soft, moist dough.
If it seems too dry, add a few more tablespoons buttermilk.

Turn the dough out onto a lightly floured surface and form it into a large, rounded disk, about 8-inches in diameter and with a sharp knife, cut a deep cross through the dough, cutting the disk almost into quarters. On a buttered baking sheet, bake the bread in the middle of a preheated 425° oven for 15 minutes, then reduce the oven temperature to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes more, or until the bread is crusty and richly browned.
Let it cool on a rack. Yields 1 large loaf.

title: mom's fresh apple cake
directions: Prepare raw apples and set aside.
Measure oil in large bowl, adding sugar and eggs.
Beat until creamy on low speed of mixer. Sift and measure flour.
Sift again with salt, soda and baking powder.
Add a small amount of flour at a time to the creamed mixture.
Beat well after each addition.
When all is added, fold in pecans and raw apples.
Spread evenly in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped pecans.
Chill until serving.

title: oven baked rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Cover and bake at 350° about 40 minutes or until rice is tender, tossing lightly with a fork several times during last 15 minutes of cooking.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes longer or until liquid is almost all absorbed.
Yields six 3/4 cup servings.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles and brown the beef.
Then mix all ingredients together well.
Cover with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt oleo in Dutch oven.
Add flour and brown to make a dark brown roux.
Add onions, celery, bell pepper and green onions. Let simmer for about 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Add Ro-Tel, mushroom soup and milk and simmer.
Add shrimp and simmer.
Liquids may vary according to need.
Also a jar of sliced mushrooms can be added or cream of celery soup may be used. According to likes and imagination.

title: beef stroganoff casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, garlic, onion, salt and pepper.
Add mushroom soup; simmer 5 minutes.
Add cream of celery soup and liquid; simmer 10 minutes.
Cook the noodles.
Prior to serving, add 1 cup of sour cream to mixture.
Pour over noodles and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mom's melon balls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes. Cool.
Pour over melon balls.
Chill.

title: sheepherder's breakfast
directions: Thaw hash browns.
In a large skillet, cook bacon and onion until bacon is crisp.
Drain all but 1/2 cup drippings.
Add hash browns and mix well.
Cook over medium heat for 10 minutes, turning when brown.
Make 8 or 10 evenly spaced wells in hash browns. Break an egg in each well.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and cheese. Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until eggs are set. Wonderful for weekend guests.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Layer ingredients in greased casserole dish in order listed, pouring undiluted soup over all.
Cover with lid or foil and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: cloud's hot dill pickles
directions: You will need quart canning jars.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Wash broccoli.
Cut into bite size pieces. Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Marinate broccoli for 6 to 8 hours.

title: chocolate drop cookies(no bake)
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, cocoa and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat. Stir in oats, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop on waxed paper.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: arthritis
directions: Grind rind and put in 1-quart of hot water; strain when cool into
juice.
Add
Epsom Salts, cream of tartar and cold water. Shake
well.
Take	2
to
3 tablespoons in warm water before breakfast.	Never
tried it, found it in an old recipe book.

title: cooked cole slaw
directions: In saucepan, heat to boiling the sugar, oil and vinegar.
Chop the bell pepper, cabbage and onion. Add the seasonings.
Best when made early and put in refrigerator overnight.
Serves 8.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together, place in 1 1/2-quart dish.

title: homemade ice cream(oreo cookies)
directions: In a large bowl, beat egg yolks, stir in Eagle Brand, water and vanilla.
Fold in cookies and whipped cream.
Cover a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan with aluminum foil, pour ingredients, cover and freeze for 6 hours or until firm.
Scoop ice cream from pan or peel off foil and slice.

title: amaretto no-bake cake
directions: Prepare pudding separately, using 1 1/2 cups milk per package. Chill.
Add 2 tablespoons liqueur to pudding after it's cooked. Line pan with toast, filling all spaces.
Mix 1/2 cup milk with 2 tablespoons of Amaretto (or rum) and drizzle over toast.
Spread chilled pudding; repeat toast layer.
Drizzle over with 1/2 cup milk and 2 tablespoons liqueur.
Spread other pudding.
Top with Cool Whip.
Garnish with slivered almonds or chocolate curls. Keep refrigerated.

title: chocolate covered cherry shake
directions: Grate ice in blender.
Add Hi-Energy Chocolate Supplement, cherry 7-Up and rum extract and blend.

title: mother's tomato soup
directions: Heat the
tomatoes
and juice in a medium size saucepan until hot.
Add
the
baking soda to the hot tomatoes and stir well. The
soda prevents the soup mixture from curdling.
Put the water in a small bowl or jar; add the flour and stir until it is very smooth.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and mix all ingredients together except bread; chill dip.
Cut center out of bread and fill with dip.
Break center of bread into bite size pieces and serve on platter.
(Also good served with crackers.)

title: persimmon cake
directions: Cream together shortening, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add the remainder of ingredients, mixing as you add each ingredient.
Pour into an angel food cake pan or Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan (sprayed with Pam). Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apple cider
directions: Mix and simmer for 10 minutes. Transfer to crock pot to keep warm.

title: broccoli with garlic and lemon
directions: Trim woody ends from stalks, leaving 4-inches of stem.
Cut lengthwise to make slender spears, leaving flowerets attached to stalks.
Cook in small amounts salted boiling water in skillet 3 to 5 minutes just until tender.
Drain.
Place in bowl.

title: party punch
directions: Mix ingredients in the order given in a large punch bowl. Do not prepare until you are ready to serve the punch.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice evenly in baking dish.
Add soup and water (mixed together).
Put chicken breasts on top.
Melt margarine. Pour over chicken.
Add Parmesan.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover last 15 or 20 minutes.

title: lemon curd(can be used with rosemary cake)
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender or mixer.
Cook in stainless or ceramic double boiler until thickened.
Serve warm on top of Sour Cream Rosemary Cake.
Refrigerate leftover sauce and reheat in double boiler to serve.
Yields about 2 cups.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Place small juice glass upside down in middle of casserole dish.
Mold meat mixture around glass in dish.
(Grease will go up into glass.)
Cover top with more catsup. Cook on High for 20 minutes.

title: creamy garden pasta salad
directions: In large bowl stir together the mayonnaise, scallions, lemon juice, basil, salt and pepper until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; toss to coat well.
Cover; chill.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tomato wine
directions: Let stand 4 days; strain and bottle.

title: red pepper soup
directions: Add dash of mint, tarragon, cayenne, fresh ground black pepper and crushed dried red pepper.

title: 24 hour slaw
directions: Shred cabbage; place 1/2 of cabbage in large crock.
Dice onion and green pepper over cabbage and cover with remaining cabbage.
Mix sugar, oil, vinegar and salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil; remove from fire and pour over cabbage.
Do not stir.
Let cabbage stand for 1 1/2 hours.
Then stir.
Place mixture in a covered dish and place in refrigerator for 24 hours before serving.
This will keep for 2 weeks.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients until blended well.
Refrigerate several hours.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: old salem pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and spices; add raisins and coat.
Cream margarine, adding sugar gradually and continue to cream.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin and water.
Stir to blend only until flour disappears.

title: fish soup(brodo di pesce)
directions: This was Dad Speciality.

title: chocolate ice cream cake
directions: Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on box.
Cool thoroughly.
Soften enough vanilla ice cream to cover top of cake, depending on taste.
From a pint to a quart.
Work quickly.
Put in freezer for 20-30 minutes.
Then frost with whipped cream and sprinkle with chocolate and return to freezer.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Heat brown sugar and butter until sugar dissolves.
Add cooked carrots.
Cook over medium heat until thickened.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Drain off grease.
Add soup and beans.
Put in a casserole dish.
Top with mashed potatoes, then the cheese.
Cook until cheese is brown in the oven.

title: graham cracker cake
directions: Beat with hand or mixer all together.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: fried apples
directions: In a large skillet, melt bacon drippings.
Pour sliced apples evenly over skillet bottom.
Sprinkle lemon juice over them, then brown sugar, then salt.
Cover and cook over low heat for 15 minutes or until apples are tender and juicy.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Serve as a side dish.

title: country-fried steak
directions: Trim fat from steak; pound to 1/4-inch thickness using a meat mallet.
Combine 1/3 cup flour, 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Dredge steak in flour mixture.
Cook steak in hot oil in skillet until browned, turning steak once.
Add sliced onion and water; cover, reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes or until tender.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs together.
Add flour, milk and smashed bananas.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Mixture will be bumpy.
Pour mixture into a loaf pan and bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pie crust(makes 2 pie crusts.)
directions: Add milk and boiling water to shortening.
Whip until mixture is creamed.
Add flour and salt.
Mix until mixture clings together. Divide into 2 parts. Roll crusts, one at a time, between 2 pieces of wax paper.
Bake at 475° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sausage bread
directions: Mix the eggs and cheese together with meat.
Roll the dough out the size of a jelly pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: potato salad for 50
directions: Cook and cool potatoes.
Mix eggs, pickles, mayonnaise, onion, pimentos and mustard well in a large bowl.
Add to potatoes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Refrigerate a few hours, covered, to blend flavors.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin and salt in hot water.
Add pineapple and juice and lemon juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in carrots and nuts.
Pour into a 4-quart mold or pan.
Chill until firm.
Makes 24 servings.

title: salad dressing
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Let cool.
Refrigerate.
Can be used on cabbage salad or lettuce.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Fry pork chops in olive oil.
Place in a big pot.
Add salt, garlic, onion and bell pepper; cook 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, seasoned salt, pepper, brown sugar and vinegar.
Cover.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Add broken spaghetti.
Cover.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream oleo, butter and cream cheese.
Slowly add and cream the sugar and eggs (1 at a time).
Mix well and add sifted flour, vanilla and almond.
Grease and lightly flour 10-inch tube Bundt pan.
Place cake in cold oven.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 285°.
Do not open oven door while baking.
Cool 20 minutes in pan after removing from oven.
This is a moist cake that keeps well.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Clean cauliflower and broccoli and chop. Mix Ranch, milk and Miracle Whip. Stir well. Add broccoli and cauliflower. Stir. Add bacon bits and cheese. Stir. Refrigerate for 3 hours. Serve.

title: devil's food mayonnaise cake
directions: Combine mayonnaise, cocoa and sugar and beat well.
Dissolve soda in water; add to mixture and add flour and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into greased, floured 2 x 8-inch square pan or two 9-inch layer pans.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Frost.

title: sweet zucchini pie
directions: Cook zucchini in microwave in 1 tablespoon water until tender; drain.
Put in blender with butter, egg and vanilla; chop.

title: quick chicken casserole
directions: Cover the rice with the water.
Sprinkle soup mix over.
Lay pieces of chicken on top.
Cover chicken with the soup mixture. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Quick and good.

title: sugar free lemon cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine in a mixing bowl.
Add liquid sweetener (or dissolved sweetener), egg, vanilla and lemon peel. Beat well.
Combine flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Drop by teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet; press flat with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until light brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, cheese, soup and 1 cup dressing.
Pour into an ungreased casserole dish.
Top with 1/2 cup dressing and melted butter.
Bake at 350° until it bubbles (about 15 to 20 minutes).

title: breakfast oatmeal pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cream butter and sugar. Blend in salt, cinnamon and cloves. Stir in maple syrup. Beat in eggs, one at a time. Stir in oatmeal. Pour into pie shell. Bake for 1 hour or until done in center. Spoon fruit on individual servings.

title: thrifty meatballs
directions: Combine beef, onion, oats, milk, salt, pepper, and poultry seasoning. Mix well and roll into little balls. Fry in grease until brown. Remove from skillet, pour off grease and add soup and water. Mix well. Add meat ball. Cook about 1
1/4 hours on slow heat.

title: quick sausage pie
directions: Cook meat in pan. Add onions and green pepper. Cook until just transparent.
Sprinkle in an 11 x 13-inch pan.
Next, add cheese. Top with cornbread batter.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt oleo and shortening in baking pan.
Dredge chicken in flour, salt and pepper.
Roll in oleo and shortening mixture. Bake for 1 hour until golden brown and crispy.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring the first 3 ingredients to a boil and cool to lukewarm. Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour onto an 18 x 21 x 1-inch cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish spice cake
directions: Put all the dry ingredients together.
Beat egg; add milk. Add to dry ingredients.
Add applesauce and melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Use a square or round baking pan.

title: pork tenderloin with honey & sesame sauce
directions: In a dish, just large enough to hold the pork, combine soy sauce, garlic and ginger root.
Add pork and let marinate, covered, turning several times for 1 hour.
Drain and pat the tenderloin dry.
Spread honey on a plate and roll the pork in it. Spread the sesame seeds on sheet of wax paper and roll pork in it.
Coat completely.
Roast pork
in a preheated 400 degree oven for 20 minutes or until no longer pink at the thickest part.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Slice on the diagonal and serve.

title: surprise fruit salad
directions: Mix drained fruit, whipped cream and granola together, then stir in sour cream or Imo.

title: tomato pepper beef
directions: Place beef in bowl, add garlic salt, flour, oil, and soy sauce.
Mix well.
Heat vegetable oil in skillet.
Add meat mixture.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Add green pepper.
Cook several minutes.
Add 1/2 cup water to each 2 tablespoons flour.
Add tomatoes and onions.
Cook 3 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: creamy scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt 6 tablespoons butter in large saucepan.
Stir in flour and seasonings.
Stir and cook until bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Continue cooking, stirring often.
Stir and boil for 1 minute.

title: venison roast
directions: Remove all fat from roast; season with salt and pepper.
Wash salt pork to remove excess salt; line roasting pan with salt pork. Place roast in pan.
Add the juice of 1 lemon, Worcestershire sauce, onion and slice of other lemon.
Cover and bake at 275° to 300° for 4 hours or until done, adding water as needed.
I use a roasting bag, done the same way.

title: eggnog pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time and mix well with electric mixer.
Add flour, flavorings and milk alternately.
Mix well.
Pour into well-greased and floured Bundt or tube cake pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: herbed walnuts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Place butter and oil in large pan and melt in oven.
Scatter nuts in pan, stir to coat, spread out in single layer.
Scatter seasonings evenly over nuts.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes, shaking and stirring several times until nuts are golden brown but not burned.
Drain (if necessary) on paper towels and serve warm or at room temperature.

title: strawberry pretzel delight
directions: Combine first three ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Beat well and spread over pretzels.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mash cooked squash; add 3 beaten eggs. Make two layers squash and eggs, onion and chicken soup and dressing-cheese (repeat).

title: apricot envelopes
directions: Cream Cheese Pastry:
Mix flour and salt.
Cut in cold water to form small peas.
Mix in cream cheese with fork to form dough. Shape into 5 inch square and chill at least 1 hour.
Roll out dough to 12 inch square.
Cut into 36 two inch squares.

title: upside-down cobbler
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into a greased square pan. Spread out.
Sweeten fruit to taste.
Pour over batter.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar and some cinnamon.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: potato dish
directions: Mix all ingredients except grated cheese.
Bake covered in a casserole dish for 1 hour 15 minutes at 350°.
Put grated cheese on top and return to oven.	Bake 15 more minutes (vary cheese to taste).

title: festive baked ham
directions: Combine apple cider and water in a saucepan, bring to a boil; set aside.
Remove skin from ham.
Place ham fat side up, on a cutting board; score fat in a diamond design and stud with cloves. Place ham in a shallow baking pan, fat side up and coat top with brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° about 2 hours (22 to 25 minutes per pound), basting every 30 minutes with cider mixture.

title: crab mold
directions: Heat soup and water; add gelatin, stir well until dissolved. Add cream cheese, blend, add other ingredients and stir.
Pour into mold.
Serve with assorted crackers or pretzels.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Combine cake mix, milk, eggs and oil.
Beat until smooth and add remaining ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dilly beans
directions: Pack beans in pint jars and leave 1/4 inch space to each jar, add 1/4 teaspoon pepper, 1 clove garlic and 1 dill head.
Combine ingredients of water, vinegar, pickling salt and sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Pour over beans.
Process 10 minutes in boiling water.
Let stand 2 weeks before tasting.

title: cinnamon peach crisp
directions: Butter a 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish or casserole.
Arrange peach slices in bottom of dish.
Drizzle with the lemon juice.
In a bowl, mix the flour, sugar and cinnamon.
With a fork, blend in the egg to make a crumbly mixture.
Sprinkle the mixture over the peaches.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until top is crisp and peaches are bubbly.
Serve warm or cooled with vanilla ice cream or whipped cream.

title: layered mexican dip
directions: Spread in order given on bottom of shallow dish.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: "fannie mae" fudge
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients over medium-high heat, until butter melts and sugar dissolves.
Stir constantly.
Add marshmallows and continue cooking until mixture is boiling, stirring constantly. Stir in all chocolates until well mixed.
Add nuts if desired. Pour into a well-greased jelly roll pan and cool.

title: barbecued pot roast(diet)
directions: Rub meat with salt and pepper.
Brown in Dutch oven over medium heat.
Cover.
Turn meat often to prevent sticking.
Pour off drippings.
Add tomato sauce, broth, onions and garlic.
Cook over low heat for 1 1/2 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat. Cover and cook for 1 hour longer or until meat is tender.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine; add all other ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch greased casserole dish.

title: crabmeat appetizers
directions: Blend all ingredients and spread on muffins.
Broil until lightly brown.
Cut each muffin into 4 pieces.
Serve hot or room temperature.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook onion and sausage.
When done, stir in potatoes (prepare as on package).
Heat to boil, then reduce.
Cover and simmer. Stir in cooked broccoli and cheese.
Cook until cheese melts.

title: christmas chocolate fudge
directions: Melt butter in large, heavy saucepan; add milk and blend. Then add sugar, stirring constantly and bring to a boil.
Boil vigorously for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add chocolate morsels and beat vigorously until morsels are melted.
Then add marshmallow cream and continue beating until melted and well blended. Add vanilla and nuts and blend well. Turn into a well buttered pan and let sit at least 6 hours before cutting.
Cut in large squares and store in airtight container. Makes about 4 pounds of fudge.

title: granola pumpkin bread
directions: Cream butter and add sugar; beat in eggs and extract.
Add pumpkin; mix well.
Sift together flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices.
Blend with pumpkin mixture.
Stir in nuts, raisins and cereal.
Add 1/2 cup orange juice if dough seems too heavy.
Divide into 3 greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° , 60 minutes.
Test with toothpick after 50 minutes.
Yields 3 loaves.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan. Sift flour with soda, cinnamon and salt.
In large bowl of electric mixer, combine sugar and salad oil.
Add half of the flour mixture; mix well.
Beat in carrots, pineapple, vanilla and nuts.
Add remaining flour mixture; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Pour into prepared pan; bake for 60 to 70 minutes.
Makes 16 servings.

title: caramel ice cream
directions: In a stainless steel bowl, beat egg yolks and 1/3 cup sugar until thick and creamy.
In a saucepan, scald milk.
Pour over eggs and place bowl over a pan of simmering water.
Stir slowly and continually for 10 minutes or until custard slightly thickens.

title: sausage spaghetti primavera
directions: Prepare spaghetti, drain.
In large skillet heat oil, add smoked sausage and remaining ingredients except spaghetti and cheese.
Cook and stir until vegetables are tender crisp.
Add spaghetti and cheese, toss well.
Serve hot.

title: granny's caramel corn
directions: Pop corn and place in a large roaster.
Combine brown sugar, margarine, salt and syrup in a large pan and boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
After it has boiled 5 minutes, add soda and stir rapidly, until caramel foams to 2 or 3 times its volume.

title: sarah's punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid; add everything else but ginger ale.
Freeze to keep.
Before serving, thaw to slush state then add ginger ale and serve.
Serves 25.

title: quick and hearty vegetable soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat, onion and garlic until tender; drain.
Stir in all remaining ingredients, except frozen vegetables.
Cover and bring to boil.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and simmer 10 more minutes.

title: lime mold
directions: Whip cream.
Blend pears and juice in blender.
Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Tear up lettuce in small pieces.
Place in oblong dish.
Layer celery, peppers, onion and peas (peas do not have to be thawed).

title: baby pizzas
directions: Cut bagels in half.
Place cut edge up on cookie sheet.
Top with sauce and cheese, then add any other topping on bagels as you like.
Place in oven at 350° until cheese is melted or put on microwave-safe plate on High for 1 minute for every 2 bagels.

title: down home corn bread
directions: Mix corn muffin mix according to instructions on package.
Stir in corn, green pepper and red pepper.
Preheat oven at 325°.
Pour corn mix into a buttered pan.
Cook until brown or until inserted fork comes out clean.

title: manhattan clam chowder
directions: Slice bacon; fry until brown.
Add onion and fry with bacon until transparent.
Add potatoes, soup, water and clam juice. Open cans of clams and add liquid to soup.
Cook 20 minutes until potatoes are done.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add clams. Bring to a boil and thicken with 1 tablespoon cornstarch in 1/2 cup water.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Mix and press hamburger, mushrooms and onions in baking dish or pie plate (bottom and sides).
Bake at 375° until brown.
Drain off grease.
Cook 5 to 6 average sized potatoes.
Mash with about 8 ounces Velveeta cheese (add more cheese if needed or add 2 tablespoons milk).
Put potatoes and cheese in middle of hamburger ring.

title: vegetable meat loaf
directions: Mix well and bake.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend eggs, sweet potatoes, sugar and evaporated milk in food processor or with mixer.
Microwave butter and marshmallows on High 1 to 2 minutes until melted.
Blend in with potatoes.
Place in ring pan or 2-quart casserole.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt oleo and mix with crumbs.
Line bottom of large casserole dish with 1/2 of mixture.
Add mixture and pour over crumbs.
Top with remaining 1/2 of crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: spice cake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together in large bowl the cake mix, brown sugar, oats, nuts and raisins.
Stir to coat nuts and raisins.
Add eggs, oil and milk.
Mix well. Drop teaspoonful of dough onto greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 60.

title: spanakopita
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan with butter.
Line pan with 4 to 5 filo including sides.
Brush melted butter lightly over layer. Beat eggs until slightly fluffy.
Dice cheese into very small pieces and mix into eggs.
Also, mix in salt and oil.
Brown finely chopped onion and mix into cheese, eggs and spinach.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown beef and onion slowly, then drain. Add other ingredients and mix well. Simmer on stove for 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with crackers or hot rolls.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs very lightly; add all other ingredients and blend. Fold into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake in a slow oven, 300°, for 45 to 60 minutes or until sets.

title: sausage skillet dinner
directions: Cook sausage, onion and green pepper in a skillet until sausage is browned. Stir to crumble. Drain. Stir in macaroni, tomatoes, tomato sauce, sugar, chili powder and salt.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 25 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Stir in sour cream.
Cook until heated.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: quick and easy meatballs and sauce
directions: Combine ingredients and heat in a skillet or crockpot.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients slowly; add eggs, milk and butter.
Beat until smooth.
Cook in waffle iron.
Makes 8 waffles.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve orange jello and lemon jello in hot water.
Add cold water.
Add pineapple.
Cut bananas and put in jello.
Put in 2 large bowls or 9 x 13-inch Pyrex pan.
Sprinkle with miniature marshmallows.
Let stand until very firm.

title: wag's little pizzas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll biscuits out as thin as possible. Lay them on a cookie sheet.
Place a spoonful of pizza sauce on biscuits.
Top with pepperoni and cheese.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes (watch for cheese to melt).

title: ham with cherry sauce
directions: Slit surface of ham, making diamond shapes 1/2-inch deep. Combine jelly, mustard and 1 tablespoon ginger ale. Rub this over ham. Cut ham in half and place in a slow cooker and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours.

title: kay crum's blueberry coffee cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients with a wooden spoon.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 9-inch pan.
Melt the remaining margarine and add the brown sugar and nuts to it.
Pour over top of batter. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes or until brown.

title: sesame chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken in flour mixture.
Coat on both sides.
Heat oil in baking pan in oven.
Add chicken, turning to coat both sides with oil.
Sprinkle with half of the sesame seed.
Bake for 30 minutes. Turn chicken; sprinkle with remaining sesame seed.
Pour wine into pan.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes more, until tender, basting occasionally.

title: corn-cheese casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: sugar waffles
directions: Beat egg and sugar together.
Mix in baking powder and vanilla.
Gradually add flour and water, alternating as you add. Beat together.

title: meat ball soup
directions: Form first 8 ingredients into meat balls.
Cook in salt water seasoned with parsley flakes and pepper.
Cook until meat balls are done.
Add pasta.
Cook until tender.
Add vegetables.
Cook to heat.
Serve.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in top of double boiler.
Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, vanilla and milk.
Mix well.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Stir in nuts and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mom's cupcake surprise
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and eggs together.
Mix in chocolate chips; set aside.
Prepare cake mix according to cupcake directions.
Fill cupcake papers 3/4 full.
Put one tablespoon of cream mixture in center.
Bake as directed.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate in pan.
Remove from heat and add sugar, eggs, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt and mix well. Add nuts and stir.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan (greased) and bake 27 minutes at 350°.
(It will be very moist when removed from oven.)
Allow to cool completely before cutting into squares.

title: lasagna toss
directions: Brown beef with onion and garlic salt.
Stir in spaghetti sauce; simmer until heated.
Remove 1 cup meat sauce and set aside.
Stir noodles into remaining sauce.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Brown beef; add green pepper and onions.
Brown; drain fat. Mix other ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: peanut soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine broth, celery, carrot and onion. Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Strain, discarding vegetables or you may puree them in blender and add to soup stock.
Put peanut butter in the same saucepan.
Gradually stir the hot broth into the peanut butter.
Mixture will be stiff at first, but will become smooth. Add evaporated milk and sugar.
Heat through, but do not boil. Serves 6.

title: brown sugar custard pie with peanuts
directions: Combine brown sugar, sugar, salt, eggs and vanilla in a large mixing bowl.
Beat with a rotary beater until thoroughly blended. Gradually stir in scalded milk; stir in peanuts.
Pour into pastry shell and bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes or until silver knife inserted in center of filling comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack for 30 minutes.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together and bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle some cheese on top if desired.

title: italian beef
directions: Place in crock-pot on high; cover in water and add the two packages Italian mix and cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until roast beef will tear apart.
Take out roast and tear in small pieces. Put back in broth and turn crock-pot on low until ready to serve.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Spray bottom of pan with Pam.
Spread rice; add chicken and soups.
Cover and bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: chicken drumsticks, tex mex style
directions: Wash drumsticks and pat dry.
(May remove skin for lower fat.) Place in plastic or brown bag with 2 tablespoons of flour and shake until coated.
Melt butter in a large skillet with cover. Brown drumsticks.
Remove to plate.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Mix rice and undiluted soups.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch casserole. Sprinkle dried onion soup mix over rice.
Dip chicken in melted oleo.
Place on top of rice.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours.
Cover with foil and cook about 35 to 40 minutes.
Uncover the last 15 minutes and finish cooking and brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles. Dice vegetables.
Mix everything together and chill.

title: coconut thumbprints
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheets.
Cream butter flavor Crisco with sugar, egg yolk and vanilla in large bowl at medium speed of electric mixer.
Combine flour with salt and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Form into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Beat egg white until slightly frothy.
Dip dough balls into egg white, then roll in coconut. Place on greased baking sheets.
Make shallow depression in center of each cookie using thumb or back of very small spoon.
Place 1/2 measuring teaspoon preserves in each center.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes or until coconut begins to brown.
Cool on baking sheets about 1 to 2 minutes.
Remove to cooling racks.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: unbaked fudge cookies
directions: In saucepan, stir sugar, cocoa and milk together.
Add 1 stick margarine.
Stir until the butter melts over medium heat.
By the time the margarine melts, the mixture will begin to boil.
Boil for 1 minute.
Take off the stove, then add 1/2 teaspoon vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto waxed paper and let cool.

title: chocolate squares
directions: Crumble graham crackers.
Melt stick of butter.
Add chips, nuts and coconut.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread can of milk on top.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
When cool, cut into squares or desired size.

title: banana walnut cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: jalapeno spinach
directions: Cook spinach according to directions. Drain well, keeping 1/2 cup liquid. Melt margarine in saucepan. Add onions and cook until tender. Blend flour, milk and spinach liquid. Cook together until slightly thickened. Add Worcestershire sauce, celery, garlic salt, salt and pepper. Add cheese. Stir until melted. Add spinach and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake 30 minutes in 300° oven.

title: oriental grilled chicken
directions: Mix marinade ingredients well.
Coat chicken; cover and refrigerate for at least 2 hours, turning occasionally.

title: squash casserole
directions: Make cornbread as instructions.
Crumble and add 2 cups milk. Let soak. Saute onion, pepper and celery together.
Add to bread mixture. Add 1/2 cup cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add 1/2 cup cheese. Return to oven for a few minutes until melted.
Makes 1 large casserole.

title: pecan delight muffins *
directions: With fork, beat eggs and add sugar and butter.
Stir in flour, vanilla and nuts.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: sweet potato bread
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well and add dry ingredients.
Add 1 cup chopped nuts.
Put equal amounts in 2 greased tall 1 pound coffee cans.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, slice in rounds.
Cool completely before removing from cans.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease jelly roll pan; line bottom with wax paper.
Grease paper.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Invert roll onto clean towel dusted with powdered sugar and walnuts.
Peel off wax paper.
Roll up cake and towel together.
Place seam side down and cool completely.

title: fresh apple dessert
directions: Mix apples, sugar, cinnamon and flour.
Place in buttered 9 X 13 pan.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and continue to bake for 30 minutes or until firm to the touch.

title: cherry-pineapple crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a 3-quart oblong Pyrex baking dish or an 11 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan, put 2 cans cherry pie filling and 1 can crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle coconut.

title: no-bake cheese cake
directions: In blender, mix milk and cream cheese.
Add pudding.
Blend and pour into crust.
Chill and top with favorite fruits.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and butter over low heat until smooth. Combine sweet potatoes and marshmallow mixture, mixing until blended.
Blend in combined granulated sugar and spices; add brown sugar, mixing until smooth.
Blend in eggs and milk.
Pour into crusts.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°; continue baking 50 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Cool.
Garnish with whipped topping and chopped pecans, if desired.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix well the eggs and sugar; add pumpkin, salad oil and water. Mix flour, baking powder, soda, salt, spices and nuts to pumpkin mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours in greased and floured pan.

title: golf balls candy
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add the other ingredients, except chocolate chips and wax, and mix by hand.
Roll in hands a medium size piece of dough to make a ball.
Chill overnight.
Dip balls in melted wax and chocolate chips.

title: radio candy
directions: Put sugars, butter and canned milk together.
Boil to soft ball stage.
Add nuts, dates and coconut to sauce; boil 5 more minutes. Beat a little with spoon until shiny.
Put into greased cookie pan. Let set up and cool, then cut into squares.

title: easy cheesy vegetable soup
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook onion in hot margarine or butter until tender, but not brown. Add corn, broccoli, carrot and water. Bring to boiling. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir in soup, milk, cheeses and pepper. Cook and stir over medium heat until cheese is melted and mixture is heated through.
Serves 4 as a first course.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Cook over high flame until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter to taste and white syrup.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool, then cut into little squares.

title: orange-coconut balls
directions: Mix together vanilla wafers (crushed) and powdered sugar.
Add warmed margarine and undiluted orange juice.
Mix well.
Make (roll) into small balls and roll in the coconut.
Chill.

title: pinto beans and ham
directions: Wash and clean pinto beans; add 2 quarts water to large pot. Add beans and cook 3 hours.
Add spices.
Add veggies and ham with 2 tablespoons of sugar.
Mash with fork some of the beans to make thick.
Serve with cornbread.

title: salad dressing
directions: Fry 3 slices of bacon, or use 4 tablespoons bacon grease in skillet. Add other ingredients.
Mix all together and cook until thick.
Pour hot over leaf lettuce.

title: apple pie
directions: Slice apples.
Fill 9-inch uncooked pie crust.
Add butter, nutmeg, cinnamon and sugar over apples.
Add tapioca around edge or mix with apples.
Cover top with pie crust.
Fold edges under bottom crust. Cut slits for steam in top of pie crust.
Bake for 1 hour at 400° or until apples are done.

title: galletas con natilla
directions: In a large bowl, cream the margarine and sugar. Add the egg yolks and vanilla. Mix well.

title: italian chicken
directions: Salt and pepper chicken pieces.
Beat 4 eggs.
Mix some of the grated Parmesan with bread or cracker crumbs.
Roll chicken pieces in egg, then in crumbs.
Place in greased baking dish. Sprinkle garlic, grated Parmesan and parsley over chicken. Drizzle oil over the top.

title: oven porcupines
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, rice, 1/2 cup water, onion, salt, garlic powder and pepper.
Shape mixture into balls.
Place in ungreased baking dish.
Stir together the rest of the ingredients; pour over meatballs.
Bake for 45 minutes, covered, and for 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: daffodil salad
directions: Mix lime jello as directed on box.
Let cool, then mix cream cheese in jello.
Add chopped celery to mixture and put in 9 x 9-inch pan and congeal.
Mix lemon jello with 1 cup hot water. Drain pineapple and put juice in 1 cup measuring cup and finish filling with water.
Add to lemon jello and add crushed pineapple. When lime jello is set, pour lemon jello on top.
When this is congealed, serve on lettuce leaf.

title: quick and easy ice cream treat
directions: Spread 1/2 of Cool Whip across bottom of 9 x 13 pan.
Layer ice cream sandwiches over Cool Whip.
Combine remainder of Cool Whip and crushed Butterfinger bars and spread over top of sandwiches.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: chicken or turkey dressing
directions: Crumble breads.
Chop celery, onion, eggs and green pepper; mix well.
Stir in salt, pepper and sage.
Moisten all with giblet broth.

title: cornflake cookies
directions: Mix sugar and syrup and bring to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add cornflakes.
Mix well.
Quickly spoon out onto wax paper.

title: pork and beans
directions: Put ingredients in 3-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered in 325° oven, stirring occasionally, for 3 1/2 hours.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
