Mix corn, flour and sugar together. Add milk and hot water.
Beat eggs well and mix in with the above ingredients.
Add melted butter; stir well.

title: skillet fried corn
directions: Fry bacon in a large skillet until crisp. Remove bacon, reserving the drippings. Add green pepper to drippings in skillet. Saut over medium heat, stirring constantly, until peppers are tender. Stir in corn. Cook over medium heat 10 to 12 minutes, stirring frequently. Stir in salt and sugar. Crumble bacon and place on top of corn.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers and salt for at least 3 hours.

title: pizzaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, crumbling meat as it cooks; drain.
Add green pepper to meat.
Stir in pasta sauce; simmer for 5 minutes.
Cook spaghetti as directed on box; drain.
Spread half of cooked spaghetti in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread half of sauce mixture over it.
Place layer of sliced pepperoni on top of sauce.
Cover pepperoni with half of cheese.
Repeat to make second layer.
Place in hot oven (375°) until cheese melts or becomes lightly browned.
Cool slightly.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: hodge podge
directions: Brown ground beef and onions. Mix together with rest of ingredients. Cook 20 minutes.

title: spiced mocha mix
directions: Mix all ingredients completely.
Store in airtight container. In a cup mix 3 to 4 heaping teaspoons with 6 ounces boiling water.

title: hash brown quiche
directions: Press hash browns between toweling to remove moisture.
Press into bottom of 9-inch pie plate or quiche pan.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat to 350°. Remove from oven.
Toss ham and cheese together.
Pour over hash brown crust.
Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Pour over ham and cheese.
Bake, uncovered 25 to 30 minutes at 350° or until knife comes out clean near center.
Let stand 10 minutes.
May use onion, green pepper or mushrooms.

title: egg strata
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay cubed bread.
Sprinkle sausage over bread, then mushrooms and both cheeses on top.
Add cream and milk to eggs.
Add seasonings.
Pour over mixture in pan. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until custard sets. Let stand for 10 minutes before serving.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Crumble cooled, baked cake.
Layer 1/2 of cake cubes in clear punch bowl.
Top with 1 can pie filling, 1/2
vanilla pudding, 1/2 pineapple chunks, 1/2 bananas and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Repeat layers using other 1/2 of ingredients.
Garnish with pecans, cherries and coconut.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: First Layer:
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, break pretzels.
Melt butter.
Pour butter over pretzels.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°. Let cool completely.

title: four bean salad
directions: Combine vegetables and eggs.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight.
Yields 12 servings.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Grease 8 x 8-inch pan. Brown meat; add soup and spices and let simmer.
Boil and drain noodles.
Place 1/2 noodles on bottom of pan.
Pour 1/2 of meat sauce over noodles.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of Cheddar cheese.
Repeat layers and top with Parmesan cheese. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and leave in for another 10 to 20 minutes to brown.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Beat sugar and cheese together in mixer, add vanilla and eggs, beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into a deep 9-inch pie dish. Bake for 50 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven, cool for 20 minutes.
Spoon the following mixture over the top:
2 cups sour cream, 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well together and pour over cake.
Bake another 15 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Cool.
Then refrigerate.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Cook together cranberries and water; boil until cranberries begin to break open and are slightly soft.
Add sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add lemon jello and stir until dissolved.
Cool.
Add crushed pineapple and nuts.
Mix well and refrigerate over nuts and are ready to use.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: oatmeal-pecan-raisin-chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set
aside.
In large bowl at medium speed, beat margarine,
brown sugar, sugar and vanilla until light.
Add eggs; blend
well. Reduce
speed to low.
Add oats and dry ingredients;
beat	just until blended.
Stir in pecans, raisins and chips.	Shape
dough into
1/2-inch
balls.
Place
on wax paper-covered
baking sheet.
Using a teaspoon, flatten balls to	3/4-inch thick. Freeze for 15 minutes, or refrigerate for 6
hours or overnight. Remove from wax paper.
Place 3 inches apart
on
greased
baking sheets.
Bake at 350° for 14 to 16 minutes until golden.
Cool 2 minutes.
Remove to rack.

title: chocolate scotcheroos
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup in a 3-pint saucepan over moderate heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in Rice Krispies.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels over very low heat or in double boiler until all is melted.
Spread over Rice Krispies mixture.
Chill about 5 minutes, until top is firm.
Cut into bars.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
By spoon, add and mix in flour until you see no flour.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: tropical delight
directions: Defrost dessert topping.
Combine all ingredients including juices from pineapple and cherries.
Refrigerate.
Yields 11 cups, about 14 servings.
Can be made one day in advance to blend flavors, but if made two days in advance, does not hold up well.

title: squash
directions: Melt margarine.
Add to stuffing. Set aside.
Cube squash. Boil until tender.
Drain and mash gently.
Mix squash with carrot, onion, soup and sour cream.

title: layered salad
directions: In a glass bowl, thinly slice and layer the first 6 ingredients in order as the appear. Chill for a minimum of 4 hours. Top with dressing and layer with remaining ingredients as they appear.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown meat, onions and spices together.
Drain grease.
Add tomato sauce, mushroom soup and crushed tomatoes.
Mix well and simmer until hot.
Taste for seasoning.
Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serves 100 people.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo and add eggs; mix well. Roll in extra flour pecans, raisins, dates, figs, coconut, and add to mixture. Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, vanilla, and strawberry preserves and mix well. Mix soda with applesauce and then add to mixture. Bake in tube pan at 225 for 1 1/2 hours and then at 275 until done. Cool in pan 10 - 15 minutes and remove.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred the cabbage, carrots and green pepper. Add salt.
Mix together and let stand 1 hour.

title: easy bake fruitcake no. 1
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into iron frying pan or loaf pan and bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours in 275° oven.
Bundt pan may be used.

title: ham-cheese delight
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into a baking dish, greased. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken with celery and leaves in buttered baking dish. Tear celery and leaves into bite size pieces.
Pour broth over and then the soup.
Spread stuffing mix over this.
Then pour the oleo.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: boiled spice cake
directions: Bring all of the ingredients to a boil.
Remove from heat and, when cool, add 3 cups sifted flour and 2 teaspoons baking soda. Pour into a baking dish and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.
Add the caramel frosting to the cake top after cake is well cooled.

title: blueberry dream squares
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine cake mix, 6 tablespoons margarine and 1 cup oats.
Mix until crumbly. Reserve 1 cup crumbs for topping.
To remaining crumbs, add 1 egg; mix well.
Press into pan.
Pour pie filling over crust.
Spread to cover.
To reserved crumbs and remaining 1/4 cup oats, 2 tablespoons margarine, nuts and brown sugar.
Thoroughly mix. Sprinkle over blueberry mixture.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with whip cream.

title: sausage-ziti bake
directions: Cook and drain ziti.
In large skillet, thoroughly brown sausage.
Add onion; saute until tender.
Drain fat.
Add sauce, ziti, salt, pepper, oregano and Parmesan.
Spoon into a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Bake, covered, for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese; bake for 5 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: corn corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 425° until brown.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Add eggs and oil, stirring until dry ingredients are moistened (do not beat).
Stir in pineapple, pecans and bananas.
Spoon batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Place sugar and Crisco or Snowdrift into bowl; blend.
Add water a teaspoon at a time until desired consistency.
Now add butter flavoring.
Blend well.
Add a dash of salt, no more than 1/4 teaspoon.
This will break down the sweetness of the sugar. Yields 2 cups.

title: easter eggnog
directions: Beat cream about 1 1/2 cups at a time, until thick.
Combine sugar and egg yolks and beat well.
Blend into cream.
Then blend in brandy.
Beat egg whites until rounded peaks are formed and fold into cream mixture.
It may require more sugar according to taste.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well; add a little hot water along to make mixing easier. Roll into 1-inch Sausage Balls.
Bake in 375° oven for 15 minutes or until done.

title: baked lemon pudding
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cut in butter, rind and juice.
Add well beaten egg yolks and milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into a 2-quart buttered dish.
Set in pan of warm water. Bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: coconut cookies
directions: With a spoon, stir sugars, shortening, eggs, salt, soda and vanilla until smooth; add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Mix first six ingredients; add mayonnaise (just enough to hold the salad together) and salt and pepper.
Chill at least two hours.
When ready to serve, mound salad on a bed of red leaf lettuce and garnish with fresh parsley and sliced olives.

title: easy punch
directions: Put all ingredients in gallon jar and finish filling with water.
Color of punch is determined by Kool-Aid.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Mix sugars well.
Add oil, eggs, peanut butter and vanilla. Stir after each ingredient.
Add flour and salt.
Will be stiff. Pour into 9 x 13 greased and floured pan.
Spread evenly.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cake will rise and then settle when cool.

title: pennsylvania dutch pie crust(from home economics teacher's cookbook)
directions: Sift flour and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
(In Cuisinart, mix first 3 ingredients, then add the rest.)
Beat water, egg and vinegar together; stir into flour mixture.
Shape into a ball.
Chill.
Turn out on floured board; roll to fit pie pan.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes in 425° oven for a pie shell.
Otherwise, follow the time set for chosen kind of pie.

title: meringue kisses
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy, then add salt and cream of tartar and continue beating until eggs are stiff enough to hold peaks, but not dry.
Add sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Fold in chocolate chips and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased aluminum foil.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes.
Remove from foil while slightly warm.
Makes 72 kisses.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake at 350`f. 180`c.
gas mark 4 for 25 minutes.

title: zucchini pie (a quiche)
directions: Cook sliced zucchini and onion in butter in frypan until tender (about 10 minutes).
Add all spices.
Cook another 5 minutes in a separate bowl; beat eggs and add grated cheese.
Add zucchini mixture and stir together.

title: spinach and cheese lasagna
directions: In microwave, cook spinach. Squeeze dry. Add approximately 2 tablespoons olive oil. Add salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste. Mix well. Layer, beginning with sauce (soup), lasagna noodles, spinach, Ricotta, Mozzarella, then more sauce. Continue to layer. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, until bubbly and lightly browned.

title: date nut bread
directions: Four eggs, four cups flour, one cup sorghum, one cup sugar, one cup sour milk, one teaspoon each of ginger, cinnamon and cloves, one teaspoon of soda dissolved in milk, one cup seedless raisins dredged in flour.
Mix and bake in moderate oven.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, melt margarine; stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil; boil and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in confectioners sugar; beat until smooth.
Spread in buttered 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: divinity
directions: Place sugar, syrup, water and salt in a saucepan over low heat.
Stir until sugar is dissolved, then cook without stirring to 252° (very firm ball).
Just before syrup reaches 252°, beat the egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Wipe the crystals from the pouring edge of the pan.
Pour the syrup in a very fine stream over the egg whites, beating constantly while pouring.
Do not scrape bottom of pan.
Continue beating until the mixture holds its shape.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Cook broccoli following directions on box.
Drain broccoli and add the rest of the ingredients.
Stir until mixed well.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400°. (Test for doneness in the middle.)
Cool and cut into squares.

title: baked shrimp
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine ingredients and pour over shrimp in shallow roasting pan.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes, stirring once or twice during cooking.
Drain at once.
Sauce is good for dunking French bread.

title: chicken breast party casserole(tastes gourmet, but is easy!)
directions: Place chicken breasts in a flat casserole dish.
Put cheese slices on top.
Cover with cream of chicken soup.
Mix cream and wine together and pour on top.
Spread stuffing mixture over all. Drizzle butter on top.
May be made the day before.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter bonbons
directions: In a large mixer bowl, beat peanut butter, margarine, vanilla and salt until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk, then confectioners sugar until smooth.
Shape into 1-inch balls. Place on baking sheets.
Chill until firm.
With fork or wooden pick, dip each ball into melted candy coating.
Place on wax paper lined baking sheets. Let stand or chill (I freeze them) until firm.
Store at room temperature, freezer or refrigerator. Excellent!

title: no crust cream cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese; add 2/3 cup sugar and beat.
Add eggs and beat; add almond extract and beat.
Pour into 9-inch greased glass pie dish.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Beat together sour cream, 5 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Pour over cheese pie that has been baked and cooled.
Return to oven.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: copper penny
directions: Peel and slice 2 packages of raw carrots.
Cook until fork-tender.
Put in colander and rinse with ice water.
Slice one purple onion and one green pepper.
Alternate layers of carrots, onion and pepper in your serving bowl.

title: winner fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Chill.
Serve with fruits cut into bite size pieces.
Especially good with strawberries, bananas, pineapple, apple, grapefruit and pears.

title: grits light bread
directions: Cook grits in 1 2/3 cups boiling water for 3 minutes.
Let cool completely.
Combine 1 pint lukewarm water with yeast and 1/3 cup sugar.
Let stand until bubbly.
Add Crisco, oil and grits.
Sift flour, dry milk and salt.
Combine with previous ingredients and let rise.
Knead down.
Divide into 8 well-greased coffee cans. Let rise.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes.
Makes great toast!

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Melt margarine in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Add mushrooms and onions; saute 7 minutes or until liquid evaporates. Stir in all-purpose flour, gradually adding chicken broth, skim milk and light cream cheese.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes. Set aside.

title: garden special
directions: Dice peppers, onions and celery; add enough water to cover. Cook over medium heat, 20 minutes.
Add cut up tomatoes, sugar and salt.
Bring to boil.
Pack in hot, sterilized jars.
Cook 25 minutes in hot water bath for pints, 30 minutes for quart jars.

title: lemon sponge cake pie
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, sugar, lemon juice and rind, salt, flour or cornstarch, egg yolks and milk.
Beat egg whites stiff and fold in.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: mango pork chops
directions: Trim fat from chops. Heat fat in skillet until you have 2 teaspoons melted fat. Remove trimming. Brown chops. Season with salt and pepper. Pour off excess fat. Add water to mango. Add to chops with celery, onion, soy sauce and vinegar. Cover pan. Simmer on low heat 45 minutes to 1 hour until tender. Remove chops. Mix cornstarch with water. Stir into sauce and cook until mixture thickens. Return chops to skillet. Cover and simmer until heated through. Serve with steamed rice. Serves 6.

title: floating biscuit chicken pie
directions: Place half the chicken in a 9-inch square baking dish.
Cover with sliced eggs, celery, onion flakes and rest of chicken.
Add soup and broth.
Mix together flour, baking powder, melted oleo and milk.
Spoon on top of chicken.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets until tender.
Cool, peel, and grate.
In large saucepan, combine cheese and margarine over low heat.
Stir until almost melted.
Blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in grated potatoes; turn into casserole dish which has been sprayed with a non-stick cooking spray.
Dot top with margarine.
May top with extra shredded cheese if desired.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese with ham and peas(a hearty whole-meal salad)
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients, then gently stir in sliced olives.
Combine yogurt and mayonnaise and then gently stir into salad.
Serve in lettuce-lined bowl.
Garnish as desired.
Serves 8 or more, maybe 12.

title: banana punch
directions: Heat water and sugar in saucepan until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat and stir in juices. Mash bananas or run in blender with 1 cup of the juices.
Add mashed bananas to fruit juice mixture.
Pour into 4 refrigerator trays and freeze.

title: sassy potato corn chowder
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain. Cook potatoes, broth, corn, onion and celery in a large pot. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Mix flour and dressing; stir in milk. Add to potato mixture. Continue cooking 3 to 5 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Sprinkle with bacon and parsley, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine jello with water according to package directions.
Add pineapple, oranges and cottage cheese.
Fold in Cool Whip. Refrigerate until set.
Serve.

title: shrimp balls
directions: Mix all ingredients until shrimp is broken up and well blended. Form into balls. Best if chilled overnight.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Grind or chop finely the oranges, apples and cranberries. Add sugar and crushed pineapple. In another bowl, dissolve the jello in the water/juice mixture. Add the fruit mixture and pecans. Refrigerate. Will keep in refrigerator for 2 weeks. Also, can be frozen.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Measure 1/2 teaspoon dill to each quart jar.
Slice pickles and pack in jars.
Bring syrup to boil; pour over pickles.
Seal, then process 5 minutes after boiling point is reached.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute onions in hot oil in skillet.
Add beef and mushrooms. Cook until brown, then drain.
Slice garlic, mash with salt, add to meat with pepper, oregano, parsley, tomatoes, tomato sauce and 2 tablespoons Parmesan.
Simmer covered 30 minutes.
Refrigerate until ready to use (best if left overnight or frozen for later use).

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken with some seasoning in water until tender; take off bones and cut in small pieces.
Set aside.
Put in bowl 1 stick melted margarine and 3 tablespoons Worcestershire sauce, Season-All, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add 1 can cream of mushroom soup.
Add 2 cans chicken broth (from boiled chicken). Add chicken and canned vegetables; mix well (add more broth if too dry).
Pour into greased baking pan.
Put pie crust on top and slices of margarine on top.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: family farmer omelet
directions: Brown sausage and drain it.
Mix up eggs, milk and cheese in large frying pan.
Stir in crumbled sausage.
Add in pepper, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook over medium heat, stirring often; it will thicken up in approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve over toasted bread (2 slices on plate); spoon over omelet.
Great eating.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt butter; pour into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Crush graham crackers.
Spread over butter.
Alternately spread chocolate chips, coconut and walnuts.
Pour can of milk over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry smoothie
directions: In blender container, combine banana, 12 strawberries, orange juice and milk.
Cover and blend on medium speed.
Makes 2.

title: two bite pizza
directions: Simmer sausage until half done.
Add onions and cook until both are done.
Drain.
Add sharp and Parmesan cheeses, oregano, salt, tomato paste and sauce.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cool.
Take 12 biscuits from 1 can.
Separate each biscuit into four layers. Place on cookie sheet.
Add 1 teaspoon pizza mixture to top of each layer.
Repeat on second can.
Freeze on cookie sheet. Remove when frozen and store in plastic bag. When ready to serve, take from freezer and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: garlic cheese
directions: Grate Cheddar cheese and pod garlic together; add cream cheese.
Use a fork and mix together well.
Knead mixture and roll into roll.
Sprinkle some chili powder and paprika on wax paper. Roll the cheese roll on the wax paper so that the entire roll as a red coat.
Roll in pecans (optional).
Place in refrigerator and let chill.
Good on Ritz crackers.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 7 to 8 minutes at 425°.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put a layer of rice in bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange chicken breasts on top of rice.
Mix soup.
Pour over chicken and on rice.
Put a pat of butter on each piece of chicken and sprinkle them with Lawry's seasoned salt for added flavor.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 250° or until done.
Remove foil and turn oven up.
Brown slightly at end of cooking time.

title: sweet potato and apple dish
directions: Mix brown sugar and cinnamon for apples.
Melt butter in bottom of baking casserole dish.
Put layers of sweet potatoes, dabs of butter, then layer of sugared apples.
Add dabs of butter (pecans optional).
Continue layers until required amount in dish.
Bake at 350° for at least 30 to 45 minutes.
Last 5 minutes of baking, add miniature marshmallows to top and brown.

directions: Heat oven to

title: christmas pie rice
directions: Mix and bake 1 hour at 400°.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine and pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Add 1/2 package hash browns.

title: easy cheesy potatoes
directions: In small bowl, combine soup, milk and pepper.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, arrange alternate layers of potatoes, onion and soup mixture, ending with soup mixture.
Dot with butter.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes.
Garnish with paprika or cooked crumbled bacon.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Grease 12 muffin cups or use baking cups.
Beat egg and sugar together.
When smooth, beat in bananas, raisins, walnuts, oil, vanilla and banana flavoring.
Let stand 1 minute.
Thoroughly mix flour, bran, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Add to the banana mixture; fold in just until ingredients are moistened.
Divide batter into the muffin cups and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 400° until browned and springy to the touch in the center.
Turn out onto rack to cool.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put all ingredients, except crust, in a blender.
Mix 1 to 2 minutes until all ingredients are blended.
Pour into 9-inch pie crust and sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake 45 minutes longer until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Add sugar, eggs, pecans, coconut, raisins, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour into crust and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sugar-free hot spiced cider
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine apple juice, brown Sugar Twin and water; bring mixture to a boil. Stir in apple pie spice. Lower heat and simmer 30 minutes.

title: sugarless doughnuts
directions: Beat condensed milk,
sour
milk,
eggs
and shortening together, then mix in
flour,
baking
powder,
soda, salt and vanilla.
Roll out on a floured board to a 1/4-inch thickness. Cut with doughnut cutter.
Fry in deep fat at 350° to 375°.

title: tomato dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill for at least 4 hours. Serve with chips.

title: pink lemonade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients and form into 2 balls.
Roll the balls in chopped pecans and refrigerate overnight.

title: broccoli casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Crush Croutettes.
Set aside.
Cook broccoli until tender. Drain.
Place soup and cheese in saucepan.
Heat until melted. Stir in broccoli and top with Croutettes.
Bake at 350° until hot. (P.S.
I put a little cheese on top.)

title: chocolate dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour bottom of rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Beat cake mix, margarine and 1 egg in a large bowl on low until crumbly.
Press into bottom of pan. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake 10 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Stir rice, sugar, egg and cinnamon together in a 1 1/2-quart or a 2-quart casserole.
Then add milk; stir together.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for about an hour (may take longer).
Check in 45 minutes.
Stir a little.
Can add milk if dry or cook longer if it's not thickening.
It will thicken as it sits after cooking process.

title: elegant easy chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix soup and wine together.
Place chicken in shallow baking pan or dish.
Pour sauce over chicken. Top each chicken piece with 1 slice of Swiss cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: congealed tuna fish salad
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in 1/4 cup hot water; add lemon jello to the 2 cups of hot water and mix both gelatins together in serving dish. When almost set, add tuna, celery, lemon juice, olives, pimento and mayonnaise. Chill until firm. Serve on lettuce. Serves 8.

title: orange scones
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a bowl.
Cut in margarine with a pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add yogurt and next 2 ingredients to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened (dough will be sticky).

title: apple-raisin dressing for duck
directions: Combine apples, bread crumbs and raisins.
Add remaining ingredients; mix lightly.
(Mixture should be rather dry since apples will add moisture during roasting.)
Makes enough for a 4 to 5 pound duck.
Fill body cavity, but do not pack.
Close with poultry pins and lace opening with a string.
Bake at 325°.

title: chicken rice medley
directions: Cook vegetables in margarine; simmer for 5 minutes.
Add water and bouillon.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in salt and rice.
Cover tightly; turn heat low and let steam for 20 to 25 minutes or until water is absorbed.
Do not lift lid while rice is cooking.

title: burgundy stew
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a Dutch oven, combine turkey, carrots, celery, onions, water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Mix flour, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and salt into turkey mixture.
Combine wine and tomatoes and pour over turkey mixture.
Cover and cook 1 hour or until turkey and vegetables are tender.
Serves 6.

title: dutch babies
directions: Put butter in 3 to 4-quart size dish.
Set into 425° oven, while mixing batter.
Put eggs in blender at high speed 1 minute. Gradually pour in milk; slowly add flour.
Continue whirling 30 seconds.
Pour batter slowly into pan with melted butter.
Bake until puffy and browned, approximately 20 minutes.

title: rice supreme
directions: Melt margarine in skillet; add cooked noodles and rice until brown.
Add rest of ingredients; simmer 5 minutes.
Put into 1 1/2 quart casserole dish, ungreased.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, covered.

title: mushroom salad
directions: Refrigerate salad for a few hours before serving so that all the seasoning flavors blend together.

title: chess bars
directions: Melt oleo and mix the cake mix and 1 egg together.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream together the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour this over the dough and bake at 350° until brown.

title: corned beef sandwich filling
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve on your favorite bread.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: spinach salad
directions: In a glass bowl, place bite size pieces of spinach in a layer to line whole bowl.
Sprinkle 1 teaspoon sugar over spinach.
Put on another layer of spinach.
Layer thinly sliced purple onion rings on, then layer sliced eggs.
Place a generous layer of peas. Sprinkle top with crumbled bacon and celery slices.

title: chocolate-dipped almond cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well. Shape the dough into 2 rolls.
Wrap rolls and refrigerate until firm, about 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350° and line baking sheets with parchment paper.
Cut dough into 1/4-inch slices.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Melt chocolate candy coating.
Dip one end of cookie into chocolate, coating about halfway and lay on wax paper.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Makes approximately 6 dozen.

title: fudgy caramel wedges
directions: In a small saucepan, melt chocolate and margarine.
Stir constantly; cool slightly.
Add sugar, eggs, vanilla and flour. Line a 9-inch round cake pan with foil and grease.
Pour batter into pan and top with coarsely chopped pecans.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes.
Turn upside down.
Remove foil and put on dish.

title: oyster snacks
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and pour over the crackers.
Mix well.
Let sit for at least 1 hour.

title: 1-2-3 stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in covered dish for 3 hours at 300°.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: white death
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Melt chocolate according to directions on package.
Cover dry ingredients with melted chocolate and stir to cover everything.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Work quickly to avoid mixture starting to set.
Sets up in about 20 minutes.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Mix cream cheese, basil and onion until smooth.
Spread on each slice of ham and roll up along the widest side.
Chill and slice in 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange on plate.
Serve.

title: coffee can bread
directions: Put 1 1/2 cups flour in large mixing bowl with yeast mixed in. In saucepan, put 1/2 cup water; add milk, oil, sugar and salt. Heat to lukewarm.
Add to flour.
Beat until smooth.
Add eggs. Mix well and add rest of flour.
Stir until smooth and elastic.

title: wilted lettuce dressing
directions: Fry bacon; remove and crumble.
Leave 4 tablespoons of drippings in skillet.
Combine all ingredients and heat.
Pour or drip over lettuce.

title: bailey's irish cream
directions: Put eggs in blender and mix lightly.
Add milk and chocolate syrup.
Blend 3 minutes.
Add whiskey and Coffee Rich.
Blend 7 minutes.
Keep refrigerated.
Shake before drinking.
Straight whiskey can be substituted.

title: richard's grilled cheese sandwich
directions: Preheat griddle to piping hot stage.
Put two dollops of margarine in and stir around fast.
Add both slices of bread.

title: whipped cream salad
directions: Mix pineapple and marshmallows; allow to stand for 1 hour. Whip and sweeten whipping cream.
Add to pineapple mixture along with chopped nuts.

title: immediate fruit pie!
directions: Prepare pudding/pie filling according to package directions. Add sliced fruit (with Fruit-Fresh if pie won't be eaten right away).
Pour into crust.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Soak bread in milk 5 minutes.
Add sugar, salt and butter.
Add vanilla mix well.
Bake in greased baking dish.
Bake in pan of hot water at 350 until firm about 50 minutes.

title: 1-2-3-4 cookies
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla, beat.
Add flour slowly, 1 cup at a time, mixing thoroughly each time.
Add soda to last cup of flour before adding to cookie dough.
Form dough into a roll.
Wrap in waxed paper and refrigerate overnight.
To bake, slice 1/8 to 1/4-inch thick.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: grilled fish(red fish, red snapper, or trout)
directions: Season fish with salt and pepper; pour Italian dressing over fish.
Let marinate 3 to 4 hours.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Combine flour and sugar.
Cut margarine into flour mixture until mixture is crumbly.
Add milk gradually and mix well.
Turn dough onto board and with well oiled hands, knead dough about 10 times.
Roll out to about 3/4-inch thick. Cut out biscuits and bake in ungreased pan for 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Cook potatoes. When done, peel off skin. Mash with fork.
Add powdered sugar until the potatoes and sugar are real stiff (use fork or spoon).
Knead in powdered sugar.
Roll out (not thick or thin).
Spread peanut butter all over them. Roll up in a big tube, then cut into small pieces.

title: mom's pineapple cheese pie
directions: Cook over medium heat crushed pineapple, 1/2 cup sugar and cornstarch until glossy; cool.
Cream together cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar; add eggs 1 at a time.
Add milk and vanilla. Spread pineapple mixture in bottom of 10-inch unbaked pie shell. Pour cream cheese mixture over pineapple layer.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 50 minutes.

title: chicken breast bake
directions: Rinse chicken and pat dry.
Arrange in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Top each fillet with slice of cheese.
Combine soup, water, wine, salt and pepper in bowl; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Toss stuffing mix with margarine in bowl.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: homemade corn dogs
directions: Mix all ingredients except hot dogs.
Dry hot dogs on paper towels.
Stick toothpick or corn dog stick in one end of hot dog. Dip into batter and fry in deep fat until desired crispness. Serve hot.

title: brown sugar pie(very rich, cut smaller pieces)
directions: Beat eggs and brown sugar together.
Add vanilla, fresh lemon juice and melted butter.
Beat all together.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
When ready, pie swells like a derby hat, then collaspes when done.
May serve with unsweetened whipped cream.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix the vanilla together with the pumpkin, eggs, margarine and sugar.
Add dry ingredients; mix well.
Then add raisins and nuts.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full or use paper cups (much better without).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 dozen muffins.
Batter can be stored (covered) overnight or up to 2 weeks in fridge.
Muffins freeze well.

title: vegetable croquettes
directions: Prepare the vegetables, steam and chop finely or mince.
Saute the finely chopped onion in butter and add with the eggs and the bread crumbs to the vegetable mixture.
Season with salt and herbs and form into rissoles.
Coat in the bread crumbs and fry in the hot fat until golden brown.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Combine sugar and Crisco; stir until smooth.
Add eggs, salt, baking powder and flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add vanilla, walnut extract, 1 can milk and black walnuts.
Stir until all is smooth. Pour in a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pat's thanksgiving potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes with all ingredients.
Put into a casserole dish and refrigerate until 2 to 3 hours before needed.
Bring to room temperature and bake at 325° for about 25 minutes.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 3 layers.

title: egg, spinach and cheese
directions: In a large bowl, crack eggs and pour spinach in bowl.
Mix well.
Grate cheese and add to egg and spinach mix.
In skillet, brown onions and bell peppers; remove and add to egg mix.
Mix well.
In a large baking dish, put in mixture and bake at 350° until eggs are set.

title: banana bran loaf
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large bowl.
With pastry blender or two knives, cut in butter or margarine until mixture resembles coarse cornmeal.
Add next 3 ingredients and, if desired, dates and nuts.
Mix just until blended.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a preheated moderate oven (350°) for 50 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove to rack to cool completely.
Makes 1 (9-inch) loaf.

title: christmas brew
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil.
Reduce to a simmer.
May be used again and again.
Store in refrigerator.

title: batter bread
directions: Measure flour separately.
Mix yeast, salt and sugar.
Add water, then melted shortening.
Add flour, a little at a time, and mix with spoon.
Let this rise until doubled.
Divide dough and place in 3 greased loaf pans and let rise again.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: crock pot sweet & sour kielbasa
directions: Slice Kielbasa; mix remaining ingredients in bowl, pour over Kielbasa in crock pot.
Cook on high approximately 3 hours or on low all day.

title: cherry delight
directions: Beat egg whites until will stand alone but are not dry.
Add the vinegar and sugar to the other ingredients.
Mix together; form crust in an 8 x 12 x 2-inch dish.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°. Cool.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° for approximately one hour.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 5 hours.
Do not stir or peek.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cook potatoes and then add all other ingredients.
Beat the 2 egg whites and add to mixture.
Pour into two unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° until well done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: spinach pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix egg, cottage cheese, salt and pepper, then add to spinach.
Spoon mixture into an 8-inch pie pan. May add chives.
Sprinkle cheese on top, then bake 30 minutes. Makes 4 servings, 165 calories each.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flavors and buttermilk. Sift together flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Add melted chocolate (melt in warm oven or double boiler).
Blend well together.
Pour into 9-inch stem pan that has been well greased and floured.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Test with toothpick; if done, toothpick will come out clean (from cake center).
Put cake under tight fitting cake cover while still hot. Leave covered until cool.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Cook the chicken in a pot of water with salt and bay leaf. Cut the chicken into bite sized pieces.
Save at least 1/2 cup of the stock. Combine the soups, tomatoes, chicken stock, chilies, onion, chicken, and pepper.
Mix well in a large bowl. Spray or grease a 3 qt. Casserole. Starting with tortillas, layer in casserole, then the soup/meat mixture, topped by cheese.
You should have two or three layers, ending with cheese on the top. Bake at 350 degrees covered with foil, about 45 minutes.

title: coconut chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water.
To beaten egg yolks, add sugar and salt.
Slowly stir in the scalded milk.
Cook over hot, not boiling water, stirring constantly until mixture coats the spoon. Remove from heat.
Add gelatine and stir until dissolved.
Chill until mixture is slightly thicker than consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Add the 3/4 cup coconut and the vanilla.
Beat until stiff the egg whites.
Beat 1/4 cup sugar in gradually.
Fold into gelatine-coconut mixture.
Pour into baked pastry shell.
Chill until firm.
Garnish with whipped cream and toasted coconut. Yield:
1 (9-inch) pie.

title: ham and mushroom quiche
directions: Stir together cheese, ham and mushrooms before arranging evenly in bottom of pie shell.
Add remaining ingredients to beaten eggs and pour over cheese mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 30 to 35 minutes or until knife inserted near middle comes clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: clam chowder
directions: Combine first six ingredients in a 3-quart saucepan and cook until limp.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In saucepan, combine ingredients, except for Equal.
Slowly bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat, stir in Equal and add shrimp.
Makes 4 servings; calories 171.

title: luther's peanut butter cremes
directions: Mix together all except chocolate chips.
Press into pan. Melt chocolate chips in top of double boiler. Spread on top.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, chocolate, vanilla and milk together in saucepan.
Bring to a boil and cook for one minute.
Take off the stove and add oats and peanut butter.
Mix together thoroughly. Spoon onto cookie sheet to cool.

title: fluffy banana bread
directions: In a
large bowl, cream butter, sugar and vanilla well. Add eggs, one
at a time and beat well until fluffy.
Sift dry ingredients and add them alternately with the bananas and sour cream
to
the
butter
mixture, small amounts at a time.
End with
the
dry ingredients and mix gently.	Add nuts.
Bake at 350°
for
one
hour.
(I cut baking time to 45/50 minutes and use small
loaf
pans.
This recipe makes one loaf or 3 small pans.)

title: nut brittle
directions: Stir together sugar and syrup in a 1 1/2-quart casserole (microwave). Microwave at High power for 4 minutes.
Stir in nuts.

title: marble pound cake
directions: 1. Mix sugar and butter on low speed until creamy.

title: tomato pie
directions: Drop tomatoes in hot water to release skin. Layer all ingredients in pan.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Scald milk; cool.
Add shortening, sugar, salt and eggs (well beaten).
Add flour.
Mix as for bread, but not as stiff, adding more flour as needed.
Let rise twice until twice the size.
Roll out, spread butter and cinnamon.
Roll up and slice, about 1 to 1 1/2-inch slices.
Bake in a pan at 350° for 25 minutes or until brown on top.

title: pie crust
directions: Add salt to flour.
Cut in shortening.
Add enough ice water to make it hold together.

title: sausage crescents
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Mix cream cheese into sausage. Spread 1 can of crescent rolls onto cookie sheet. Spread sausage and cream cheese mixture on top of crescents. Put 2nd can of crescents on top of sausage mixture. Bake at 350° for 13 to 15 minutes.

title: akwadu(banana-coconut bake, an african recipe)
directions: Cut bananas crosswise into halves; cut each half lengthwise into halves.
Arrange in greased 9-inch pie plate.
Dot with butter; drizzle with orange and lemon juice.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and coconut.
Bake in 375° oven 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: polly's coconut pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together in a little bowl.
Pour milk in top of double boiler and get quite warm.
Dump mixture into milk.
Cook until it starts getting thick.
Separate eggs; beat the yolks.
Add about 3 tablespoons of mixture to yolks.
Stir and pour back into milk mixture.
Cook until thick.
Set aside and add vanilla, margarine and coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat whites for topping.

title: stove top peanut butter pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, flour and salt.
Add milk and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils. Cook 2 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and stir a small amount of the hot mixture into egg yolks.

Return to hot mixture. Cook 1 minute longer, stirring constantly. Add peanut butter and butter. Stir until blended. Pour into cooled pastry shell. Allow filling to cool. Top at serving time with hot fudge topping.
Garnish with Cool Whip and Reese's pieces.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mash with clean hands all together to form a ball in a bowl, then put on waxed paper; form roll and chill in refrigerator. Slice and top with pecans, if desired.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: aunt emily's italian cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Whip eggs in separate bowl.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt to creamed mixture.
Add some flour mixture, then eggs, then flour, then eggs until all used up.
You may need extra flour if dough is too sticky.
For each extra cup flour, add 1 teaspoon baking powder.
Run a layer of dough onto greased cookie sheet, using a cookie press.
Mix apple butter, nuts and raisins.
Put layer of this filling onto dough and run another layer of dough on top.
Decorate.
Put in 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: gingerbread(easy, excellent and quick)
directions: Mix brown sugar, margarine and flour together.
Take out 1 cup for topping.
Add to remaining the nutmeg, ginger, cinnamon, buttermilk mixed with soda and beaten egg.
Mix and pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle reserved topping. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: layer lettuce salad
directions: Chop pepper, celery and onions.
Layer first five ingredients in casserole dish, starting with lettuce.
Spread peas over chopped vegetables.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and pulp.
Sift flour and baking powder; add gradually to batter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes and, when almost done, pour melted butter over the top.
Bake until done, about 10 minutes more.

title: beef rice
directions: Saute chopped onion and rice in butter until well mixed. Transfer to casserole and add the consomme.
Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: potato cheese soup
directions: Boil the potatoes, onion, celery and carrots until soft.
Mash vegetables right in the water.
Add milk and bring to a boil. Add salt, pepper and cubed cream cheese.
Simmer until cheese is melted.
Do not boil with cheese in it.

title: lemon sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, sour cream and soda.
Add 2 eggs and a cup of flour.
Beat.
Repeat until eggs and flour are all mixed. Add lemon extract and blend.
Pour in a greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Blend first two ingredients well, then add rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle small amount of sugar on graham cracker crust and heat.
Pour pie mixture in crust and chill.

title: "fried" cabbage
directions: Shred cabbage.
In large saucepan combine cabbage with remaining ingredients.
Cook covered over medium heat for about 45 minutes or until cabbage is tender, stirring occasionally.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Add cheese.
Add milk to make a thick batter, stirring only until flour is well moistened. Using 2 forks, drop batter in long, narrow sticks (about 6 x 1-inch) on greased baking sheets.
Press sides smooth.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 12 to 14 sticks.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften cheeses.
Mix together thoroughly.
Add onion flakes. Chill; form into ball and roll in parsley or sprinkle on top. Serve with crackers.

title: italian spaghetti squash
directions: Wash outer skin of squash.
Pierce with fork or knife once. Place in 300° oven in pan with 1/2-inch water.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours until fork pierces skin and squash easily.
Remove from oven and cut in half.
Scrape out squash into platter.
Ladle tomato sauce over top and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serve hot.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: Mix together all the marinade ingredients and marinate meat for at least 4 hours, turning from time to time.
Grill and enjoy!

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl combine eggs, syrup, sugar, vanilla and pecans until well blended.
Stir in pecans and chocolate chips.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Allow to cool.
Serves 8.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed.
Drain and rinse in cold water. Prepare dressing according to package and slice all vegetables into bite-size pieces.
Layer salad in a glass bowl, alternating vegetables with noodles.
Make last layer tomatoes.
Leave a hole in the center.
Place salad dressing in the middle of top layer and sprinkle with bacon bits.
Let stand at least 12 hours to allow dressing to settle to bottom.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Place rhubarb in pie shell.
Mix sugar, cornstarch, salt and egg; beat well.
Add syrup and butter.
Pour over rhubarb.
Cut remaining pie crusts into strips and lattice.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients. Cover and refrigerate. Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: carrot-shoestring salad
directions: Mix all above except shoestring potatoes.
Just before serving, add potatoes so they will stay nice and crisp.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Use 8-quart or larger soup pot.
Brown meat in oil.
When almost browned, add onions to lightly brown.
Add tomatoes, crushed with juice and enough water to cover meat and vegetables. Vegetables can be added now or last 45 minutes to hour.
Add seasonings to taste.
(Lots of onion and garlic powder, minimum salt).

title: peach satin cream pie
directions: In large bowl beat cream cheese and sugar until fluffy.
Slowly blend in Phillips Peach Cream liqueur.
Fold in whipped topping. Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours or overnight. Serve each slice topped with Peach Sauce.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar in eggs.
Dissolve soda in milk.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add with juice and milk to butter mixture.
Add fruit and nuts.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and milk together.
Add green pepper, onion, pepper, dried beef and sour cream.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Break
bread into small pieces; mix with other ingredients. Shape and fry until browned.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Mix flour, salt and pepper together.
Coat chicken pieces with flour mixture.
Place floured chicken in pan with melted butter.
Bake at 350° to 425° for 30 minutes.
Turn chicken.
Cover with lid and bake 30 minutes again or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the soups and milk.
Mix together the dressing, melted butter and chicken broth.
Layer chicken and dressing mixture.
Pour soup mixture over; top with dressing.
Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: vegetarian spaghetti
directions: Saute the onion in a little oil.
Add in garlic and zucchini and saute.
When onion is transparent, add the spaghetti sauce and simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve on spaghetti accompanied by a tossed salad and bread.

title: spoonburgers
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown meat over medium heat, breaking into small pieces.
Drain; add garlic, onion and salt.
Cool 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients except buns.
Simmer about 20 minutes or until thick.
Spoon onto toasted hamburger buns.
Makes 8 sandwiches.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well. Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, at least 4 hours.
Garnish with fresh fruit.

title: creamy vegetable medley
directions: Heat soup to boiling in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in vegetables.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender.
Stir occasionally.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Spoon into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, or until brown.

title: spaetzle(german noodle)
directions: Combine all ingredients well to a thick paste.
Put through a spaetzle maker (or potato ricer) into salted boiling water. Spaetzle is done when all pieces come to the top.
Remove an drain.
Wash in cold water.

title: french cinnamon muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease muffin pans.
Combine flour, sugar and cinnamon in mixing bowl.
Set aside.
In another bowl, beat egg.
Stir in butter and milk.
Add liquid ingredients all at once to flour mixture.
Stir only until flour is moistened.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake about 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: homemade corn bread
directions: Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Keep refrigerated.

title: strawberry souffle salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Put all ingredients in blender and whip after Jell-O has cooled.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put
in
flat
pan or baking dish. Roll out 1 roll of Ritz crackers.
Put on top of casserole with a little cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pepper jelly
directions: Remove seeds from peppers, grind.
Mix peppers, juice, vinegar. Add sugar.
Bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Cool 2 minutes.
Add pectin.
Cool.
Taste and add more peppers if you want it hotter. Add green or red food coloring if desired.
Pour into jelly jars and seal.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine and mix corn meal, eggs, sweet milk, salt and corn together to make batter.
Saute ground meat; drain.
Add onions and peppers.
Prepare skillet for cornbread by greasing and sprinkling with meal and let brown.
Pour half of batter into skillet.
Add beef mixture, onion and peppers.
Top with cheese.
Add remainder of batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: armenian rice pilaf
directions: In medium saucepan, saute orzo in butter until golden brown. Add rice, saute for about 5 more min. Add chicken broth and bring to a full boil. Cover and lower heat, simmer for 25 min. Let stand for 10 min. Fluff with fork.
Serves 4.

title: beet raspberry jelly
directions: Leave roots and about 3-inches of tops on beets. Wash well and cook until tender. Strain juice and add the remaining ingredients. Bring to boil and fill jelly jars.

title: diabetic cole slaw
directions: Add all ingredients together, then put on the Miracle Whip. Can be kept in refrigerator for 1 week.
Keep the juice drained off.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Sauce:
Melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Stir in 2 tablespoons flour until lightly brown.
Add 1 teaspoon tomato paste and mix. Add 1 1/2 cups stock and bring to a boil, slowly whisking constantly until smooth and thick.

title: cream cheese pie crust
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Chill or store overnight in refrigerator.
Roll out on floured board.
Do not use more flour than necessary.

title: parmesan baked catfish
directions: Blend milk and egg in a bowl.
Set aside.
Combine in a shallow dish bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley and sesame seed. Lightly oil a baking dish large enough to hold the catfish fillets in a single layer.
Rub the inside of the dish with a piece of cut garlic.
Dip catfish fillets in milk mixture and roll in crumb mixture, making a good coating.
Arrange in baking dish.
Drizzle with olive oil and sprinkle with salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry pie
directions: Bring 1 cup berries, 3/4 cup sugar, 3/4 cup water and lemon rind to a boil.
Combine remaining sugar, water and cornstarch and stir into the boiling berries.
Cook for 1 minute or until clear and thickened.
Place remaining berries in shell.
Cover with the cooked glaze and chill until completely set.

title: one dish microwave meal
directions: Bake potato in microwave.
Mash into a microwave dish (with or without skin).
Add vegetables (I use corn, peas, carrots, green beans or mixed vegetables).
Sprinkle on pepper, parsley and chives.
Mix in bacon bits.
Cook 2 minutes on Medium.

title: cajun cheese straws
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour and Cajun seasoning.
Cut in the cheese and
butter using a pastry blender, electric mixer, or food processor.
When the mixture clings together and can be formed into a soft ball, put the dough into a cookie press fitted with a star, rosette or long, flat disk.
Press onto an ungreased cookie sheet cutting to desired length.
Bake in a 325 degree oven for about 25 minutes or until dry and lightly browned.
Makes about 6 doz.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine milk, soups, salt and pepper.
Pour over beans.
Mix in 1/2 can French fried onions.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Garnish with 1/2 can onions and pimento. Bake 5 more minutes.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Simmer chicken in pan until completely cooked.
Pour in can of chicken and rice soup.
Fill empty can with rice and pour in. Add water.
Let cook until rice is soft and fluffy.
Then serve.

title: fruit pizzas
directions: Press dough into 6 (4-inch) tart pans.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned; cool.
Meanwhile, combine cream cheese, milk, orange zest and sugar to taste.
In small mixing bowl, beat until smooth.
Spread cream cheese mixture over cooled cookie tart.
Top with fruit.
Makes 6 servings.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Combine
the
oil,
sugar and eggs; beat together for 2 minutes.
Add
the	flour,	salt
and
baking powder.
Stir in alternately with the pineapple juice.
Coat fruit, raisins and nuts
with the flour.
Pour batter on the fruit; mix thoroughly. Pour
into	a
greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake on the lower shelf of oven at 275° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Cool before removing from
pan.	When cool, wrap in aluminum foil.
Store in refrigerator for at least a week or more.

title: italian chicken with potato casserole
directions: Alternately layer chicken pieces, potatoes and garlic. Sprinkle on grated Romano cheese, salt, pepper and parsley to taste. Cover with tomatoes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: skier's chowder
directions: Cook sausage until
brown
and	drain thoroughly.
In a large pot, combine
beans,
tomatoes,
water, onion, bay leaf, seasoning salt, garlic salt, thyme and pepper. Add sausage and simmer, covered, for 1
to 1 1/2 hours. Add potatoes and green pepper. Cook, covered,
15	to
20 minutes, until potatoes are tender. Remove bay leaf. Makes 8 servings.

title: smothered fried cabbage
directions: Discard outer leaves of cabbage.
Cut cabbage coarsely; wash and drain.
Fry fat back in a heavy skillet over medium heat until crisp.
Remove fat back.
There should be enough fat in your skillet to fry cabbage; if not, add butter.
Turn heat up; put cabbage in skillet.
Cover; lower heat and steam (5 minutes). Remove lid and season with salt, pepper and other ingredients, including the ham.
Replace lid and cook additional 10 minutes.

title: taffy
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients except vanilla.
Cook to soft crack stage (270°).
Pour onto buttered platter.
As candy cools, lift edges toward center.
When cool enough to handle, add vanilla and pull, using the fingertips and stretching taffy until it becomes white.
Pull into a long rope and cut with scissors while soft or crack into pieces after it hardens.
Makes 3/4 pound.

title: for a happy home
directions: Mix ingredients with T.L.C. (tender loving care).

title: monkey bread
directions: Completely dissolve yeast in lukewarm water; set aside.
Mix Crisco, sugar and salt.
Add boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Add beaten eggs and mix.
Add flour and yeast alternately.
Mix thoroughly.
Cover.
Let rise until double.
Flatten on lightly floured board.
If too sticky, add a little more flour.
Cut out like biscuits.
Dip each piece in melted butter.
Place in layers in greased and floured Bundt pan.
Cover.
Let rise until double. Bake at 300° for about 1 hour, until lightly browned.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into bread bowl. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tagliarini
directions: Cook egg noodles as directed on package; drain and set aside. Fry burger and onion; drain and add to noodles.
Heat soup, corn, red chili sauce and tomato sauce; add to noodles and burger and add some cheese and olives.
Garnish with olives.
Mix ingredients.
Add green peppers; top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: In a bowl combine beans, corn, soup, sour cream, cheese and onion.
Pour in ungreased 2-quart baking dish.
Combine butter and crumbs over veggies.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: easy new england clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon and saut onion in bacon drippings.
Stir in half and half and remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling and serve.

title: cheesy beef and green chile rice
directions: Combine broth and onion in medium skillet; bring to boil and add instant rice. Cover and turn off heat. Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: sugar and cinnamon coated pecans
directions: Bring sugar, water and cinnamon to a boil; add pecans. Continue to boil on medium to medium-high heat until all liquid is gone. Spread out on baking sheet and bake in oven for about 10 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Last 4 ingredients, mix together to make egg wash.

title: spanakopitta
directions: Thaw spinach.
Drain spinach well.
Mix cottage cheese, spinach and crumbled Feta cheese into mixture.
Beat eggs in a bowl.
Pour beaten eggs over cheeses and spinach; mix well!
Add cream of wheat.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Combine all ingredients to form a dough. Roll out on a floured surface. Cut into 1/4 to 1/2-inch wide strips. Hang up to dry (on plastic hangers works great) for 24 hours. They work great to make homemade soup.

title: e. z. chicken
directions: In a 9 X 13-inch pan pour in the rice.
Add the Cream of Chicken Soup with 2 cans of water which have been mixed together. Sprinkle on 1/2 pkg. dry onion soup mix.
Place chicken breasts on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Place foil on top if it becomes too brown.

title: corn flake holly
directions: Melt butter and marshmallows.
Add vanilla and food coloring. Add corn flakes.
Shape like holly leaves.
Add cinnamon heart to each.

title: 2 hour buns
directions: Mix and let rise 1 hour.
Put in pans; let rise 1 more hour. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Makes about 32 buns.

title: glorified goulash
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese.
Brown hamburger and drain.
Add soup, onion, catsup and cheese.
Mix.
Add to macaroni and cheese. Mix.
Put in large casserole dish.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing mix according to package directions, or mix your favorite way.
Combine milk and meat, divide into 5-8 patties.
On waxed paper, pat each patty into a six inch circle. Put 1/4 C stuffing (for 5 patties) in center of each circle.
Wrap meat around stuffing, seal and place in casserole.

title: surprise meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw frozen potatoes; drain well.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour into an 8-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 25 minutes or more at 350°.
Then reduce heat to 325° for another 5 minutes or until custard is set.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix together.
Use 1/2 teaspoon size portions and flatten. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: lo-cal fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients.
Your favorite fruit can be added.

title: butter chess pie
directions: Cream sugar with butter. Add eggs, meal, water and vanilla. Beat well. Pour into uncooked pie shell. Bake about 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: basic white sauce
directions: Combine milk powder and water.
Stir well and set aside.
Melt margarine in a small, heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Add flour and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly with a wire whisk. Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Cook, stirring constantly, an additional 10 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Yields 1 cup.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat margarine, sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add 1/2 cup sour milk, mixed with dry ingredients.
Beat well.
Stir in zucchini.
Put in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with chocolate bits.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine ingredients; boil 1 hour and simmer 2 hours.

title: 24 hour cole slaw
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly in large bowl.
Cover tightly and refrigerate at least 12 hours.

title: crab au gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine lemon juice, pepper and onion. Toss with crabmeat and set aside.
Melt butter and blend with flour.
Stir in cream and sherry.
Heat and stir until thickened. Add 1/2 cup cheese.
Slowly stir in egg yolk.
Allow to cool slightly before folding in crabmeat.
Pour into well buttered casserole.	Spread remaining cheese on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes until hot and bubbly.

title: crustless pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and add flour and sugar.
Pour in other ingredients. Pour into greased and floured pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until light brown.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon pieces and chopped onions and drain.
Add other ingredients and put in a casserole.
Bake 1 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: pina colada punch
directions: In blender pour cream of coconut; add pineapple juice a small amount at a time.
Add ice cream.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Garnish glass with small slice of orange, lemon, lime or pineapple.
Serve with straw.

title: taco chicken stew(low-fat)
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients except chicken and bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 10 minutes. Stir in chicken.
Heat through.
Makes 4 servings, about 1 gram of fat per serving.

title: standard butter cake
directions: Beat egg yolks in small mixer bowl; cream butter and sugar and add extract.
In meantime, sift flour and measure.
Add baking powder and salt to flour mixture and set aside.
Add beaten egg yolks to butter mixture and beat.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to butter mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff but not dry. Fold into cake mixture.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: shrimp newburg
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add flour, stirring constantly.
Add milk and continue to stir.
As mixture thickens, add cheese, salt, pepper and sherry.
Allow to simmer for 3 minutes.
Add whole shrimp and continue to simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve on toast. Garnish with parsley.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Cook celery and onion in chicken broth for about 20 minutes. Add salt, soy sauce, bean sprouts or vegetables, chicken and cornstarch mixed with cold water.
Cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve on cooked rice or Chinese noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chicken or veal vegetable soup
directions: Cut veal in inch cubes; place in water.
Add salt.
Cook 1 hour.
Add sliced carrots. Cook until carrots well done.
Add peas, cook slowly 15 minutes.
Melt butter; blend in flour and brown slightly.
Add onion and water; bring to boil.
Add sauce to soup; bring to boil.
Remove from heat and serve.
Serves 6.

title: mayonnaise
directions: Cream one-half cup of butter, add the yolks of four eggs, one at a time, stirring well after each addition.

Add two tablespoons of lemon juice, a small quantity at a time, one teaspoon of salt, one-fourth teaspoon of white pepper and very little cayenne pepper; then add one-half cup boiling water and cook in a double boiler until thick as soft custard.

title: creole deviled oysters
directions: Put oysters through meat grinder, saving juice.
Saute chopped onion, celery, bell pepper and parsley in shortening until tender. Mix oysters, eggs and sauteed ingredients.
Soak crackers in oyster juice; squeeze liquid out of crackers, then measure and add to oyster-seasoning mixture.
Put into saucepan and cook 20 minutes over slow heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat. Add Worcestershire, catsup, salt, pepper, lemon juice and garlic (put through a garlic press).
If oysters seem too moist, add 1/2 to 1 cup cracker crumbs.
Put mixture into oyster shells or ramekins; cover with cracker crumbs, dot with butter and brown in hot oven.
Garnish with fresh sprig parsley.
Serves 6.

title: saltine cracker snacks
directions: Use cookie sheet with sides. Line with foil and spray with cooking spray.

title: holly's fried potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and cut into wedges.
Mix flour, fried chicken seasoning and black pepper.
Sprinkle over potatoes and toss until potatoes are coated with mix.
Spray a 10 x 13-inch (or any large pan) with Pam.
Arrange potatoes in pan in a single layer.
Drizzle with liquid margarine.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir. Continue baking for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Can use Cajun style seasoning for a more spicy flavor.

title: chocolate chip cookie pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Cool.
Serve with whipped cream or serve warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; set aside.
Cream shortenings, sugar and egg yolks.
Gradually add milk and flour; mix well.
Add flavorings.
Fold in coconut.
Fold in egg whites last.
Stir only until mixed well.
Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: taco dip
directions: On a 14-inch heatable platter, spread bean dip in a thin layer. Mash avocados with lemon juice and spread over bean dip.
Mix the sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning and spread over avocado. Sprinkle olives, onion and tomatoes and top with cheese.
Heat to melt cheese.
Serve with tostados.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Put ice cream in a bowl to melt. Add Cool Whip to ice cream, then crushed cookies (easiest when put in plastic bag and smashed with rolling pin). Pour into a 9 x 13 cake pan. Cover and freeze.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs, milk and sugar.
Add salt, vanilla and corn. Drizzle butter over mixture.
Bake in casserole at 375° until set. Takes about 1 hour.

title: peanut butter fingers
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugars slowly.
Cream well.
Blend in egg, 1/3 cup peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Add flour and oats.
Mix well.

title: quick and easy barbecue beef
directions: Spray a heavy skillet with Pam.
Place all ingredients in skillet, breaking apart the corned beef and stir until well blended.
Heat on medium heat until bubbly.
Serve on buns for a delicious sandwich.
Serves 8.

title: no weep meringue
directions: In small saucepan, mix the sugar, cornstarch and water.
Cook until thick.
Cool completely.
Beat egg whites, salt and vanilla until stiff in separate bowl.
Add cooled mixture and beat until smooth and stiff peaks form.
Spread over cream pie filling of your choice, sealing to the edge of the pie crust.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until golden light brown.

title: taco soup
directions: Place all ingredients in a large pot and simmer for 1 to 2 hours or place in a crock pot on low for 4 to 6 hours.
Serve with grated cheese and crushed tortilla chips.

title: carolyn's favorite taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients in 9-inch pie plate.
Serve with Doritos.

title: chili pie
directions: Put 1 1/2 cups corn chips in baking dish.
Spread onions and 1/2 of the cheese over chips.
Pour heated chili over onions and cheese.
Top with remaining corn chips and cheese.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in a large bowl. Make a well.
Add other ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Place in two 9 1/2 x 5-inch bread pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
One cup raisins and nuts may be added.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain fat.
Add celery, onion and green pepper.
Cook until tender, but not brown.
Stir in pimento, soup, milk, rice and seasonings.
Pour into an ungreased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 50 minutes.
Mix butter and crumbs.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake 20 minutes more, uncovered.

title: turkey scrapple
directions: Break turkey carcass apart.
Put in large pan and cover with water.
Bring to a boil and simmer about 2 hours.
Cool until you can handle.
Strip bones off all meat.
Discard bones.
To broth, add celery stalks and onion.
Cook until vegetables are tender. Add sage, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add turkey bits and meal (much like mush).
Steam for about 30 minutes.

title: a pea pickin' cake
directions: Combine the cake mix, mandarin oranges with juice, oil and eggs.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lithuanian meatballs
directions: Place crackers in warmed milk.
Add to beef with salt, eggs and garlic.
Add milk to make 1/2 tablespoon rolled meatballs. Fry in medium hot Crisco until done to satisfied specifications. Do not fry in fat that is too hot.

title: monkey bread
directions: Divide bread dough into quarters.
Shake in bag with sugar, brown sugar and spices.
Put sugared dough in greased Bundt pan. Slice butter and top the dough with it.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bring water to boiling in 2-quart saucepan.
Reduce heat to low.
Add oil, salt and flour all at once.
Cook, stirring vigorously until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a compact ball.
Do not over cooked.

title: hello dollie cookies
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in layers, starting with vanilla wafers, chocolate chips, coconut and pecans.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over all.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and blend well.
Dissolve pumpkin in soda.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Add all dry ingredients.
Add pecans last.
Pour into loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: raspberry cream cheese coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Set aside 1 cup of crumbs for topping.
Add baking powder, baking soda, salt, sour cream, egg and almond extract to remaining crumbs.
Mix well.

title: fudgies(no bake cookies)
directions: Boil 1 minute the sugar, milk and margarine.
Remove from heat and add oatmeal, cocoa, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoon on waxed paper.
May substitute 1/2 cup coconut and 1/2 cup nuts for peanut butter.

title: barbecue meat loaves
directions: Combine beef, eggs, crumbs, horseradish, onion, peppers, mustard, milk, salt and pepper together.
Mix well and form 8 small loaves; place bacon on top each loaf.
Place in 9 x 12-inch baking dish with rack.
Combine margarine and catsup; pour over all loaves.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain.
Beat eggs with milk, salt and mustard. Place bread in bottom of well buttered 9 x 13 casserole.
Crumble sausage over bread; top with cheese.
Pour egg mixture over all. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 - 40 minutes. Serves 6.

title: white bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, salt and water together. Add yeast; mix in your mixer bowl and let set 5 to 10 minutes. Put on mixer. Add approximately 5 cups of flour gradually. Let mix 8 to 10 minutes; mixer does your kneading. Take dough out and put on a lightly floured board and just knead 4 or 6 times to form a ball. Put in a bowl with 2 tablespoons of oil. Flip over and let rise, double in bulk. Put in 3 foil loaf pans sprayed. Let rise until double again. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: old-fashioned baked beans
directions: Place beans in medium size kettle, cover with water and soak for 2 hours.
Drain beans; add enough fresh water to cover.
Cover kettle and bring to a boil, then simmer until beans are tender, about 45 minutes.
Do not drain.
Mix in remaining ingredients. Place entire contents of kettle in ovenproof bean pot with lid. Bake in 350° oven for 3 hours.
Stir occasionally and add water as needed.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt margarine in a large skillet.
Mix other ingredients and margarine; mix.
Pour into skillet and bake at 300° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: marshmallow cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 glass cake pan.
Spread a layer of mini marshmallows in bottom.
Mix cake as directed and pour over marshmallows.
Spoon cherry pie filling on top.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: rosamarina salad
directions: Cook the macaroni according to package.
Save the pineapple and orange juices; mix in pan with sugar.
Add flour, salt and eggs.
Cook until thick like pudding, then mix with macaroni; set in refrigerator overnight.
Next day, add oranges and pineapple. Mix in Cool Whip and let it set.

title: tortellini alfredo
directions: Mix together cream and egg yolks.
In saucepan, melt butter over low.
Add cream/egg mixture and heat thoroughly.
At the same time, cook tortellini following directions, then add to mixture. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix so tortellini are well coated. Serve immediately.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: May add cooked prunes, chopped, if desired.

title: black cat cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and cocoa until smooth.
Stir in eggs and sour cream.
Blend the flour, baking soda and salt.
Add to the creamed mixture.
Mix well and fold in the chocolate chips and almonds.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten only slightly with a fork to shape into a circle. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet immediately.
Press candy cane into cookies for eyes and ears of cat.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: crab quiche
directions: Mix eggs, cream and grated cheese and stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in pie
shell. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve marshmallows in boiling water, stirring constantly. Add gelatin, stirring to dissolve.
Chill until slightly thick, but not set.
Add pineapple, strawberries (thawed) and nuts. Chill until set.
Top with mixture prepared of whipped topping and cream cheese, blended together.

title: chinese chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except margarine, almonds and corn flakes.
Put in 2-quart oblong casserole.

title: old-fashioned lemonade
directions: Boil sugar and water in a small saucepan for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
