Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice. Cool, then pour into jar and refrigerate.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop peppers and onions.
Pour scalding water over them and drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and boil 15 to 20 minutes. Place in jars and seal.

title: carroll's concoction
directions: Fix the rice according to directions, add cream of chicken soup.
Heat and stir for 2 minutes.
Add peas and corn.

title: iced mint tea
directions: In 1 quart boiling water, steep the tea bags into strong tea. In large container, combine thawed orange juice, lemon juice, sugar and mint; mix tea in.
Add enough cold water to make 1 gallon.
Stir, strain and serve.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: pure fruit cookies or "good for you cookies!"
directions: Use no flour, no eggs, no sugar!!

title: velvet molasses candy
directions: Put molasses, sugar, boiling water and vinegar in saucepan. Bring to boil, then add cream of tartar.
Boil until mixture will become brittle when dropped into cold water.
Stir constantly during last part of cooking.
When nearly done, add butter and soda.
Turn into a buttered pan; as mixture cools around sides, fold toward center.
When cool enough to handle, pull until porous and light colored, allowing candy to come in contact with tips of fingers and thumbs, not to be squeezed in the hand.
While pulling, add 1 teaspoon of vanilla or 1/2 teaspoon lemon extract.

title: skillet salad
directions: Add all together and simmer for about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
In a small saucepan, combine cream cheese and 2 tablespoon of margarine and stir over medium heat until thick and smooth.
Stir in milk until thick and bubbly. Add 1 teaspoon of salt and a dash of pepper.
Fold in pearl onions, if you wish. Place broccoli in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish and pour cream cheese sauce evenly over the broccoli.

title: chicken and wild rice
directions: Cook rice.
Put everything together except the mayonnaise and soup.
Put this mixture in a baking dish.
Mix the mayonnaise and soup and pour over the mixture.
Cover with foil and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serve with green beans and peach halves with cottage cheese.

title: alvin hopson's texas biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together twice.
After sifting, work in shortening and add buttermilk.
When ingredients are blended, turn out onto floured board.
Roll dough to about 1/2-inch thickness and cut with Texas-size cutter.
Place biscuits on greased sheet and bake in 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Guaranteed to satisfy!

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on jelly roll pan.
Bake according to package and cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise, spices and soup mix.
Spread over crust.
Put raw vegetables on top.
I use broccoli, cauliflower, green and black olives and avocado.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt; pack in ice for 3 hours. Boil vinegar, celery seed, mustard seed and sugar.
Get the mixture hot enough to melt sugar.
Put cucumbers mixture in.
Wait until pickles turn dark, like pickles in a jar do.
Put in jar.

title: oriental chicken wings
directions: Marinate overnight.
Bake at 425° on cookie sheet.
Baste and turn until done.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: easter blueberry muffins
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, sugar and salt together into mixing bowl.
Make well in center.
Add blueberries.
Cool shortening; combine egg and milk.
Add to shortening.
Add shortening mixture to dry ingredients all at once, mixing well.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full with blueberry batter.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 12 muffins.

title: bread pudding
directions: Toast bread, then break into pieces.
Blend eggs, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Pour over toast.
Add milk.
After mixing, add cinnamon, raisins and pineapple.
Mix and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Mix 1/4 cup stuffing mix with 3 tablespoons melted margarine. Mix all other ingredients together and pour into a buttered casserole.
Top with the 1/4 cup stuffing mix that had been mixed with the 3 tablespoons margarine.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot fudge cake and sauce
directions: Boil all ingredients except cake until thickened and creamy. Cool slightly.
Cut cake into squares and split.
Put layers of vanilla ice cream between.
Then cover all with warm sauce.

title: bacon and wild mushroom pasta(servings:  2)
directions: Soak mushrooms in 1/4 cup hot broth until soft.
Drain.
Cut mushrooms into bite size pieces.
Cook bacon; discard all but 3 teaspoons fat.
Remove bacon and crumble; set aside.
In frying pan, add pepper, garlic and mushrooms.
Saute 5 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Add brandy and scrape pan; reduce to glaze.
Return the pepper mixture to pan.
Add remaining 1/2 cup broth and thyme. Simmer 10 minutes or until reduced by 1/2.
Add cream and simmer over very low heat until warm.
Toss with pasta and bacon.
Serves 2.

title: scalloped apples
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Put half of the mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish. Add sliced apples and 1/2 cup water. Add the rest of the crumbs. Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°. Microwave 15 to 20 minutes on High.

title: sour cream waffles
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Beat egg yolks and add egg yolks and sour cream to dry mixture.
Beat egg whites in cold metal bowl until peaks form.
Fold melted butter into batter.
Now fold egg whites in.
Cook on prepared grill.
Best you ever had!

title: fettucine alla carbonara
directions: In a skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
In a medium mixing bowl, beat together eggs and cream just until blended.
Stir in cheese and set aside.
In a large kettle or Dutch oven, cook pasta according to package directions.
Drain and immediately return to hot kettle.
Toss pasta with margarine or butter until melted.
Add bacon and cheese mixture.
Toss gently until well mixed.
Transfer to a warm serving dish.
Sprinkle with parsley and pepper; serve immediately.
Makes 6 main dish servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli about 15 minutes or until you mash with a fork; set aside.
In a bowl, mix sour cream, mushroom soup, eggs, onion and half of the cheese.
Drain broccoli; make sure it is mashed well.
Add broccoli and 3/4 cup cracker crumbs to mixture.
Pour into large casserole dish; sprinkle remaining cheese and crackers on top.
Bake in 340° oven for 35 minutes.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups hot water.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into mold or pan and refrigerate.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: doritos dip
directions: Melt cheese in saucepan.
Brown ground beef; drain and add onion.
Mix all ingredients together and heat in casserole dish.

title: chicken breast roll-ups
directions: Pound chicken flat.
Place 1/2 slice of Swiss cheese and cubed chipped beef in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Roll each chicken breast up and wrap with strip of bacon.
Place in baking pan.
Mix sour cream and soup (undiluted), then pour over chicken roll-ups. Bake uncovered at 275° about 2 hours.
Test for doneness.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top before serving.
Makes 8 servings.
You may use turkey bacon and low-fat sour cream for less fat content.

title: kass knopf(cottage cheese bundles)
directions: Dough:
Mix flour, egg, 1/2 teaspoon salt, baking powder and water into a firm dough (add more flour, if necessary).
Roll out in large sheets, thin like pie crust.
Cut into 3 to 4-inch squares.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Wash, peel and cut up potatoes.
Pat dry with paper towels. Put all ingredients into blender or food processor.
Blend well. Pour batter onto hot, greased griddle or pan (about 1/4 cup for each pancake).
Brown and turn to brown second side.
Serve with sour cream.

title: children's play dough
directions: Add ingredients as listed.
Add food coloring as desired. Keep covered in plastic bags or containers.

title: honey sauce for ham
directions: Combine sugar, sherry, honey, mustard and black pepper; set aside. After ham has cooked for 1 3/4 hours, remove from oven; turn heat up to 425°.
Pour juice from ham into shallow bowl; chill so that fat can be easily skimmed.
Trim off excess fat from ham; score in 3/4 inch diamond shapes with a sharp knife and coat generously with glaze.
Turn oven back to 325° and bake ham 15 minutes; glaze again.
Decorate and return to oven for 15 minutes.
Once more remove ham and glaze, bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven, pour off juices and allow ham to sit 15 to 20 minutes. Serve juices.
Serves 16 to 20.

title: pork chops in beer
directions: After pork chops are browned, add remaining ingredients and simmer until pork is done, 1 hour or so.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Mix sausage, grated cheese and Bisquick mix.
Knead until mix stays together; set aside.
Split peppers and remove seeds.
Stuff a piece of cheese into each half.
Pinch a little sausage mix and flatten.
Wrap the pepper inside flat sausage; mix and shape into egg shapes.
Bake on cookie sheet at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Roll into balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Bring the milk, sugar, salt to a boil in a saucepan, cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly from time mixture starts to bubble around edge of pan.
Remove from heat add the marsh mellows, semi-sweet chocolate pieces and vanilla.
Stir vigorously or until marsh mellows are melted, add nuts. Pour in pan greased with butter.

title: low-fat carrot and zucchini bars with citrus icing
directions: In larger mixing bowl, combine first 5 ingredients; mix well and set aside.
In another large bowl, combine remaining ingredients except icing; mix well.
Add carrot mixture to flour mixture; stir until combined.
Spread batter into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until bars test done.
Place on wire rack to cool completely.
Frost with icing. Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Mix Jell-O and boiling water until dissolved.
Add drained pineapple; set (don't let it get firm).
When set, add cherries, sour cream and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased mold.
Let set until firm or overnite.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix salmon, potatoes, onion, egg and pepper until blended. Form into 8 patties, each about 3/4-inch thick.
Gently press patties in crumbs to coat.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add patties and cook about 4 minutes on each side until brown and crisp.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Add all ingredients to spinach. Refrigerate 2 hours.
Shape into walnut sized balls.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
(Can be frozen on cookie sheets, unbaked, and then stored in freezer bags; do not thaw before baking.)

title: eclair squares
directions: Put water and butter in whipping bowl.
Put in microwave for 3 minutes or until it comes to a boil, then add flour.
Beat well. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread in pan and bake 15 minutes at 450°, then 20 minutes at 350°.
Take out and let cool.
Push down with hand as needed.

title: curried garbanzo beans(chickpeas)
directions: Heat oil; stir in spices and allow to heat 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in chickpeas and enough of liquid to cover.
Stir well.
Mash some of the beans with a potato masher.
Cook until thick. Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon juice, chopped cilantro and tomatoes.
Taste and adjust seasoning.
Serve hot or at room temperature.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: anise biscotti
directions: Cream
margarine
and
sugar.
Add eggs or Egg Beaters, one at	a
time;
then	add
remaining ingredients.
Grease a cookie sheet with an edge or a jelly roll pan.
Spoon dough on each
side of pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; slice and return to pan.	Bake another 15 minutes.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Take cooked chicken and chop into chunks.
Add Veg-All, soup and milk with chicken and mix.
Pour into pie crust and top with other crust.
Slit and butter crust.
Bake at 425° until done.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Press into greased 11 x 17-inch pan.
Mixture will be crumbly.
Mix with mixer last 3 ingredients.
Pour over cake mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing thoroughly.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: zucchini with cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
With a stiff brush, scrub zucchini well.
Cut crosswise into 1/4-inch slices.

title: magnolia fried chicken salad
directions: Deep fry tender bites; remove from fryer.
Drain.
Combine next 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss well, cover and chill. To portion, arrange 3 cups salad greens on plate.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup mushrooms and 1/4 cup mandarin oranges.
Add 1 tablespoon walnuts.
Top with 5 ounces of chicken.
Accompany with 1/4 cup Charleston Apricot Dressing.

title: nacho-tortilla dip
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Heat all ingredients together in slow cooker or on low on stovetop, but not in the microwave. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: alma's coconut pie
directions: Bring milk to a boil; set aside.
Mix flour and sugar; add to well beaten egg yolks.
Beat until lemon color.
Mix with scalded milk and cook in double boiler until thick.
Add coconut.
Pour in deep dish cooked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown in 350° oven.

title: olive-cheese balls
directions: Mix thoroughly cheese, butter, hot pepper sauce, salt, paprika and flour.
Form portion of dough around each well drained olive. Bake in 400° oven for about 15 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: crunchy jumble cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Blend together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture. Stir in Rice Krispies and chocolate chips.
Drop by level tablespoons full and bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Dough will be very stiff.
Don't try to double.

title: 2 pecan pies
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour evenly into pie crusts.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat shortening and sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in rolled oats.
Chill.
Shape dough into balls about 1 inch in diameter.
Place about 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° (moderate oven) 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet while warm.

title: chicken divan
directions: Defrost broccoli.
Place on bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan. Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Mix mayo and soup.
Pour over top.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: heavenly delight pie
directions: Melt Hershey bar in microwave (do not burn).
Mix 1/2 chocolate and 1/2 Cool Whip with blender.
Mix other half together.
Pour into shell and chill until set (approximately 2 hours).
Additional Cool Whip can be served on individual pieces if desired.

title: carrot salad
directions: Cover raisins with boiling water; let stand 5 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator one hour.
Serves four.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chips, butter and peanut butter.
Pour over cereal. Stir.
Pour into bag filled with powdered sugar and shake until coated.

title: baked cheese canapes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cheese, onion, egg white and Tabasco sauce and beat with whisk until light.
Spread the mixture on muffin and bake until lightly browned

title: low calorie dressing
directions: Blend all
ingredients.
Two tablespoons of this dressing equals 25 calories.

title: amish peanut butter spread
directions: Combine brown sugar, water, Karo and maple flavoring in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Blend together peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Remove syrup from heat and blend into peanut butter mixture.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: In medium bowl, combine 3/4 cup of flour, yeast, sugar, salt, water and 2 teaspoons oil; mix with mixer on low until flour is just moistened.
Gradually stir in remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough onto lightly floured surface.
Knead about 5 minutes or until smooth and elastic.
Place dough in greased bowl. Turn dough over to expose greased side; cover with towel.
Set in warm place to rise about 45 minutes or until doubled.

title: grandma's tomato pudding
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, in a 3-quart saucepan over medium heat, heat tomatoes to boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer until tomatoes are soft, about 10 minutes.
Uncover saucepan and cook 15 minutes longer, until tomatoes are slightly thickened, stirring often.
Stir in brown sugar, tomato paste and salt.
Arrange bread cubes in a 3-quart casserole.
Pour melted butter over bread cubes; top with tomato mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 to 40 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Makes 10 servings.

title: mexican dip
directions: You will also need a 13 x 9 baking dish. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together well.
Roll into small balls.
Drop on cookie sheet and press down with fork.
Bake at 325° to 350° for about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: buttermilk cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Put oil in a 10-inch iron skillet and place in oven to heat.
Put milk in a medium size mixing bowl and add soda and stir.
Add meal, flour, salt, baking powder and egg. Mix well.
Add 2 tablespoons of hot oil to mixture and stir.
Pour in pan and cook until brown, about 20 or 25 minutes.
(Sometimes I add 2 tablespoons of sugar to mixture.)

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Add salt, pepper and onions to taste.
Shape into balls and bake about 1 hour.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: *Parboil head of cabbage.
Cool and cut out core. Separate the leaves.
In a small skillet, put in the shortening or oil and saute the onion until clear.
In a large bowl, put the ground meat, rice, eggs, salt, pepper and sauteed onion. Mix well together.
In a large kettle, make a bed of the sauerkraut. Sprinkle with paprika.
Make even balls of meat.
Put on a cabbage leaf. Roll up and tuck in ends.
Place tomato juice and/or tomatoes over this. Add about 1/2 can of water.
Cook until tender, about 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot fudge pudding
directions: Sift together into a bowl the first five ingredients. Stir in the milk and melted shortening.
Blend in the nuts.
Spread in a 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with mixture of brown sugar and cocoa.
Pour over entire batter the hot water.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: microwave country style ribs
directions: Place ribs in 3-quart (13 x 9 x 2-inch) glass baking dish; cover with wax paper.
Cook on 70% or Medium-high (roast microwave) for 25 minutes.
After 15 minutes, rearrange by placing outside ribs in center.
Drain off fat.
Mix remaining ingredients well and brush over both sides of ribs.
Cook, covered, on 70% (roast) for 30 to 35 minutes or until meat is fork-tender.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pizza crust
directions: Mix the first 2 ingredients and let stand 10 minutes.
Mix remaining ingredients, then stir in yeast and water.
Spread on pan and let sit 5 minutes. Top with favorite sauce and toppings. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix together.
Cook for 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery

title: pecan butterscotch bread
directions: In a large bowl, combine all of the ingredients and mix well. Pour into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Let cool before serving.

title: quick liver
directions: Saute liver in butter; take out.
Saute onions, put in a little ketchup, stir, put in rest of ingredients.
Stir; put liver back.
Serve with rice.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Debone and shred chicken; set aside.
In small skillet, saute onion and bell pepper in margarine or butter.
Boil spaghetti al dente.
Drain and place in a large bowl.
Mix spaghetti, peas, mushrooms, cheese, and tomatoes.
Add chicken, sauteed onion and bell pepper.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: pecan pie
directions: Melt butter; add other ingredients.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quaker's best oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together margarine and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices.
Add to margarine mixture, mixing well. Stir in oats.
Drop by tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8 to 9 minutes for chewy, 10 to 11 minutes for crisp cookie. Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: fruit salad
directions: Beat eggs up and add vinegar and sugar in double boiler and cook until thick.
Add butter and mix.
Then pour hot mixture over fruit.
Fold this mixture into whipped cream.
Can have nuts and other fruits.

title: butter crumb potatoes(microwave)
directions: Peel potatoes and slice in 1/4-inch pieces.
Roll potatoes in melted butter, then in bread crumbs.
Arrange in baking dish. Drizzle with butter.
Cover baking dish.

title: pork chop and pasta dinner
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water according to package directions; drain.
Place macaroni in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: crock-pot swiss steak
directions: Layer ingredients beginning with 1 can of tomato sauce, 1/2 at a time with couple pieces of steak in between, then the tomato soup and ending with onion soup.
Repeat meat, sauce, meat, sauce, meat, soup; onion soup should be the last on top.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
If in a hurry, can start on high, then go to low for 4 to 6 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes, green pepper and onion.
Mince hot pepper and garlic.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pour into pint jars and water bath for 35 minutes.
Four times recipe makes 10 pints.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Drop tablespoon at a time into hot fat in deep frying pan and cook until golden brown.
Drain on paper and serve hot with butter and maple syrup.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook chicken and shred meat; set aside.
Cook rice as directed; set aside.
Cook onions in margarine.
Blend in flour, soup, mushrooms and milk.
This is your sauce so add salt and pepper.
In a large casserole, add sauce, then rice, then chicken. Top with cheese.
Bake at 300° until bubbly or cheese melts.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Beat egg whites and cream of tartar on high speed until stiff. Add vanilla, lemon juice and sugar or substitute.
Continue beating until very stiff.
Beat in strawberries on low speed, scraping to distribute evenly.
(Should be large chunks of fruit; beat just until blended.)
Chill.
Serves 4 generously.

title: best ever punch
directions: Mix all ingredients except 7-Up.
Add only a little of the 7-Up.
Freeze mixture.
Thaw to mushy stage just before serving (usually need to thaw about 3 hours).
Add 7-Up and ladle into cups.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Prepare the fruits and nuts.
Roll fruits and nuts in flour. Sift the flour, then mix together the remains of flour and spices. Cream the butter and sugar.
Mix the well beaten egg yolks and dried ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.
Makes 2 large fruit cakes.
Steam 3 hours, then bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tossed salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together and add your favorite dressing.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: In a 10-inch deep dish pie pan with prepared crust, line with apples.
Mix together sugar, flour and spices and sprinkle over apples.
Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar.
Bring to a boil and pour over apples.
Put on top crust and bake at 400° for 40 minutes.

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix well and form into ball or 3 rolls.
Garnish with finely chopped nuts or parsley and paprika.
May use whatever you like.

title: spinach parmesan
directions: Cook spinach in water.
Drain well.
Place spinach into buttered 1-quart ovenproof serving dish.
Combine softened cream cheese, milk and 2 tablespoons of Parmesan cheese.
Spread mixture over spinach.
Sprinkle with paprika and the rest of the Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: razorback corn bread
directions: Fry sausage until done.
Reserve 2 or 3 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble sausage.
Combine corn meal, flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
In separate bowl, combine eggs, pepper, onion, corn, buttermilk and cheese.
Add egg and sausage.
Pour into greased skillet and bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Add vinegar and beet juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat until thick and clear.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and drained beets.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix these thoroughly, add tears of joy and sorrows, and sympathy for others.
Flavor with little gifts of love and kindly service.
Fold in 4 cups prayer and faith to lighten all other ingredients, and raise the texture of great heights of character and Christian living.

title: grandma elliott's lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and water in a saucepan. Stir gradually over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils. Boil for 1 minute. Slowly stir at least 1/2 of the hot mixture into egg yolks; blend into remaining hot mixture and boil for 1 minute longer, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and continue stirring until smooth. Blend in butter, lemon juice and rind. Pour into a baked pie shell and top with meringue.

title: chicken and red sauce
directions: Place chicken pieces skin side up (or skin chicken).
Wash and scrub potatoes.
Cut in half and place cut side down between chicken.
Add tomato sauce, water and oil (I don't add oil as we don't need the extra fat and calories).
Cover to about one inch over chicken.
Add salt and pepper and sprinkle "cinnamon" on top. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange milk punch
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shake or stir before serving.

title: brandy slush
directions: Bring 7 cups water and sugar to a boil.
In a separate pan boil the tea bags in 2 cups water.
Once both pans have boiled, remove from heat and mix together.
After the mixture has cooled, add orange juice, lemonade and brandy.
Mix well.
Place the mixture in the freezer to set.
(It will not freeze hard, but will remain slushy.)
Stir after 24 hours or it will separate.
Serve with 7-Up or Sprite.

title: baked corn
directions: Bake in greased casserole for an hour, or until firm.

title: agnes' chicken casserole
directions: To stuffing mix, add the water and margarine.
Set aside.
Mix celery, onions, mayonnaise, chicken and salt.
Pour in with stuffing mix, then slightly beat 2 eggs and beat again in milk. Put stuffing mix in greased baking dish, then pour milk and egg mixture over this.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.

title: sudie's chicken
directions: In an electric skillet place chicken and salt and pepper.
In a bowl, mix soup, bell peppers, celery, onion, milk, Worcestershire sauce, butter and lemon juice.
Mix and pour over chicken.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 4 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: banana blueberry oatmeal bread
directions: Sprinkle blueberries with 2 tablespoons of the flour.
Sift remaining flour, sugar and baking powder.
Stir in oatmeal.
Blend eggs, margarine and banana.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add blueberries.
Pour batter into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cool 10 minutes then remove from pan. Wrap when cool.
Store 1 day before slicing (if you can wait).

title: grandma's marinara sauce(in memory of maria bragaglia)
directions: Heat oil to warm.
Add garlic cloves and cook on low to medium heat until cloves slightly brown up.
Add tomatoes and stir.
Add parsley, basil, salt, celery leaves and stir well. Bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Then reduce heat to low, cover and let simmer 30 minutes.
This is a light sauce.
Add tomato paste, if a thicker sauce is desired.
Makes 6 servings of sauce.

title: greek style fresh tomato slices
directions: Arrange sliced tomatoes on attractive serving platter.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Mix soups, water and rice in large roast pan.
Submerge chicken into soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: lime punch
directions: Mix kool-aide as directed on package. add ginger ale and pineapple juice, mix well. Let sherbet soften a little, cut up and put on top of punch.

title: cheese-filled rolls
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.
Stir in flour, egg yolk, lemon peel and lemon juice.
Roll dough into 15-inch square on lightly floured surface.
Cut into 25 (3-inch) squares.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Spoon about 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture onto center of each square.
Bring 2 diagonally opposite corners to center of each square, overlapping slightly.
Pinch.
Let rise until double, about 40 minutes.

title: seafood cocktail sauce
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
together
to your own individual degree of
hotness
and chill.
Serve over lettuce for shrimp cocktails or to accompany raw of cooked seafood.

title: macaroni and beef
directions: Brown and drain meat; put in crock-pot.
Cook macaroni; drain. Add macaroni and the rest of ingredients.
Stir and cover.
Cook on low for 7 hours.

title: raisin bars
directions: Boil raisins and water; set aside to cool.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Add raisins.
Pour into jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Drizzle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: apple dumplins
directions: Peel and core apples.
Place apple on square of pastry large enough to wrap up and around apple.
Combine brown sugar and raisins.
Spoon brown sugar and add raisin mixture into core of apple.
Add a pat of butter on top.
Finish layer with brown sugar mixture.
Sprinkle cinnamon and allspice over apple.
Wrap pastry up and around apple, pinching together and place in baking dish.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Mix beef, rice, salt and pepper with 1/2 can of soup.
Stuff peppers with meat mixture.
Stand upright in baking dish.
Pour over remaining soup, diluted with 1/2 soup can water.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes and uncovered 15 minutes longer at 350°.

title: low-fat crab enchiladas
directions: Combine crab, 1/2 ounce of Jack cheese, 1/3 cup picante sauce, celery, cream cheese, onions and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Spoon 1/3 cup of filling onto each tortilla center.
Roll up and lay seam side down in Pam sprayed baking dish.
Spoon remaining picante over top evenly.
Cover with foil and bake in 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Top with remaining Jack cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Put butter and milk in center of cocoa and sugar mixture.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Stir well. Add vanilla and pecans. Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch dish.
Put in refrigerator for 20 minutes.

title: easy corn casserole
directions: In a buttered baking dish, combine the corn, egg and sugar. Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: yellow pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour pan.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Tube pan: 50 to 60 minutes; 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan: 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool tube cake 25 minutes, then put on serving plate. Cool 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together and press in the bottom of a pan.

title: georgia sally lunn cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Combine eggs and milk.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients and liquid alternately to creamed mixture.
Put in greased 9 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: szoradi's play dough(not for human consumption)
directions: Mix water, flour, salt, oil, cream and tartar and food coloring together.
Stir constantly over medium heat until the dough becomes the consistency of mashed potatoes.
Let dough cool.

title: zesty roast beef
directions: Roll roast in flour and brown in skillet.
After browning, put in crock-pot.
Place potatoes and carrots in pot.
Mix onion soup, tomato Ro-Tel, soy sauce and Worcestershire in a two cup measuring cup.
Finish filling cup with water to make 2 cups.
Pour over roast.
Turn crock-pot on high for 1 hour, then low for as long as it takes to finish cooking roast.

title: pineapple angel food trifle
directions: Drain pineapple tidbits, reserving 1 c. juice; set aside. Combine instant pudding mix, 1/2 c. reserved juice, and milk in large bowl.
Beat at low speed with an electric mixer 2 minutes or until thickened.
Fold in sour cream and pineapple tidbits.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Mix and bake 40 minutes at 375°.

title: chinese hash
directions: Cook rice.
Brown ground beef.
Add onions and celery.
When ground beef is nearly done, finish browning.
Put mixture in a casserole dish and add rest of ingredients.
Stir to mix.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chicken and noodle casserole
directions: Prepare soups as directed on cans.
Add chopped celery, green pepper and minced onion.
Bring to a light boil.
Add chicken and simmer while cooking noodles as directed on package.
Add soup to drained noodles.
Let simmer 20 minutes.
Pour noodles and soup mixture into ungreased casserole dish.
Layer with cheese and then cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: oven-baked apple-pecan pancake
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Combine pancake mix, milk, eggs and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Mix well.
In 9 or 10-inch ovenproof skillet, saute apples in melted butter over medium-high heat until tender. Remove skillet from heat; sprinkle apples with nuts.
Pour batter evenly over apples and nuts.
Combine remaining sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over batter.
Cover skillet with lid or foil.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until pancake is puffed and sugar melted.
Loosen side of pancake from skillet; cool slightly.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken breasts until tender.
Take chicken off bone. Cut into small pieces.
Mix cream of chicken soup, broth and vegetables together in a saucepan.
Mix plain flour and buttermilk together; beat well.
Pour over top of chicken, soup and vegetables.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 45 minutes or until top is brown.
Serve.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Mix together until smooth. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
